revolving_hearts:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f49e.png\" data-shortname=\":revolving_hearts:\" /> involved in the latest ... MEGA session. Incredibly interesting; e.g. the many aspects that where touched upon - so i&#039;ll have to read it a second time in order to let it sink in.<br /><br />Just wow.<br /><br />Again Thank you all !<br /><br /><hr /><br /><b>I have a personal story to add about <span style=\"color: rgb(184, 49, 47)\">fungus</span> </b><br /><br />Around 2 years ago i wrote in one of the health threads here for advice regarding leaking ears, which turned up in me out of nowhere. Since then, I have tried just about everything i could think of during the past 2 years - and nothing helped. (The more i tinkered with my ears, the worse it got). Even H2O2 didn&#039;t help, but rather turned my ear(s) completely jammed.<br /><br />Anyway; this went on in many waves - often just one ear at the time - albeit the constant leakiness with tough fluids, never  disappeared.<br /><br />Last August 2023 - things culminated suddenly into the worst episode of all: waking up one morning - without i could hear anything in both of my ears, and knowing i had to work driving subway trains in the evening... it freaked me out quite a bit. (it worked-ish in the evening, as the tough goo left a tiny-tiny opening, just barely enough so i could at least hear a little bit - in order drive the trains and hear orders in the radio).<br /><br /><b>Story behind / culprit:</b><br />Something guided me gradually to where the origin of all this ear mess was: <b><span style=\"color: rgb(184, 49, 47)\">It was in my washing machine</span></b><span style=\"color: rgb(184, 49, 47)\">.</span> I had during the past 2 years noticed that our clothes - even after coming out &quot;fresh&quot;, had a peculiar smell of fungus, which not even the softener could mask - and it just got worse and worse. But where was the source ?! I just couldn&#039;t figure it out. I did look into the washing machine, but didn&#039;t find anything...<br /><br />One day after focussing intensely and listening inwards - i had the idea of once again digging into the washing machine - <u>but this time even deeper</u>. The multi folded isolation layers in the opening where you put in the clothes.... What did I find ? A incredible, really thick layer of fungus - present 360° all around - ghastly, horrible smelling black-brown in nature. It was so hidden, that i never came of the idea to dig that deep. (Nor did i expect such fungus layer to establish itself there) It took me 1 hour to remove it.... boy, that smell... was... *HURRK*<br /><br />So, what happened was that the thick fungus basically infected all our clothes for many years - including being present in our pillows - to which my ears reacted strongly. Sal had just switched to a &quot;new&quot; pillow for me (probably when it was wet, made the fungus grow even more, because it takes quite a while to get pillows dry). So, when i slept on it in August 2023, it took only one single night, abruptly to induce another episode of leaky ears - and new this time - also severe infection in both ears.<br /><br /><b>Ever since I cleaned the isolation layers in the washing machine</b><br />scraping it off - disinfecting it with vinegar + 95°C hot water -  and then another run with bicarbonate, as well washing our clothes (and bought new pillows *LOL*); there is no more fungus smell in our clothes.<br /><br /><u>And no more leaky ears.</u> Not even a hint. The yellow-orange stuff that normally protects the ears, started to return in both ears doing its natural thing - and I couldn&#039;t be happier <img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"🥰\" title=\"Smiling face with hearts    :smiling_face_with_3_hearts:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f970.png\" data-shortname=\":smiling_face_with_3_hearts:\" /><br /><br /><b>So, what is it, I wish to point at here ? </b><br />That a source of (heavy) fungus infestation somewhere at home, could be the reason for unexplained illness - and it may not always be obvious from where the fungus is coming from / or is located.<br /><br />(I do have to add, that Sal my husband, didn&#039;t have any issues at all. Perhaps he is used to fungus, because when you lived in Sicily for decades - well - there is fungus everywhere)","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":17410,"user":"Arlind","date":"2024-04-02T22:49:31+0200","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17316,"user":"KaWaiAwaAwa","date":"2024-01-24T21:09:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-24T03:52:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9854,"user":"oli 518","date":"2024-01-23T03:42:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5556,"user":"freigeist2.0","date":"2024-01-21T15:46:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17361,"user":"seve","date":"2024-01-21T15:18:03+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-20T19:28:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6869,"user":"artofdream","date":"2024-01-20T09:31:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11608,"user":"nidO","date":"2024-01-20T01:48:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":29,"user":"dantem","date":"2024-01-20T00:42:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-19T23:37:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2826,"user":"1peacelover","date":"2024-01-19T22:04:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-19T18:36:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-19T18:15:06+0100","reaction":"Love"},{"user_id":5393,"user":"sbeaudry","date":"2024-01-19T01:04:36+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":7597,"user":"hiker","date":"2024-01-18T20:54:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16150,"user":"Franck-alexandre","date":"2024-01-18T20:25:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11611,"user":"Mikkael","date":"2024-01-18T19:21:01+0100",