ser":"ryu","date":"2024-01-16T20:43:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12421,"user":"Set Terrad","date":"2024-01-16T19:50:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-16T19:31:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-16T19:24:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-16T19:12:42+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-01-16T19:06:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-16T18:49:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-01-16T17:20:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13630,"user":"Stella Marys","date":"2024-01-16T16:31:47+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-01-16T16:29:53+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11382,"user":"Odin","date":"2024-01-16T16:25:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7615,"user":"mimimari","date":"2024-01-16T16:24:16+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-16T16:20:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12697,"user":"youlik","date":"2024-01-16T16:01:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7765,"user":"Goemon_","date":"2024-01-16T15:56:55+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":11120,"user":"Mr.Cyan","id":1155662,"date":"2024-01-16T15:27:25+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Q: (Joe) And where is it likely to be released? Globally, or in one particular area?<br /><br />A: California, New York, Singapore, Paris, London.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />Well, Singapore as a location would not be surprising.<br /><br />I recall an article by Bulgarian journalist Dilyana Gaytandzhieva that had a map with Singapore in it as one of the current locations of a US bioweapons lab.<br /><br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"14145\" data-url=\"https://www.sott.net/article/375723-Pentagon-Biological-Weapons-Program-Never-Ended-US-Bio-labs-Around-The-World\" data-host=\"www.sott.net\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sott.net%2Fimage%2Fs22%2F446369%2Ffull%2F1024499606.jpg&amp;hash=cbc401c97ef170c05f4063fa0c28694f&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.sott.net\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://www.sott.net/article/375723-Pentagon-Biological-Weapons-Program-Never-Ended-US-Bio-labs-Around-The-World\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Pentagon Biological Weapons Program Never Ended: US Bio-labs Around The World</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">Comment: In light of the &#039;COVID-19 pandemic&#039;, which - despite its mortality rate being blown up out of all proportion to reality - is, nevertheless, indeed an illness stemming from infection by the SARS-CoV-2 virus first discovered by the Chinese...</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sott.net%2Ffavicon-16x16.png&amp;hash=45e2e27813e95541bcc0cf6a827d2094&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.sott.net\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>www.sott.net</div></div></div></div><br />It is a small island (around ~700+ square kilometers); but there are still many places off limits and restricted military sites and any one of these can host these sites above ground or underground. Singapore is also a site of a massive BBC relay station with lots of massive antennas. I have been to the site - and the view of the site reminded me of pics of HAARP (not the same antenna array, but it had the same feel to it).<br /><br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"191272\" data-url=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BBC_Far_Eastern_Relay_Station\" data-host=\"en.wikipedia.org\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BBC_Far_Eastern_Relay_Station\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">BBC Far Eastern Relay Station - Wikipedia</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\"></div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fstatic%2Ffavicon%2Fwikipedia.ico&amp;hash=5b43b2db373f6af9b865a4001a82536e&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"en.wikipedia.org\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>en.wikipedia.org</div></div></div></div><br />As is common knowledge - the Singapore government is staunch ally of the US and western powers and is their permanent &quot;Aircraft Carrier&quot; in South East Asia - located crucially at a shipping chokepoint in the Straits of Malacca - another sea route through which China receives most of its oil and goods.<br /><br />Another strange thing they have been doing over the last year is Project Wolbachia - releasing GM mosquitoes in order to combat dengue fever cases that have been skyrocketing (most likely because of the extensive use of the mRNA vaccines).<br /><br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"191273\" data-url=\"https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/five-more-residential-areas-to-be-part-of-project-wolbachia-to-curb-dengue\" data-host=\"www.straitstimes.com\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fstatic1.straitstimes.com.sg%2Fs3fs-public%2Fstyles%2Flarge30x20%2Fpublic%2Farticles%2F2023%2F11%2F21%2Fyaohui-pixgeneric-1876.jpg&amp;hash=87357f34f4d8f146c6153a367a59ed51&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.straitstimes.com\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/five-more-residential-areas-to-be-part-of-project-wolbachia-to-curb-dengue\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Five more residential areas to be part of Project Wolbachia to curb dengue</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">The areas are Bukit Merah-Telok Blangah, Clementi-West Coast, Commonwealth, Holland and Marine Parade-Mountbatten. Read more at straitstimes.com.</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.straitstimes.com%2Fthemes%2Fcustom%2Fstraitstimes%2Ffavicon.ico&amp;hash=bec9e674e03176c0ae21d47cd37feb96&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.straitstimes.com\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>www.straitstimes.com</div></div></div></div><br />Sounds like a good cover story to test mosquitoes as a delivery vector for new viruses...<br /><br />On a side note - just over the last 2 weeks, i have met like 5-6 people that had &quot;Covid&quot; right after getting off a flight at Changi Airport (Singapore&#039;s main airport and it is also an important air hub in Asia). They got sick with a bad cold/flu within 24 hours of returning to Singapore - and they didnt get sick while they were travelling abroad. It seems to be a pattern now and before this session, the thought did cross my mind if they were testing some pathogen.<br /><br />Something doesn&#039;t seem right - and as the C&#039;s said, the timelines are definitely accelerating.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":29,"user":"dantem","date":"2024-02-09T00:37:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-25T17:56:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11459,"user":"ToxicCoward","date":"2024-01-22T22:56:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":1666,"user":"adam7117","date":"2024-01-22T12:04:42+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6869,"user":"artofdream","date":"2024-01-21T05:36:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-20T19:44:57+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7597,"user":"hiker","date":"2024-01-20T03:51:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-20T00:48:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-19T23:41:49+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2826,"user":"1peacelover","date":"2024-01-19T22:12:25+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":15344,"user":"Cassis","date":"2024-01-19T19:14:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-19T18:53:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3693,"user":"JEEP","date":"2024-01-19T02:00:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5393,"user":"sbeaudry","date":"2024-01-19T01:55:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4373,"user":"Rhys","date":"2024-01-18T23:40:49+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16530,"user":"AvibeZ","date":"2024-01-18T22:33