was some kind of free formal energy floating about and hitting susceptible...<br /><br />A: Yes</b><br /><br />Q: (Andromeda) Like a ripple.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>It reminded me of the phrase: where it&#039;s thin, it breaks.<br /> On the same Thursday, I had a problem. It doesn&#039;t sound very scary: my laptop&#039;s memory burned out and all my information about work, hobbies, books, and useful things saved from the Forum for <b>almost a year </b>disappeared. <br /> Everything happened in front of my eyes in one second in the evening. The memory cannot be restored. It turned out to be a new kind of memory that overheats very much and mine was the most unreliable.<br /><br /> It seemed to me that we took precautions: we periodically copied information to external hard drives, and uploaded some of it to the Yandex Disk cloud. And in fact, it turned out that the last time I updated information on them was in March 23 (how quickly and imperceptibly time flies<img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/huh.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":huh:\" title=\"Huh?    :huh:\" data-shortname=\":huh:\" />), one drive broke down, the other was lost, the cloud did not copy automatically for some reason. I often put my laptop on the bed with a fluffy blanket<img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/bashhead.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":headbash:\" title=\"Bashing head    :headbash:\" data-shortname=\":headbash:\" /><br /><br />In general, it &#039;s my own fault all around. I lost my vigilance and did not listen to the quiet squeak of an inner voice that tried to tell me in December of the 23rd year that it was time to save new information. Now I&#039;m recovering all the information bit by bit and periodically tearing my hair out. AndrewMn also bought a special fan table for a laptop, a fast large flash drive, and I will write in blood on a piece of paper at my workplace that I need to save at least 1 time a month. <br />Unfortunately, these are not all the troubles that happened in those days, but more about them later.<img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"☹️\" title=\"Frowning face    :frowning2:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/2639.png\" data-shortname=\":frowning2:\" />","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":17410,"user":"Arlind","date":"2024-04-03T00:51:11+0200","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":29,"user":"dantem","date":"2024-02-09T11:39:52+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-25T17:59:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9854,"user":"oli 518","date":"2024-01-23T23:59:07+0100","reaction":"Sad"},{"user_id":8800,"user":"SMM","date":"2024-01-23T19:22:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11459,"user":"ToxicCoward","date":"2024-01-22T22:59:24+0100","reaction":"Sad"},{"user_id":5556,"user":"freigeist2.0","date":"2024-01-21T19:54:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6869,"user":"artofdream","date":"2024-01-21T05:41:51+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7597,"user":"hiker","date":"2024-01-21T05:10:53+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-20T19:53:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-01-20T14:15:42+0100","reaction":"Sad"},{"user_id":2567,"user":"miguel angel","date":"2024-01-20T08:54:42+0100","reaction":"Sad"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-20T01:17:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-19T23:42:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2826,"user":"1peacelover","date":"2024-01-19T22:16:15+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-19T19:04:12+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":5393,"user":"sbeaudry","date":"2024-01-19T17:56:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3693,"user":"JEEP","date":"2024-01-19T02:53:59+0100","reaction":"Sad"},{"user_id"