at. <br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 13701\" data-quote=\"Gruchaa\" data-source=\"post: 1155647\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155647\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155647\">Gruchaa said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Is there a possibility that it&#039;s not only Russia, but also Slavic countries also like Poland and Ukraine? I am asking, cause C&#039;s mentioned that World War II was a test to get rid off &quot;Semite gene&quot; from the planet, right? And one of the most destroyed population that time was Eastern Europe countries like Poland, Ukraine, Belarus locations and also Hitler final plans were to destroy Russsia (but failed), right?</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />I actually had the same thought. Russian causalties were 27 million, and there were also more than 2 million causalties in Belarus. It is almost a quarter of the region&#039;s population. Belarus was almost totally destroyed during the war.<br /><br />There is also the following remark. Don&#039;t know yet how to connect it yet, need to look into it more.<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"\" data-quote=\"\" data-source=\"\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">A: Russians of Belarus are closer to the original Ukrainians. And they were originally Kantekkians and had recently destroyed their own planet.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>","attachments":[],"reactions":[