=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Q: (Approaching Infinity) Jeremy Corbell and George Knapp recently released a video from Iraq taken on a base in late 2017 of a strange jellyfish UFO that was visible only on thermal camera. It resembles many other videos people have taken over the years. The video itself has been confirmed as legitimate by a soldier who was stationed at the base who said they referred to it as the spaghetti monster. What was this object?<br /><br />A: 4D energy being that feeds on human suffering.<br /><br />Q: (Approaching Infinity) And what was this other jellyfish object seen on February 16th, 2020 in Sao Paulo at 8:45 AM?<br /><br />A: Similar except more physical. Probe.<br /><br />Q: (Andromeda) There were several that were kind of jellyfish-like. What&#039;s up with the jellyfish form?<br /><br />A: Conduits of energy. Representative of the essence of the object as perceived by humans.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>I saw something similar on Tenerife a few years ago, though it seemed more like an octopus or squid than a jellyfish:<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 1789\" data-quote=\"axj\" data-source=\"post: 989145\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=989145\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-989145\">axj said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">1) Saw something like this flying in the night sky in early 2019:<br /><br /><script class=\"js-extraPhrases\" type=\"application/json\">{\"lightbox_close\": \"Close\",\"lightbox_next\": \"Next\",\"lightbox_previous\": \"Previous\",\"lightbox_error\": \"The requested content cannot be loaded. Please try again later.\",\"lightbox_start_slideshow\": \"Start slideshow\",\"lightbox_stop_slideshow\": \"Stop slideshow\",\"lightbox_full_screen\": \"Full screen\",\"lightbox_thumbnails\": \"Thumbnails\",\"lightbox_download\": \"Download\",\"lightbox_share\": \"Share\",\"lightbox_zoom\": \"Zoom\",\"lightbox_new_window\": \"New window\",\"lightbox_toggle_sidebar\": \"Toggle sidebar\"}</script><div class=\"bbImageWrapper  js-lbImage\" title=\"[IMG]\"data-src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=http%3A%2F%2F4.bp.blogspot.com%2F-0K4KhvLk7pk%2FTepgC3Zu1nI%2FAAAAAAAABrI%2Fb6rbpx-pJBU%2Fs400%2FJellyfish_in_sky-SW.jpg&amp;hash=bb828d31a9bbf5f669d5472495042ed4\" data-lb-sidebar-href=\"\" data-lb-caption-extra-html=\"\" data-single-image=\"1\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=http%3A%2F%2F4.bp.blogspot.com%2F-0K4KhvLk7pk%2FTepgC3Zu1nI%2FAAAAAAAABrI%2Fb6rbpx-pJBU%2Fs400%2FJellyfish_in_sky-SW.jpg&amp;hash=bb828d31a9bbf5f669d5472495042ed4\"data-url=\"http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-0K4KhvLk7pk/TepgC3Zu1nI/AAAAAAAABrI/b6rbpx-pJBU/s400/Jellyfish_in_sky-SW.jpg\"class=\"bbImage\"data-zoom-target=\"1\"style=\"\"alt=\"[IMG]\"title=\"[IMG]\"width=\"\" height=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" /></div><br /><br />It looked like a flying squid with pulsating lines of lights along its legs. There was also a noticeable smell of sulphur or rotten eggs - which supposedly happens when something materializes here from another realm.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />The strange thing was that it did not even cross my mind to take a picture while looking at it slowly flying through the night sky. <br />Tenerife is a huge and mostly dormant volcano, by the way.<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">A: Yes. Volcanic regions generate portals.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":17462,"user":"Steph_rivers","date":"2024-02-12T05:46:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17406,"user":"Pat","date":"2024-01-26T23:48:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-25T18:10:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":8800,"user":"SMM","date":"2024-01-23T19:36:49+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11459,"user":"ToxicCoward","date":"2024-01-22T23:04:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5556,"user":"freigeist2.0","date":"2024-01-21T20:10:22+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6869,"user":"artofdream","date":"2024-01-21T08:48:41+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7597,"user":"hiker","date":"2024-01-21T05:28:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-01-20T21:06:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-20T20:07:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2567,"user":"miguel angel","date":"2024-01-20T10:36:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7776,"user":"Carl","date":"2024-01-20T09:58:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11608,"user":"nidO","date":"2024-01-20T03:40:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-20T02:25:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6987,"user":"Two-tents","date":"2024-01-20T00:28:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-19T23:47:17+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-19T22:17:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13086,"user":"mrtn","date":"2024-01-19T20:54:35+0100","