"N1mTzo","id":1155736,"date":"2024-01-16T19:47:07+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 14181\" data-quote=\"Wandering Star\" data-source=\"post: 1155587\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155587\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155587\">Wandering Star said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Plasma (state of matter)<br /><br />In physics and chemistry, the fourth state of aggregation of matter is called plasma (from the Latin plasma and the Greek πλάσμα &#039;formation&#039;), a fluid state similar to the gaseous state but in which a certain proportion of its particles are electrically charged (ionized). ) and do not have electromagnetic balance, which is why they are good electrical conductors and their particles respond strongly to long-range electromagnetic interactions.[1] In a certain way and synthetically, plasma can be characterized as an ionized gas.<br /><br /><br />I have thought about this, as something similar that could be in the blood of these people who shine.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>This is called biophotons/cold plasma in living organisms. Even official science began to recognize the existence of this phenomenon not so long ago (and previously objectionable scientists were simply ignored - for years).<br />This is actually hard for the average person to understand and visualize. Fortunately, there is a guy on YouTube (<b>Versadoco</b> channel, it is in both English and Russian) who makes excellent videos on physics (for ordinary people):<br /><br /><b>The 4th STATE of LIFE: Inner Light. BIOPHOTONS</b><br /><div class=\"bbMediaWrapper\" data-media-site-id=\"youtube\" data-media-key=\"ZeXB_jbC1OA\"><div class=\"bbMediaWrapper-inner\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/ZeXB_jbC1OA?wmode=opaque\"width=\"560\" height=\"315\"frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe></div></div><br />I also recommend watching the full version of the film about plasma (all 5 parts - <b>Bioplasma and bioelectricity</b>) - <div class=\"bbMediaWrapper\" data-media-site-id=\"youtube\" data-media-key=\"K3UHfO4Ie-8\"><div class=\"bbMediaWrapper-inner\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/K3UHfO4Ie-8?wmode=opaque\"width=\"560\" height=\"315\"frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe></div></div><br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Q: (Ryan) What relationship, if any, did they have with the Celtic peoples of the British/Irish isles who constructed the megaliths?<br /><br />A: Ancestors were the same.<br /><br />Q: (L) So the ancestors of the Russians and the Celtic peoples were the same?<br /><br />A: Yes</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>This is wonderful, I assumed that there was some kind of relationship between us. <a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/members/17427/\" class=\"username\" data-xf-init=\"member-tooltip\" data-user-id=\"17427\" data-username=\"@MJF\">@MJF</a> , do you eat lard? I could send you some.<img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/grin.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":-D\" title=\"Grin    :-D\" data-shortname=\":-D\" /><br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">(Joe) Well, what I was gonna ask is, what are the odds of a major conflict in the Middle East involving Iran, etc. happening this year? What are the chances?<br /><br />A: Good.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Probably, a big war in the East has already begun. After the US and its satellites began bombing Yemen. Yesterday Iran launched a missile attack on Syria (Idlib ~1000 km from Iran), and today Iran launched a missile attack on Pakistan.<br /><br /><br />PS It was an amazing session, many thanks to Laura and the guys (and girls).","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-25T18:12:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":29,"user":"dantem","date":"2024-01-24T00:16:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":8800,"user":"SMM","date":"2024-01-23T19:37:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6869,"user":"artofdream","date":"2024-01-21T08:50:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-01-20T21:08:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-20T20:09:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2567,"user":"miguel angel","date":"2024-01-20T10:38:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7776,"user":"Carl","date":"2024-01-20T10:01:06+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-20T02:37:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-19T22:21:19+0100","reaction"