bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155926\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155926\">Tyomodachi said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">As someone who also came here from Dreamland, I agree. As a minimum you can make the same table as for English transcripts on the forum<br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"191352\" data-url=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/cassiopaean-session-transcripts-by-date.13581/#post-101368\" data-host=\"cassiopaea.org\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/img/FB_sky.jpg\" alt=\"cassiopaea.org\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/cassiopaean-session-transcripts-by-date.13581/#post-101368\"class=\"link link--internal fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"\"rel=\"\"data-proxy-href=\"\">📚 Cassiopaean Session Transcripts by date</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">2030  2029  2028  2027  2026  2025  2024  2023  2022  2021               13 Jan 14 Jan  26 Feb  30 Jan               9 Mar 25 Feb 23 Apr  13 Mar               13 Apr 8 Apr 24 Jun  29 May               27 Apr 13 May 17 Jul  17 Jul               18 May 24 Jun 27 Aug 18 Sept               6 Jul 29...</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/styles/cass/img/favicon.png\" alt=\"cassiopaea.org\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>cassiopaea.org</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />This is a good idea and I agree with you that it would be very helpful  <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/smiley.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":-)\" title=\"Smile    :-)\" data-shortname=\":-)\" /> <img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"👍\" title=\"Thumbs up    :thumbsup:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f44d.png\" data-shortname=\":thumbsup:\" /> <br /><br />Please note, though, that it is a time and energy consuming project, because contrary to what was posted on Dreamland, there is a great emphasis on the quality of translation, so it&#039;s not possible to just translate all the transcripts using Google or Deepl, and then make the table in order to cover &quot;the minimum&quot;. A lot of it is already translated, but it still requires planning and time to integrate it. <br /><br />But it is definitely something worth considering. We would also appreciate help, since the number of people who can do translations is very limited. <img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"🙏\" title=\"Folded hands    :pray:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f64f.png\" data-shortname=\":pray:\" /> If any of you would like to assist and contribute, please let us know. We would greatly appreciate it. <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/flowers.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":flowers:\" title=\"Flowers    :flowers:\" data-shortname=\":flowers:\" /><br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 15488\" data-quote=\"N1mTzo\" data-source=\"post: 1155757\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155757\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155757\">N1mTzo said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">This would greatly help with the research that each of us is (hopefully) doing and sharing with others.<br />This is a wish, of course. Such work would take time (it doesn’t exist!<img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"🙂\" title=\"Slightly smiling face    :slight_smile:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f642.png\" data-shortname=\":slight_smile:\" />).</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />Good and thorough research is exactly one of the main reasons why people should read Laura&#039;s books and not only raw transcripts.<img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"👍\" title=\"Thumbs up    :thumbsup:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f44d.png\" data-shortname=\":thumbsup:\" /> And that&#039;s why the books were and are still in the process of being translated.<br /><br />The thing is that we had a lot of examples of people coming to the forum with an interest only in the transcripts. The same people afterward share their own ideas, conclusions and theories, and then it turns out that either this was already mentioned and covered in the Wave, or in the books Laura explained her thinking process. and the meaning of what was written in the transcripts becomes more clear and nullifies their theories. <br /><br />Bottom line, it&#039;s highly recommended to read the Waves and High Strangeness at least once. If you haven&#039;t done it, then you are missing a lot of valuable content and context. <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/wink.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\";-)\" title=\"Wink    ;-)\" data-shortname=\";-)\" /> What&#039;s more, the Wave books already contain the text of most of the early sessions, so if anyone wants to read them again or go over them, it&#039;s possible to find all of it already published on the ru.cassiopaea.org site.<br /><br />And we will have to look into the project of making the table <img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"😊\" title=\"Smiling face with smiling eyes    :blush:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f60a.png\" data-shortname=\":blush:\" />","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":17410,"user":"Arlind","date":"2024-04-03T04:38:53+0200","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18142,"user":"तत्परिवर्तनं भव","date":"2024-02-06T15:10:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-27T04:09:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11608,"user":"nidO","date":"2024-01-21T20:18:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2567,"user":"miguel angel","date":"2024-01-21T16:51:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-01-21T06:19:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-21T02:25:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-01-21T00:04:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17281,"user":"Aylen","date":"2024-01-20T23:49:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-20T20:42:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-20T19:48:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7776,"user":"Carl","date":"2024-01-20T10:59:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-19T23:55:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3693,"user":"JEEP","date":"2024-01-19T20:51:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5809,"user":"Breo","date":"2024-01-18T21:06:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13103,"user":"Evan","date":"2024-01-18T18:31:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":274,"user":"Niall","date":"2024-01-18T13:10:17+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-18T13:08:11+0100