e":"2024-01-18T22:14:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-18T13:08:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-18T11:39:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7840,"user":"Stoneboss","date":"2024-01-18T06:30:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":882,"user":"latulipenoire","date":"2024-01-18T02:38:41+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17335,"user":"forest_light","date":"2024-01-18T00:52:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-17T22:26:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12879,"user":"Harmony99","date":"2024-01-17T20:20:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-17T19:40:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-17T19:09:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-17T18:41:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-17T17:33:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13630,"user":"Stella Marys","date":"2024-01-17T16:26:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-01-17T15:31:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-17T15:05:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":114,"user":"genero81","date":"2024-01-17T14:24:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":47,"user":"Ryan","date":"2024-01-17T14:10:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5546,"user":"Thebull","date":"2024-01-17T13:11:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-01-17T12:51:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4845,"user":"naorma","date":"2024-01-17T12:48:05+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":7776,"user":"Carl","id":1155932,"date":"2024-01-17T12:27:04+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 16918\" data-quote=\"XPan\" data-source=\"post: 1155643\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155643\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155643\">XPan said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Last August 2023 - things culminated suddenly into the worst episode of all: waking up one morning - without i could hear anything in both of my ears, and knowing i had to work driving subway trains in the evening... it freaked me out quite a bit. (it worked-ish in the evening, as the tough goo left a tiny-tiny opening, just barely enough so i could at least hear a little bit - in order drive the trains and hear orders in the radio).<br /><br /><b>Story behind / culprit:</b><br />Something guided me gradually to where the origin of all this ear mess was: <b><span style=\"color: rgb(184, 49, 47)\">It was in my washing machine</span></b><span style=\"color: rgb(184, 49, 47)\">.</span> I had during the past 2 years noticed that our clothes - even after coming out &quot;fresh&quot;, had a peculiar smell of fungus, which not even the softener could mask - and it just got worse and worse. But where was the source ?! I just couldn&#039;t figure it out. I did look into the washing machine, but didn&#039;t find anything...</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Thanks for sharing this! I&#039;ve noticed a similar suspicious smell coming from wet clothes fresh out the washer. Do you mean it was in or under the rubber seal that surrounds the door opening? Or actually deeper than that? Sorry I can&#039;t quite understand the exact location that you found the mould. Did it require using a screwdriver and taking apart pieces of the machine?","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-27T04:12:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-21T22:43: