tion":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-17T14:27:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-17T14:17:28+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":47,"user":"Ryan","date":"2024-01-17T14:10:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2556,"user":"clerck de bonk","date":"2024-01-17T13:38:41+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":8877,"user":"Persej","date":"2024-01-17T13:24:39+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":11459,"user":"ToxicCoward","id":1155940,"date":"2024-01-17T13:16:45+0100","text":"I&#039;ve seen &quot;black something&quot; around rubber in someone washing machine. I guess owner of that washing machine only used &quot;green programs&quot; 30 or 40 C...<br /><br />Since i would like to avoid such fate - from time to time i use 90° C program to wash things that are near end of life or towels or underwear.<br /><br />If i will replace my washing machine then i guess i won&#039;t have to bother cause manufacturers &quot;solved&quot; issue with fungus by making washing machines not last long enough for those to appear...<br />Nowadays most of washing machines come with bearings welded in, which makes them kinda unprofitable to fix cause instead of replacing bearings you have to replace majority of whole washing machine which could cost as much or even more than next washing machine.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-27T04:12:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-21T22:45:16+0100","reaction":"Sad"},{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-01-21T06:20:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-21T02:30:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-01-21T00:06:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-20T19:52:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-19T23:56:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3693,"user":"JEEP","date":"2024-01-19T20:55:46+0100","reaction":"Sad"},{"user_id":4667,"user":"Tristan","date":"2024-01-18T22:13:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-18T13:10:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-18T11:39:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7850,"user":"Ðekel","date":"2024-01-18T05:09:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":882,"user":"latulipenoire","date":"2024-01-18T02:39:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5546,"user":"Thebull","date":"2024-01-17T20:14:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-17T19:42:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-17T19:12:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-17T18:42:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-17T17:33:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13630,"user":"Stella Marys","date":"2024-01-17T16:28:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6269,"user":"loreta","date":"2024-01-17T16:25:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18714,"user":"Freya Stewart","date":"2024-01-17T16:12:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-01-17T15:32:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-17T15:06:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-17T14:18:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15878,"user":"heinrich","date":"2024-01-17T14:09:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2556,"user":"clerck de bonk","date":"2024-01-17T13:39:54+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":14181,"user":"Wandering Star","id":1155946,"date":"2024-01-17T13:57:29+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 87\" data-quote=\"Keit\" data-source=\"post: 1155929\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155929\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155929\">Keit said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">This is a good idea and I agree with you that it would be very helpful  <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/smiley.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":-)\" title=\"Smile    :-)\" data-shortname=\":-)\" /> <img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"👍\" title=\"Thumbs up    :thumbsup:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f44d.png\" data-shortname=\":thumbsup:\" /><br /><br />Please note, though, that it is a time and energy consuming project, because contrary to what was posted on Dreamland, there is a great emphasis on the quality of translation, so it&#039;s not possible to just translate all the transcripts using Google or Deepl, and then make the table in order to cover &quot;the minimum&quot;. A lot of it is already translated, but it still requires planning and time to integrate it.<br /><br />But it is definitely something worth considering. We would also appreciate help, since the number of people who can do translations is very limited. <img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"🙏\" title=\"Folded hands    :pray:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f64f.png\" data-shortname=\":pray:\" /> If any of you would like to assist and contribute, please let us know. We would greatly appreciate it. <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/flowers.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":flowers:\" title=\"Flowers    :flowers:\" data-shortname=\":flowers:\" /><br /><br /><br /><br />Good and thorough research is exactly one of the main reasons why people should read Laura&#039;s books and not only raw transcripts.<img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"👍\" title=\"Thumbs up    :thumbsup:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f44d.png\" data-shortname=\":thumbsup:\" /> And that&#039;s why the books were and are still in the process of being translated.<br /><br />The thing is that we had a lot of examples of people coming to the forum with an interest only in the transcripts. The same people afterward share their own ideas, conclusions and theories, and then it turns out that either this was already mentioned and covered in the Wave, or in the books Laura explained her thinking process. and the meaning of what was written in the transcripts becomes more clear and nullifies their theories.<br /><br />Bottom line, it&#039;s highly recommended to read the Waves and High Strangeness at least once. If you haven&#039;t done it, then you are missing a lot of valuable content and context. <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/wink.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\";-)\" title=\"Wink    ;-)\" data-shortname=\";-)\" /> What&#039;s more, the Wave books already contain the text of most of the early sessions, so if anyone wants to read them again or go over them, it&#039;s possible to find all of it already published on the ru.cassiopaea.org site.<br /><br />And we will have to look into the project of making the table <img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"😊\" title=\"Smiling face with smiling eyes    :blush:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f60a.png\" data-shortname=\":blush:\" /></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Welcome page in English.<br /><br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"25304\" data-url=\"https://cassiopaea.org/\" data-host=\"cassiopaea.org\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\