k-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Be careful what you wish for? On one hand, think a new different narrative would be more believable and suck more people in. On the other hand, This is like Neanderthal football strategy for the controllers. “Hey that play worked so well, let’s just run it again and again until the other side figures out how to defend it.” AND they get to play out the forced injection plan to really weed out the dissidents and cull the heard at the same time. It actually makes strategic sense after all.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":17410,"user":"Arlind","date":"2024-04-03T04:44:26+0200","reaction":"Sad"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-28T07:10:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15831,"user":"Sheeba","date":"2024-01-26T17:11:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-01-22T00:49:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-21T23:20:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2567,"user":"miguel angel","date":"2024-01-21T17:13:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13630,"user":"Stella Marys","date":"2024-01-21T14:01:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-01-21T06:35:42+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-21T05:34:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7776,"user":"Carl","date":"2024-01-20T11:12:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10482,"user":"Hindsight Man","date":"2024-01-20T09:53:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-20T00:01:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-01-19T04:21:28+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15332,"user":"Matty F","date":"2024-01-18T21:29:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-18T18:46:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-18T12:11:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12854,"user":"Tuulikki","date":"2024-01-18T09:42:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-18T09:01:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":882,"user":"latulipenoire","date":"2024-01-18T02:43:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":679,"user":"Mark7","date":"2024-01-18T02:33:17+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17335,"user":"forest_light","date":"2024-01-18T01:32:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-17T23:31:47+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-17T22:47:49+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12829,"user":"ryu","date":"2024-01-17T20:30:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-01-17T20:00:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-17T19:57:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-17T19:36:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2556,"user":"clerck de bonk","date":"2024-01-17T19:35:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-17T19:23:34+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","id":1156044,"date":"2024-01-17T19:20:35+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 16918\" data-quote=\"XPan\" data-source=\"post: 1156003\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156003\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156003\">XPan said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \"><b>No, <span style=\"color: rgb(184, 49, 47)\">no need to screw apart</span> anything. </b><br /><br />Uhm ... wait. I am not a washing machine expert, how these things can look like in various or even old models (or where else mold potentially could accumulate over time)<br /><br />But let&#039;s assume it is similar for most machines - the mold was embedded <b>inside</b> the multiple folded <b>rubber gasket seal</b>. The ones you face, when opening the door to a front loading machine. Just dig in there and inspect it all around. In my case - it must have accumulated for 10 years or so. And me, naive as i was, never even considered that such quantities could build up in there... <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/umm.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":umm:\" title=\"Um...    :umm:\" data-shortname=\":umm:\" /><br /><br />Ignorance engagers - so, now i got lesson i needed; about mold and machines <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/smoking.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":cool2:\" title=\"Smoking    :cool2:\" data-shortname=\":cool2:\" /><br /><br />(I am not sure what we did in the past - that this could happen to accumulate. Perhaps it came from a time when we used powder based soap a long time ago. Perhaps at one time something went wrong, didn&#039;t get flushed out properly - and from there the goo started to rot,  accumulate silently... I don&#039;t know. But whatever goes inside the gasket i our machine, doesn&#039;t easily escape / doesn&#039;t get washed out).<br /><br />Since August last year - i haven&#039;t had any accumulations of anything in there. Every month I inspect the inside of that rubber gasket seal. All clean. No mold what so ever.<br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12px\">Edit:</span><br />The article <a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/members/10309/\" class=\"username\" data-xf-init=\"member-tooltip\" data-user-id=\"10309\" data-username=\"@Jenn\">@Jenn</a> refered to, shows a similar rubber gasket like we have. Thank you Jenn <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/tongue.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":-P\" title=\"Tongue    :-P\" data-shortname=\":-P\" />, great that you pointed out about the place where you put in the detergent, as well can be a source for mold accumulation. And leaving the front door open, is wise as well (in a family without children). <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/thumbup.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":thup:\" title=\"Thumbs up    :thup:\" data-shortname=\":thup:\" /></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Like XPan I am not an expert on washing machines, but regularly when I wash white clothes, I put one or two laundry bleach tablets to do the washing and this prevents me from having mold and its smell in the washing machine and my white laundry is whiter... <img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"😉\" title=\"Winking face    :wink:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f609.png\" data-shortname=\":wink:\" />","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-28T07:10:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-01-22T00:49:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-21T23:21:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2567,"user":"miguel angel","date":"2024-01-21T17:13:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13630,"user":"Stella Marys","date":"2024-01-21T14:02:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-01-21T06:36:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-21T05:35:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-20T00:01:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-19T13:58:55+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-18T18:47:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-18T12:11:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12854,"user":"Tuulikki","date":"2024-01-18T09:42:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"