+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19148,"user":"Happy Poo","date":"2024-01-18T11:44:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-18T11:31:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-18T10:19:06+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-18T09:40:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-18T05:36:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":882,"user":"latulipenoire","date":"2024-01-18T02:46:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17335,"user":"forest_light","date":"2024-01-18T01:54:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18714,"user":"Freya Stewart","date":"2024-01-18T01:38:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":47,"user":"Ryan","date":"2024-01-18T00:50:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-01-18T00:42:42+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7948,"user":"irjO","date":"2024-01-18T00:38:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11382,"user":"Odin","date":"2024-01-18T00:35:02+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":6460,"user":"Puma","id":1156108,"date":"2024-01-18T00:41:52+0100","text":"<b><span style=\"font-size: 22px\">Imaginal realm and Ideaspace </span></b><br /><br />I take up your comment to add some ideas<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 16918\" data-quote=\"XPan\" data-source=\"post: 1156027\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156027\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156027\">XPan said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Reality changed, portals opened and <b>showed awful scenes from the Vietnam war, soldiers fighting</b> - but fighting <b>against horrible monsters. Creatures who slashed everything they came in contact with.</b><br /><br />Kind of strange when you think about it... the parallels and details; in this case an old Comic story vs reports from people like Cliff High..</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />I think the story you mention was published in Uncanny X-Men #187- 188 (1984, possibly published in Sweden in the 90s). In that story the hyperdimensional beings are called &quot;Dire Wraiths&quot;, &quot;deathwings&quot; and &quot;shadowbeings&quot;<br /><a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/attachments/rco008_1469328489-jpg.90005/\"target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/data/attachments/73/73168-cc76c11d5e63248373ddb488c23d0f2c.jpg\"class=\"bbImage \"style=\"\"alt=\"RCO008_1469328489.jpg\"title=\"RCO008_1469328489.jpg\"width=\"130\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" /></a><br />The Dire Wraiths (red beings) use to stick a kind of tongue in the forehead of their victims to extract their energy and memories.<br /><br /><a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/attachments/rco021_1469328489-jpg.90006/\"target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/data/attachments/73/73169-0e84571bb52e225af9f588cc2d341b4b.jpg\"class=\"bbImage \"style=\"\"alt=\"RCO021_1469328489.jpg\"title=\"RCO021_1469328489.jpg\"width=\"215\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" /></a><br /><br />Shadowbeings have no physical substance, but appear as black objects.<br /><a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/attachments/rco003_1469335387-jpg.90007/\"target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/data/attachments/73/73170-e195cf5354c22ca744b9bd84da85a070.jpg\"class=\"bbImage \"style=\"\"alt=\"RCO003_1469335387.jpg\"title=\"RCO003_1469335387.jpg\"width=\"138\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" /></a><br /><br /><div style=\"text-align: justify\">All this fauna is but a part of the Marvel Universe &quot;window fallers&quot;.<br /><br />I think, Marvel Universe is itself part of the <b>imaginal realm </b>(And all other imaginary universes) a product of the mind of comic writers and screenwriters.<br />&#8203;</div><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Q: (Ryan) Are the thought plane described in session 18 March 1995, the imaginal realm, and informational field equivalent?<br /><br />A: No</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Q: (Ryan) What is the relationship of the astral plane to any of these?<br /><br /><br />A: <b>All are in a sense different dimensions</b>.<br /><br />Q: (L) Well, are the thought plane and the imaginal realm equivalent?<br /><br />A: Close.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br /><div style=\"text-align: justify\">Within the comic industry there is a term coined by the writer Alan Moore: &quot;<b>Idea-Space</b>&quot; (Since there is no time in a comic book but ideas and space)  According to comic book writer <a href=\"https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rick_Veitch#:~:text=Richard%20Veitch%20(%2Fvi%CB%90t%CA%83,1992%20San%20Diego%20Comic%20Con\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Rick Veitch</a>:&#8203;</div><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"\" data-quote=\"\" data-source=\"\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">&quot;Alan had actually worked out a terminology. He saw ideas being made of stuff called &#039;ideoplasm&#039;. <b>And he had a name for the dimension it inhabited, Ideaspace. </b>He came to it because he was teaching himself the disciplines of magic: kabbalah and European traditions of consciousness, referred to as magic. It was just a way of exploring these levels beyond time and space.&quot;</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br /><div style=\"text-align: justify\">So the Cs tell us that the relationship between the &quot;astral plane&quot;, the &quot;imaginal realm&quot; and the &quot;thought plane&quot; is that they are dimensions, yet the plane of thought and the imaginal plane are very close. Whereas Alan Moore thinks that <b>ideas inhabit a dimension</b> he calls ideaspace from which energy can be drawn to create &quot;ideoplasms.&quot;<br />&#8203;</div><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Q: (L) But are they different from the information field itself?<br /><br />A: Yes</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br /><div style=\"text-align: justify\">Rick Veitch also mentions about Ideaspace:<br />&#8203;</div><blockquote data-attributes=\"\" data-quote=\"\" data-source=\"\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \"><div style=\"text-align: justify\">The central theme is <b>that ideas are alive</b>. I chose the Superman archetype to address that theme and illustrate it. To me superheroes are an industrial age version of the gods. So I&#039;m using them to explore the concept that <b>ideas are living entities, and that there is a dimension for where these ideas exist outside of time and space, from which they impact human flesh and minds.</b>&#8203;</div></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br /><div style=\"text-align: justify\">Incidentally, Alan Moore&#039;s graphic novel V for Vendetta has impacted the lives of many readers around the world.<br /><br /><a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/attachments/23vm4rpmufhtbjk2bhxkyzidvy-jpg.90010/\"target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/data/attachments/73/73173-ac8e9ba5b478f606b6cff44df9c827d5.jpg\"class=\"bbImage \"style=\"\"alt=\"23VM4RPMUFHTBJK2BHXKYZIDVY.jpg\"title=\"23VM4RPMUFHTBJK2BHXKYZIDVY.jpg\"width=\"128\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" /></a><br /><br />From all this we can say that while the &quot;information field&quot; is composed of knowledge suitable or understandable for a given density, the &quot;imaginal plane&quot; and the &quot;thought plane&quot; are composed of <b>ideas and imagination that are an individual&#039;s own</b>, <b>but that can be shared through a visual or written medium.</b> I think the latter belong to what Alan Moore calls Ideaspace.<br /><br />&#8203;</div>","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":17410,"user":"Arlind","date":"2024-04-03T04:57:24+0200","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-04-01T21:24:56+0200","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2567,"user":"miguel angel","date":"2024-02-02T16:43:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-28T07:15:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7597,"user":"hiker","date":"2024-01-24T18:28:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-23T19:22:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17281,"user":"Aylen","date":"2024-01-22T22:53:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17361,"user":"seve","date":"2024-01-21T15:48:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-20T00:03:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5809,"user":"Breo","date":"2024-01-19T20:11:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-19T17:30:16+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-19T16:54:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-01-19T05:19:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":679,"user":"Mark7","date":"2024-01-18T23:04:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-01-18T21:53:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-18T19:08:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-18T16:26:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11382,"user":"Odin","date":"2024-01-18T13:02:51+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-18T12:26:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19148,"user":"Happy Poo","date":"2024-01-18T11:47:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-18T11:32:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15102,"user":"Kari Baba","date":"2024-01-18T11:02:45+0100","reaction":"Like