3>Aspergillus is very common in air ducts and can cause a variety of health problems, including respiratory infections, allergic reactions, and asthma attacks. It can also produce mycotoxins, which are toxic substances that can damage the lungs and other organs.<br /><br /><h3><b>Chaetomium</b>&#8203;</h3>Chaetomium is a type of mold that can grow in air ducts as well as on other surfaces in your home, such as walls, floors, and ceilings. It is most commonly found in damp or humid environments, and it can produce mycotoxins, which are toxic substances that can cause a variety of health problems.<br /><br />Chaetomium mold is typically brown or black, and it has a cottony or velvety texture. It can sometimes be mistaken for other types of mold, such as black mold, so it is important to have a professional mold inspector identify the mold if you are unsure.<br /><br /><h3><b>Fusarium</b>&#8203;</h3>Fusarium is a common type of mold that can grow in air ducts. It can cause respiratory problems, allergic reactions, and other health problems in people who are exposed to it.<br /><br /><h3><b>Mucor</b>&#8203;</h3>Mucor is one of the most dangerous types of mold in air ducts. It’s extremely toxic and can cause serious health problems, including respiratory infections, neurological problems, and even death.<br /><br />Mucor is most likely to grow in air ducts that are damp and dark. It can also grow on organic materials, such as dust, pollen, and pet dander.<br /><br />If you think you might have mucor in your air ducts, it’s important to have them professionally cleaned by a certified mold remediation company. Do not try to clean them yourself, as this could spread the mold and make the problem worse.<br /><br /><h3><b>Stachybotrys</b>&#8203;</h3>Stachybotrys, also known as black mold, is the most toxic type of mold that can grow in air ducts. Many get confused– what does black mold look like on air vents? It is black or greenish-black in color and has a slimy texture.<br /><br />Stachybotrys require high humidity levels to grow, so it is often found in areas that have been water-damaged.<br /><br />Exposure to Stachybotrys can cause a variety of health problems, including respiratory infections, allergic reactions, and even neurological issues. In severe cases, it can even be fatal.<br /><br /><h3><b>Trichoderma</b>&#8203;</h3>Trichoderma is a fast-growing mold, but not as toxic as some other types of mold, but it can still cause health problems, such as respiratory infections and allergic reactions.<br /><br /><h3><b>Ulocladium</b>&#8203;</h3>Ulocladium is a rare but dangerous type of mold that can grow in air ducts. It is often difficult to detect, as it can grow on hidden surfaces and in dark corners. Ulocladium exposure can cause a variety of health problems, including respiratory infections, allergic reactions, and skin irritation.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":9854,"user":"oli 518","date":"2024-02-07T15:45:37+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":2567,"user":"miguel angel","date":"2024-02-02T18:15:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-29T02:35:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11608,"user":"nidO","date":"2024-01-27T05:10:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-25T11:16:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-01-24T21:04:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-23T19:26:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":1739,"user":"anartist","date":"2024-01-23T00:28:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-22T20:52:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-01-22T18:36:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15332,"user":"Matty F","date":"2024-01-21T08:56:53+0100","reaction