"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fcorehtml%2Fpmc%2Fpmcgifs%2Fpmc-card-share.jpg%3F_%3D0&amp;hash=7cac684a7abf4850b4f89c3e7b3e57b9&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4141785/\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Standing at the Gateway to Europe - The Genetic Structure of Western Balkan Populations Based on Autosomal and Haploid Markers</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">Contemporary inhabitants of the Balkan Peninsula belong to several ethnic groups of diverse cultural background. In this study, three ethnic groups from Bosnia and Herzegovina - Bosniacs, Bosnian Croats and Bosnian Serbs - as well as the populations of ...</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fcoreutils%2Fnwds%2Fimg%2Ffavicons%2Ffavicon.png&amp;hash=eb8ac7f39d9da0327bd85a4f035f16b8&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov</div></div></div></div><br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"191458\" data-url=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4558026/\" data-host=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fcorehtml%2Fpmc%2Fpmcgifs%2Fpmc-card-share.jpg%3F_%3D0&amp;hash=7cac684a7abf4850b4f89c3e7b3e57b9&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4558026/\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Genetic Heritage of the Balto-Slavic Speaking Populations: A Synthesis of Autosomal, Mitochondrial and Y-Chromosomal Data</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">The Slavic branch of the Balto-Slavic sub-family of Indo-European languages underwent rapid divergence as a result of the spatial expansion of its speakers from Central-East Europe, in early medieval times. This expansion–mainly to East Europe ...</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fcoreutils%2Fnwds%2Fimg%2Ffavicons%2Ffavicon.png&amp;hash=eb8ac7f39d9da0327bd85a4f035f16b8&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov</div></div></div></div><br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"191459\" data-url=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3646727/\" data-host=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fcorehtml%2Fpmc%2Fpmcgifs%2Fpmc-card-share.jpg%3F_%3D0&amp;hash=7cac684a7abf4850b4f89c3e7b3e57b9&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC3646727/\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">The Geography of Recent Genetic Ancestry across Europe</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">A genomic survey of recent genealogical relatedness reveals the close ties of kinship and the impact of events across the past 3,000 years of European history.The recent genealogical history of human populations is a complex mosaic formed by individual ...</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fcoreutils%2Fnwds%2Fimg%2Ffavicons%2Ffavicon.png&amp;hash=eb8ac7f39d9da0327bd85a4f035f16b8&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov</div></div></div></div><br /><div><a href=\"https://www.cell.com/cell/fulltext/S0092-8674(23)01135-2\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">https://www.cell.com/cell/fulltext/S0092-8674(23)01135-2</a></div> (&quot;X&quot;)<br /><br />we know now that it cannot be only Russia and that the most Slavic people are Belarusians (on whom C&#039;s also gave some comments). This is the Slavic genetic ancestry in Eastern and Central Europe:<br /><br />Belarusians 75-100% (those with less % are due to similar Baltic ancestry)<br /><br />Ukrainians 80-100% (Western in addition have Germanic and Balkan ancestry)<br /><br />Russians c. 90% (with growing Asian influence)<br /><br />Poles 70-80% (tend to have in addition 10% Germanic ancestry)<br /><br />Slovaks 65-70% (in addition some 20% Germanic ancestry)<br /><br />Czechs 60-65% (in addition some 20-25% Germanic ancestry)<br /><br />Slovenians c. 60% (in addition some 15% Celtic-Germanic ancestry)<br /><br />Hungarians c. 60% (in addition some 15% Celtic-Germanic ancestry)<br /><br />Croats 65-70% (&quot;X&quot; 66.5% +/- 2.7%; other % is some 5% Germanic and 30% local Iron Age-Roman)<br /><br />Bosnians/Bosniaks 55-70% (other % is the same)<br /><br />Serbs 55-60% (&quot;X&quot; 58.4% +/- 2.1%; other % is the same minus Germanic)<br /><br />Romanians 50-60% (&quot;X&quot; 55.4% +/- 2.4%; other % is the same)<br /><br />Bulgarians 45-55% (&quot;X&quot; 51.2% +/- 2.2%; other % is the same)<br /><br />Montenegrins 45-55% (other % is the same)<br /><br />East Germans and Prussians 25-65%<br /><br />Albanians 31.0% (that&#039;s &quot;X&quot; +/- 5.3%; most ancestry is local Iron Age-Roman-Anatolian)<br /><br />Greeks 17.9-40.2% (that&#039;s &quot;X&quot; +/- 2.0%; most ancestry is local Iron Age-Roman-Anatolian)<br /><br />Russians and Belarusians are obviously &quot;anti-globalist&quot; pact, Ukrainians are a sad geopolitical casualty (basically fallen and will have hard time to recuperate whatever the outcome of the West-vs-East conflict), Poles-Czechs-Hungarians-Romanians are showing some signs of resistance to the EU-centrism and globalism, ex Yugoslavian states are always a battleground between broader globalistic and local tribalistic interests (with the Croats more under the &quot;anti&quot; influence, but the population still showing significant critical mass). Others can be considered more or less neutral.<br /><br />To be noted, the Slavic nations and those countries with substantial Slavic ancestry are most traditional, conservative, religious (Christian with Old-New Slavic traditions gaining popularity), private-household/estate and so on part of Europeans. All of them are a thorn in the eye for the globalists and Western European elites. The on-going Ukrainian-Russian war, 90s dissolution of the Eastern Bloc, bloody war in Yugoslavia, recent academic attempts to deconstruct the Slavic identity and heritage denying mass migration of the Slavs in the early medieval age (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Florin_Curta#Theories_and_criticism;\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Florin Curta - Wikipedia</a> and non-academic &quot;autochthonic romantics&quot; in Serbia) and so on, are all anti-Slavic and anti-Pan Slavic in the core. Mutual disputes and bad relations among the Slavs, and the tyranny by the Soviet Russians, only contributed to the Slavic nations being exploited by the Western elites.<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 16791\" data-quote=\"Benjamin\" data-source=\"post: 1156114\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156114\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156114\">Benjamin said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">If there is a major &#039;true Semite&#039; population living in Russia (Iraq and Iran) who had the same ancestors as the megalith builders of the Celtic people, and (one of) the aim of 4D STS is to eliminate these &#039;true Semites&#039;, do these &#039;true Semites&#039; have the (potential? latent?) ability to &#039;shine&#039;? Perhaps one of these bioweapons is designed to eliminate this ability? And/or make sure no one else can aquire the DNA for it?</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Slavic, Celtic and Germanic peoples all have the same ancestors or related relatives in the distant past - Eastern Hunter Gatherers (EHG) and Yamnaya/Bell Beakers people - as all of them represented Indo-Europeans. There exist significant difference between Slavic and Celtic peoples, as Celts are more related to Italic and Germanic peoples (Centum) than Slavic peoples (Satem), however centuries before the current era must have happened some crucial Celtic (and later Germanic) influence on the Proto-Slavs which diverged the Proto-Slavs from the Balts.<br /><br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"191460\" data-url=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-023-06705-1\" data-host=\"www.nature.com\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.springernature.com%2Fm685%2Fspringer-static%2Fimage%2Fart%253A10.1038%252Fs41586-023-06705-1%2FMediaObjects%2F41586_2023_6705_Fig1_HTML.png&amp;hash=6b21691b73a14fb95296601b01f92141&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.nature.com\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-023-06705-1\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">The selection landscape and genetic legacy of ancient Eurasians - Nature</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">Analyses of imputed ancient genomes and of samples from the UK Biobank indicate that ancient selection and migration were large contributors to the distribution of phenotypic diversity in present-day Europeans.</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Fstatic%2Fimages%2Ffavicons%2Fnature%2Ffavicon-48x48-b52890008c.png&amp;hash=8bc75c492f20938fce1802f47f1d146b&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.nature.com\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>www.nature.com</div></div></div></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"191461\" data-url=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-023-06865-0\" data-host=\"www.nature.com\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.springernature.com%2Fm685%2Fspringer-static%2Fimage%2Fart%253A10.1038%252Fs41586-023-06865-0%2FMediaObjects%2F41586_2023_6865_Fig1_HTML.png&amp;hash=a6b434f9e862f073320e9b521a6f991f&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.nature.com\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://www.nature.com/articles/s41586-023-06865-0\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Population genomics of post-glacial western Eurasia - Nature</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">An analysis involving the shotgun sequencing of more than 300 ancient genomes from Eurasia reveals a deep east–west genetic divide from the Black Sea to the Baltic, and provides insight into the distinct effects of the Neolithic transition on either side of this boundary.</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Fstatic%2Fimages%2Ffavicons%2Fnature%2Ffavicon-48x48-b52890008c.png&amp;hash=8bc75c492f20938fce1802f47f1d146b&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.nature.com\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>www.nature.com</div></div></div></div><br />There&#039;s some issue with the connection of relating the Megalithic builders with the Indo-Europeans as thery were not genetically related. The builders were pre-Indo European population of Europe, mostly of Neolithic farmer-like genetics and Western Hunter Gatherer (WHG) paternal lineage, which later got invaded and replaced by the Indo-Europeans (autosomally and paternal lineage). The megalithic phenomenon was much more widespread than it seems and not something specific for Western Europe.<br /><br />I think C&#039;s connection between Slavs and Celts shouldn&#039;t be understood genetically but as an cultural-soul collective type of predisposition which is different to Germanic and other peoples. It is a more like an oral, folk, tribalistic type of culture and not a written/materialistic, elite, nationalistic/imperialistic type of cultural-soul. Probably related to C&#039;s distant division to different &quot;sons of ...&quot;.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":2567,"user":"miguel angel","date":"2024-02-03T13:06:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-29T02:40:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15831,"user":"Sheeba","date":"2024-01-26T17:35:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-01-24T21:10:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17281,"user":"Aylen","date":"2024-01-23T23:17:57+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19399,"user":"Faca Fritz","date":"2024-01-23T11:14:42+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-22T21:28:29+0100","reaction":"Love"},{"user_id":15102,"user":"Kari Baba","date":"2024-01-22T11:26:17+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7840,"user":"Stoneboss","date":"2024-01-21T07:02:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-20T20:15:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-20T18:21:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7776,"user":"Carl","date":"2024-01-20T15:39:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15669,"user":"Henchman 21","date":"2024-01-20T03:26:52+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17335,"user":"forest_light","date":"2024-01-19T23:47:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-01-19T21:59:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-19T18:01:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-19T13:06:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-19T05:35:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11403,"user