on":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-18T17:02:16+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-18T16:18:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4518,"user":"Adobe","date":"2024-01-18T15:21:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19544,"user":"meadow_wind","date":"2024-01-18T14:56:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-01-18T14:46:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19148,"user":"Happy Poo","date":"2024-01-18T14:42:41+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-18T14:31:33+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":19544,"user":"meadow_wind","id":1156287,"date":"2024-01-18T14:56:16+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 8877\" data-quote=\"Persej\" data-source=\"post: 1156281\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156281\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156281\">Persej said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Yes, Mike Adams <a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/coronavirus-pandemic-apocalypse-now-or-exaggerated-scare-story.48214/post-861698\" class=\"link link--internal\">actively promoted</a> the Covid hysteria.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Yes, that, he did a lot. <br />Plus lots of political hysteria, political bias, and colorful language (running a news business). <br />But I don&#039;t remember him going in line with &quot;trust the gov. science&quot;.<br />That aside, there is some good data to be dug if one knows how to look.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":1739,"user":"anartist","date":"2024-02-10T03:42:47+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-20T00:08:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9535,"user":"hlat","date":"2024-01-19T07:17:28+0100","reaction":"Dislike"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-19T05:52:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":679,"user":"Mark7","date":"2024-01-19T00:25:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-01-18T22:12:57+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6164,"user":"Jefferson","date":"2024-01-18T18:03:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-18T16:18:41+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4518,"user":"Adobe","date":"2024-01-18T15:21:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-18T15:00:32+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":8558,"user":"Temperance","id":1156294,"date":"2024-01-18T15:40:24+0100","text":"Thank you so much for this session! Quite a lot to take in. <br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">A: As yet unknown organic structure throughout the body carrying a different fluid other than blood or lymph that is related to light. Your ancestors glowed and transmitted light and power.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>I know they&#039;re saying it&#039;s as yet unknown, but there are some systems that have been looked at that sound like they could fit the bill. Possibly they mean not made mainstream yet? Or widely known?<br />For example, there&#039;s the<a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S2005290113002082\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"> Primo Vascular system</a>:<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"\" data-quote=\"\" data-source=\"\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Traditional <a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/oriental-medicine\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Eastern medicine</a> has had a successful existence for a long time and has provided functional paths for curing disease. However, some scientists do not accept <a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/auriculotherapy\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">acupuncture</a>, primarily because the <a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/meridian-system\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">meridian system</a> lacks a physical anatomical basis. To date, scientific theories have not been able to explain the functional paths used by traditional Eastern medicine to cure disease. According to Western medicine, no known anatomical foundation exists for the meridians and unknown nervous, circulatory, endocrine, and immune mechanisms mediate the effects of acupuncture. In the early 1960s, only one hypothesis was proposed to explain the anatomical basis of the meridians. By using different experimental approaches during the past 10 years, the number of scientific papers that report the discovery of different anatomical and physiological evidence confirming the existence of an anatomical basis for the meridian system has increased. Morphological science is greatly challenged to offer a new biomedical theory that explains the possible existence of new bodily systems such as the primo <a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/vascular-system\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">vascular system</a> (PVS). The PVS is a previously unknown system that integrates the features of the cardiovascular, nervous, immune, and hormonal systems. It also provides a physical substrate for the <a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/acupuncture-point\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">acupuncture points</a> and meridians. Announcements of the morphological architectonics and the function of the PVS fundamentally changed the basic understanding of biology and medicine because the PVS is involved in the development and the functions of living organisms. <b>We propose a new vision of the anatomical basis for the PVS and the vital energy—called “<i>Qi</i>”—as an electromagnetic wave that is involved very closely with the DNA in the PVS. DNA provides genetic information and it functions as a store of information that can be obtained from the <a href=\"https://www.sciencedirect.com/topics/medicine-and-dentistry/electromagnetic-field\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">electromagnetic fields</a> of the environment. The PVS is the communication system between living organisms and the environment, and it lies at the lowest level of life. T</b>he theory of the PVS could be a good basis for forming a new point of view of Darwin&#039;s evolutionary theory. Discoveries in morphological theory—such as discoveries with respect to the PVS—have not been made since the 18th century. For that reason, the PVS needs more attention.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>I suppose the EM aspect of this could have to do with the &quot;light and power&quot; they mentioned. <br /><br />There&#039;s also others I remember reading about, but that one sounded like the best hit. <br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Temperance) Does spring dew have special properties as described in alchemical lore?<br /><br />A: Not as you are thinking. It is a metaphor.<br /><br />Q: (L) So it&#039;s not really spring dew, it&#039;s...<br /><br />(Joe) Mountain Dew.<br /><br />(L) So the subsequent questions are irrelevant.<br /><br />(Joe) Most things in alchemy are metaphors.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>The way I was thinking was along the lines of the sun charging the water with life-giving properties which cause the growth in spring, as I had understood the lore. <br /><br />I&#039;m wondering if &quot;not as I am thinking&quot; refers to the water collected still having some properties but more imparted by the collector, a la Masaru Emoto. Or if they&#039;re referring to the dew itself as being a metaphor altogether and I need to look deeper. Could it be referring to the fluid mentioned before, to be collected and stored for healing use?","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":16215,"user":"xahyr","date":"2024-04-25T16:37:24+0200","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":1739,"user":"anartist","date":"2024-02-10T03:45:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2567,"user":"miguel angel","date":"2024-02-03T17:51:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-29T02:44:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T00:05:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17281,"user":"Aylen","date":"2024-01-23T23:22:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11120,"user":"Mr.Cyan","date":"2024-01-23T07:46:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-22T21:41:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2451,"user":"Aiming","date":"2024-01-22T08:41:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7840,"user":"Stoneboss","date":"2024-01-21T14:49:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-20T20:17:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":1789,"user":"axj","date":"2024-01-20T19:56:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-01-20T19:54:47+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-20T18:49:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-20T00:08:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17335,"user":"forest_light","date":"2024-01-19T23:50:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15344,"user":"Cassis","date":"2024-01-19T19:38:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-19T18:40:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17269,"user":"Lyndi Lama","date":"2024-01-19T17:36:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17354,"user":"Liliea","date":"2024-01-19T16:35:06+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-19T13:16:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-19T09:23:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-19T06:04:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-01-19T05:40:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":47,"user":"Ryan","date":"2024-01-19T05:03:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11403,"user":"Sylvia","date":"2024-01-19T03:58:57+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4601,"user":"987baz","date":"2024-01-19T02:44:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4180,"user":"