":"Happy Poo","date":"2024-01-18T21:33:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-18T19:24:10+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":8987,"user":"lilies","id":1156332,"date":"2024-01-18T18:59:20+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 8877\" data-quote=\"Persej\" data-source=\"post: 1156310\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156310\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156310\">Persej said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">On the link you posted, they mention the role of collagen in biophoton emissions:</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Collagen is important!!<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 8877\" data-quote=\"Persej\" data-source=\"post: 1156310\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156310\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156310\">Persej said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">I wrote about my father&#039;s <a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/sciatica-anyone.10763/post-1152724\" class=\"link link--internal\">positive experience</a> with collagen peptides. Perhaps it&#039;s also connected with this biophoton thing?</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Positive confirmation on collagen. Last year I began with <a href=\"https://alfonsmiller.com/products/millers-alpha-gel-1000-g\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">high quality / expensive cattle collagen </a>(super-fine, not coagulating, Western make), but I started smelling strange, like cow-dung. Then I used fish collagen. Then I <a href=\"https://floravita.superwebaruhaz.hu/zselatin-sertes-floragel-100-bloom-250g-nagy-tisztasagu-etkezesi-hidrolizalt-kollagen-t147542\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">started using pig collagen</a>. Because I also eat pig meat exclusively, I think I can&#039;t smell it now. :D :D If you decide, <u>try using the fine powder</u> collagen, as it doesn&#039;t coagulate in soup!<br /><br />Basically chock full of essential amino acids.<br /><br />Now I&#039;m eating hydrolyzed pig collagen, fine, 100 bloom. Three teaspoons stirred into soup. Or finely pressed with a fork into solid food, so it dissolves. <span style=\"color: rgb(184, 49, 47)\"><b>Major downside is this collagen needs 3x more energy to digest than normal food.</b></span> So there were people, who developed diets from this - eating this almost exclusively and died.<br /><br />Upside is these collagen powders give your body the ingredients to repair joint damage to max. (IIRC) 30% self-repair [?], quoted here on this forum years ago.<br /><br />It also appears to give my brain more its specific type of food &amp; energy, so I eat less snacks now and am still able to work in my high-level-creative job, where literally creating best quality product out of nothing is paramount!<br /><br /><b><u>DOWNSIDE of overeating collagen: </u></b><br />I noticed, if I ate too much of this - 3 heaped teaspoons - every day, then I get tired and unable to work and have a &#039;starving-shambling overall exhaustive sensation all day&#039;, indicating my body is using 3 x times more energy from my regular food intake to ingest this high amount of collagen.<br /><br />Therefore I decided I only eat this thing about 4 days per week.<br /><br />Also appears to give robustness of muscle performance when under high stress: Like bicycling upward a slope while also pulling a heavy package  <a href=\"https://www.goride.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/IMG_0513.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">on my bike-carrier.</a> Since I eat pig collagen, my knee, leg joints and muscles endure this physical torture much better: I don&#039;t feel the need to stop near the top of the slope, anymore. Still climbing near the top - slowly with the bike by this point - looks &amp; feels like torture and is exhausting. :D<br /><br />Watch out: <b>Collagen is heat sensitive and is destroyed at 80 degrees Celsius!</b>  So always wait, until your hot soup cools down enough for your tongue to touch it, THEN mix the collagen in and eat. This makes sure that <a href=\"https://cbsupplements.com/cc/collagen-amino-acids-profile/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">all the essential amino acids</a> and the other expensive-to-buy ones are preserved intact, when you eat this collagen.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-04-01T21:34:01+0200","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2567,"user":"miguel angel","date":"2024-02-03T17:55:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-29T02:48:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-25T11:43:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17281,"user":"Aylen","date":"2024-01-23T23:25:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-22T21:49:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-22T21:23:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-01-22T18:45:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16530,"user":"AvibeZ","date":"2024-01-21T23:41:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15332,"user":"Matty F","date":"2024-01-21T09:18:51+0100","reaction":"Like"},