low ugc noopener\"> Primo Vascular system</a>:<br /><br />I suppose the EM aspect of this could have to do with the &quot;light and power&quot; they mentioned.<br /><br />There&#039;s also others I remember reading about, but that one sounded like the best hit.<br /><br /><br />The way I was thinking was along the lines of the sun charging the water with life-giving properties which cause the growth in spring, as I had understood the lore.<br /><br />I&#039;m wondering if &quot;not as I am thinking&quot; refers to the water collected still having some properties but more imparted by the collector, a la Masaru Emoto. Or if they&#039;re referring to the dew itself as being a metaphor altogether and I need to look deeper. Could it be referring to the fluid mentioned before, to be collected and stored for healing use?</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br /><br />This article will explore the concepts of what are known as the ‘Three Treasures’ in Traditional Chinese Medicine and the relationship between them.<br /><br />Jing ,Qi  and Shen<br /><br /><div><a href=\"https://www.britishacupuncturefederation.co.uk/2023/01/03/the-three-treasures-jing-shen-and-qi/\"class=\"link link--external\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">https://www.britishacupuncturefederation.co.uk/2023/01/03/the-three-treasures-jing-shen-and-qi/</a></div>","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T00:10:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-22T21:59:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-21T15:53:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11403,"user":"Sylvia","date":"2024-01-20T04:42:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-20T00:09:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-19T10:48:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-19T09:43:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":47,"user":"Ryan","date":"2024-01-19T05:13:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4601,"user":"987baz","date":"2024-01-19T02:56:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":679,"user":"Mark7","date":"2024-01-19T00:44:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-19T00:30:42+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-01-18T22:24:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4667,"user":"Tristan","date":"2024-01-18T22:15:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19148,"user":"Happy Poo","date":"2024-01-18T21:39:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-18T20:32:56+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":8877,"user":"Persej","id":1156353,"date":"2024-01-18T20:02:36+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 13103\" data-quote=\"Evan\" data-source=\"post: 1156327\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156327\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156327\">Evan said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Are you perhaps referring to <a href=\"https://www.rogelcancercenter.org/support/symptoms-and-side-effects/alternative-medicine/acupressure#:~:text=Acupressure%20is%20an%20ancient%20form,(meridians)%20inside%20the%20body.\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">acupressure</a>?</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Yes, acupressure on the spine with fingertips.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-02-06T13:59:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T00:10:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-22T21:59:53+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-21T15:53:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-20T00:09:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-19T10:49:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-19T00:30:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13103,"user":"Evan","date":"2024-01-18T20:45:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-18T20:33:02+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":14181,"user":"Wandering Star","id":1156366,"date":"2024-01-18T20:30:05+0100","text":"Many, many years ago I was looking for things about nutrition and so on.<br /><br />On the subject of &#039;ingested&#039; collagen, what rings true for me is the following (until I read something somewhere that makes me change my mind):<br /><br />Indeed: NOTHING. It doesn&#039;t matter if you take it in pills, powder or infusion. Many experts say this, among them the researcher, disseminator and professor of the Department of Biotechnology at the Polytechnic University of Valencia, José Miguel Mulet, author, among others, of the book &#039;What is a healthy life&#039; (ed. Destino). &quot;Collagen is a protein made of amino acids. When we ingest it, our body breaks it down into its smallest parts, which are no longer collagen,&quot; he explains to Yo Dona. And of course, those pieces are not going to come back together to form collagen again inside our body. That wouldn&#039;t be nutrition. It would be a miracle.<br /><br />The key idea for us to understand is given to us by the endocrinologist and nutritionist Paloma Gil in her blog: eating a type of tissue (and collagen molecules are) does not produce the generation of that tissue in our body. If that were true, bald people would eat hair and the problem would be solved, says the expert.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-02-06T14:14:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T00:10:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7597,"user":"hiker","date":"2024-01-26T03:24:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-22T22:01:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-01-22T18:59:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-21T15:59:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-21T00:14:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-01-20T19:59:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7776,"user":"Carl","date":"2024-01-20T19:09:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-20T00:09:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17307,"user":"Asa","date":"2024-01-19T14:36:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12854,"user":"Tuulikki","date":"2024-01-19T13:43:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-19T10:49:47+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-19T09:44:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":679,"user":"Mark7","date":"2024-01-19T00:50:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18714,"user":"Freya Stewart","date":"2024-01-19T00:46:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-19T00:31:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11382,"user":"Odin","date":"2024-01-18T23:07:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6460,"user":"Puma","date":"2024-01-18T22:14:57+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11128,"user":"michaelrc","date":"2024-01-18T22:03:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":1533,"user":"Debra","date":"2024-01-18T21:43:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4518,"user":"Adobe","date":"2024-01-18T21:41:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19148,"user":"Happy Poo","date":"2024-01-18T21:40:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":8987,"user":"lilies","date":"2024-01-18T20:40:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-18T20:34:03+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":14181,"user":"Wandering Star","id":1156367,"date":"2024-01-18T20:31:38+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 8987\" data-quote=\"lilies\" data-source=\"post: 1156332\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156332\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156332\">lilies said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Collagen is important!!<br /><br />Positive confirmation on collagen. Last year I began with <a href=\"https://alfonsmiller.com/products/millers-alpha-gel-1000-g\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">high quality / expensive cattle collagen </a>(super-fine, not coagulating, Western make), but I started smelling strange, like cow-dung. Then I used fish collagen. Then I <a href=\"https://floravita.superwebaruhaz.hu/zselatin-sertes-floragel-100-bloom-250g-nagy-tisztasagu-etkezesi-hidrolizalt-kollagen-t147542\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">started using pig collagen</a>. Because I also eat pig meat exclusively, I think I can&#039;t smell it now. :D :D If you decide, <u>try using the fine powder</u> collagen, as it doesn&#039;t coagulate in soup!<br /><br />Basically chock full of essential amino acids.<br /><br />Now I&#039;m eating hydrolyzed pig collagen, fine, 100 bloom. Three teaspoons stirred into soup. Or finely pressed with a fork into solid food, so it dissolves. <span style=\"color: rgb(184, 49, 47)\"><b>Major downside is this collagen needs 3x more energy to digest than normal food.</b></span> So there were people, who developed diets from this - eating this almost exclusively and died.<br /><br />Upside is these collagen powders give your body the ingredients to repair joint damage to max. (IIRC) 30% self-repair [?], quoted here on this forum years ago.<br /><br />It also appears to give my brain more its specific type of food &amp; energy, so I eat less snacks now and am still able to work in my high-level-creative job, where literally creating best quality product out of nothing is paramount!<br /><br /><b><u>DOWNSIDE of overeating collagen: </u></b><br />I noticed, if I ate too much of this - 3 heaped teaspoons - every day, then I get tired and unable to work and have a &#039;starving-shambling overall exhaustive sensation all day&#039;, indicating my body is using 3 x times more energy from my regular food intake to ingest this high amount of collagen.<br /><br />Therefore I decided I only eat this thing about 4 days per week.<br /><br />Also appears to give robustness of muscle performance when under high stress: Like bicycling upward a slope while also pulling a heavy package  <a href=\"https://www.goride.co.nz/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/IMG_0513.jpg\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">on my bike-carrier.</a> Since I eat pig collagen, my knee, leg joints and muscles endure this physical torture much better: I don&#039;t feel the need to stop near the top of the slope, anymore. Still climbing near the top - slowly with the bike by this point - looks &amp; feels like torture and is exhausting. :D<br /><br />Watch out: <b>Collagen is heat sensitive and is destroyed at 80 degrees Celsius!</b>  So always wait, until your hot soup cools down enough for your tongue to touch it, THEN mix the collagen in and eat. This makes sure that <a href=\"https://cbsupplements.com/cc/collagen-amino-acids-profile/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">all the essential amino acids</a> and the other expensive-to-buy ones are preserved intact, when you eat this collagen.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>My before post is related with this, sorry.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-02-06T14:15:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-21T16:00:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-19T10:50:16+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-19T00:32:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-18T20:34:14+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":16150,"user":"Franck-alexandre","id":1156368,"date":"2024-01-18T20:38:53+0100","text":"Thank you for this incredible session. <img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"🙏\" title=\"Folded hands    :pray:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f64f.png\" data-shortname=\":pray:\" />","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-02-06T14:15:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-29T02:51:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T00:11:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-21T16:00:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-20T20:20:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":8976,"user":"marek760","date":"2024-01-20T10:28:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-20T00:09:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-19T20:36:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-19T19:47:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15344,"user":"Cassis","date":"2024-01-19T19:40:46+01