,"date":"2024-01-19T02:02:34+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":25,"user":"Mrs. Peel","id":1156423,"date":"2024-01-19T01:52:42+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 19544\" data-quote=\"meadow_wind\" data-source=\"post: 1156421\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156421\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156421\">meadow_wind said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">? I have always brought the water to a boil, then let it simmer for 5h with my bones, thinking it would help get the marrow out. I</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Heck, I boil my bones on low for 24 hours in a crock pot.  How do you make bone broth without boiling it?  I thought that was the point of it, to get the marrow out of the bones. <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/huh.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":huh:\" title=\"Huh?    :huh:\" data-shortname=\":huh:\" />","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":15831,"user":"Sheeba","date":"2024-01-27T14:55:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T07:40:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7597,"user":"hiker","date":"2024-01-26T03:31:51+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":8253,"user":"aimarok","date":"2024-01-25T13:28:57+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11262,"user":"Matai","date":"2024-01-24T03:02:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-23T19:56:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-22T22:12:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-21T16:36:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"