eBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156325\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156325\">Evan said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">When I saw the name Grazielaia, I thought immediately of course “Thanks” in Italian, and “Grace” obviously. But the word I “felt” was Gratitude, which is sort of both, in a sense. Anyway just my gut feeling, so I figured I’d add it to the conversation.<img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"🙏\" title=\"Folded hands    :pray:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f64f.png\" data-shortname=\":pray:\" /></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>The name also caught my attention as it is basically the same as Graziela, a woman&#039;s name here. Below is the etymology I found. And it makes sense to me that Gratitude is what one should/would feel in the face of Grace.<br /><br /><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Graziella\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"><b>Graziella</b></a> f<br /><ol><li data-xf-list-type=\"ol\">a female <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/given_name\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">given name</a>, a diminutive form of <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Grazia\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Grazia</a> (<a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Grace\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Grace</a>)</li></ol><br /><a href=\"https://www.dicionariodenomesproprios.com.br/graziela/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"><b>Graziela</b></a>: It means &quot;little grace&quot;, &quot;little divine gift&quot;, &quot;little divine benevolence&quot;, &quot;little gift from God&quot;, &quot;cherished gift from God&quot;.<br /><br /><h3><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/grazia\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">grazia </a>&#8203;</h3><b>Etymology 1</b><br />Borrowed from <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Latin\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Latin</a> <i><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/gratia#Latin\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">grātia</a></i> (“favour; goodwill; charm”).<br /><h4>Noun&#8203;</h4><b>grazia</b> f (<i>plural</i> <b><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/grazie#Italian\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">grazie</a></b>)<br /><ol><li data-xf-list-type=\"ol\"><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/grace\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">grace</a></li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ol\">(<a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/law#English\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">law</a>) <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/pardon\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">pardon</a></li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ol\"><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/favour\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">favour</a>/<a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/favor\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">favor</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/kindness\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">kindness</a></li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ol\">(usually in the <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#plural\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">plural</a>) <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/serif\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">serif</a></li></ol><br /><b>Etymology 2</b><br /><h4>Verb&#8203;</h4><b>grazia</b><br /><ol><li data-xf-list-type=\"ol\">inflection of <i><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/graziare#Italian\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">graziare</a></i>:<ol><li data-xf-list-type=\"ol\"><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#third_person\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">third-person</a> <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#singular_number\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">singular</a> <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#present_tense\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">present</a> <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#indicative_mood\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">indicative</a></li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ol\"><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#second_person\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">second-person</a> <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#singular_number\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">singular</a> <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#imperative_mood\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">imperative</a></li></ol></li></ol><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/gratia#Latin\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"><span style=\"font-size: 18px\"><b>gratia</b></span></a><br />From <i><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/gratus#Latin\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">grātus</a></i> (“<a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/pleasing\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">pleasing</a>”). Related to <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sanskrit\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Sanskrit</a> <i><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/%E0%A4%97%E0%A5%82%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%8D%E0%A4%A4%E0%A4%BF#Sanskrit\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">गूर्ति</a></i> (gūrtí, “praise, welcome, benediction”).<br /><br /><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/graziare#Italian\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"><b>graziàre</b></a> (<i>first-person singular present</i> <b><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/grazio#Italian\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">gràzio</a></b>, <i>first-person singular past historic</i> <b><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/graziai#Italian\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">graziài</a></b>, <i>past participle</i> <b><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/graziato#Italian\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">graziàto</a></b>, <i>auxiliary</i> <b><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/avere#Italian\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">avére</a></b>)<br /><ol><li data-xf-list-type=\"ol\">(<a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#transitive\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">transitive</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/law#English\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">law</a>) to <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/pardon\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">pardon</a></li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ol\">(<a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#transitive\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">transitive</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/Appendix:Glossary#figurative\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">figurative</a>) to <a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/spare\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">spare</a></li></ol>","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-29T02:53:06+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11608,"user":"nidO","date":"2024-01-28T22:11:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T07:40:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-23T19:56:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-22T22:12:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12829,"user":"ryu","date":"2024-01-22T21:35:57+0100","reaction":"Love"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-21T16:40:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3761,"user":"Yas","date":"2024-01-21T15:46:41+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15332,"user":"Matty F","date":"2024-01-21T13:39:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3693,"user":"JEEP","date":"2024-01-21T02:14:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15669,"user":"Henchman 21","date":"2024-01-20T14:56:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11403,"user":"Sylvia","date":"2024-01-20T04:53:24+0100","reaction":"Love"},{"user_id":17335,"user":"forest_light","date":"2024-01-20T00:13:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-20T00:10:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-19T20:48:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-19T19:53:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17269,"user":"Lyndi Lama","date":"2024-01-19T17:22:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17354,"user":"Liliea","date":"2024-01-19T16:24:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13103,"user":"Evan","date":"2024-01-19T16:11:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10630,"user":"JeanneT","date":"2024-01-19T16:04:55+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":8558,"user":"Temperance","date":"2024-01-19T15:07:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2556,"user":"clerck de bonk","date":"2024-01-19T14:54:16+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16215,"user":"xahyr","date":"2024-01-19T13:54:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12854,"user":"Tuulikki","date":"2024-01-19T13:51:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-19T13:00:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12341,"user":"Laurentien2","date":"2024-01-19T11:39:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-19T11:35:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3628,"user":"mantle","date":"2024-01-19T11:31:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-19T10:53:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19148,"user":"Happy Poo","date":"2024-01-19T10:43:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7765,"user":"Goemon_","date":"2024-01-19T10:22:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-19T09:52:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-19T08:43:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5384,"user":"Maya","date":"2024-01-19T06:50:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-01-19T06:23:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10595,"user":"Korzik18","date":"2024-01-19T05:47:53+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":882,"user":"latulipenoire","date":"2024-01-19T03:39:30+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":27,"user":"Beau","id":1156427,"date":"2024-01-19T02:14:43+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 14284\" data-quote=\"iamthatis\" data-source=\"post: 1156419\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156419\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156419\">iamthatis said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Yeah, it&#039;s recommended to make sure you don&#039;t boil your bone broth, as it denatures collagen. Making bone broth is a fine art!</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Back when i made broth more consistently, I would usually always boil my bones first for 20 or 30 minutes. The &quot;blanching&quot; method would help eliminate the sometimes funky odors that bone broths would have. Then I would roast them in the oven and simmer in pot or slow cooker overnight. That first batch would be so full of collagen it would solidify at room temperature.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T07:40:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7597,"user":"hiker","date":"2024-01-26T03:32:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-25T12:00:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-23T19:56:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11120,"user":"Mr.Cyan","date":"2024-01-23T07:48:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-22T22:13:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-01-22T19:08:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-21T16:41:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3761,"user":"Yas","date":"2024-01-21T15:47:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7840,"user":"Stoneboss","date":"2024-01-21T15:04:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15332,"us