er":"Happy Poo","date":"2024-01-19T16:18:33+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":10829,"user":"Jtucker","date":"2024-01-19T15:57:55+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6460,"user":"Puma","date":"2024-01-19T15:35:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18714,"user":"Freya Stewart","date":"2024-01-19T15:13:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11007,"user":"Bluegazer","date":"2024-01-19T14:32:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-19T14:01:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13515,"user":"KJS","date":"2024-01-19T13:55:07+0100","reaction":"Wow"}]},{"user_id":15488,"user":"N1mTzo","id":1156528,"date":"2024-01-19T13:52:09+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 14284\" data-quote=\"iamthatis\" data-source=\"post: 1156438\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156438\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156438\">iamthatis said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \"><b>The goal is gelatinous stock, stock that sets up as a solid gel if you put it in the fridge, so solid that you can turn the container over and the gel will stay in place.</b></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>This dish is called HOLODETS and it is an integral part of Russian cuisine (Ukrainian, Belarusian, etc.). It is mainly prepared in WINTER (for the New Year). You need to take the bones (and meat) of animals: pork legs (required), beef meat with bone, turkey leg (or other meat, according to your taste and choice) - put it all in a huge saucepan (I have 12 liters) and cook for low heat for about 6 hours. At the end you need to add a bay leaf (as an antiseptic) and some pepper (peas) to this fatty broth (and an onion bulb - optional). Then the meat must be separated from the bones, finely chopped and placed in plates. You need to take a lot of garlic, crush it into small pieces and also put it in the plates (where the meat is). Then you pour the hot, fatty broth into the same plates where the meat and garlic are. The balance of broth and meat is approximately 70% broth and 30% meat. Then you put these plates in the refrigerator or outside (where it is cold and frosty). It turns out something like this (photo from the Internet):<br /><script class=\"js-extraPhrases\" type=\"application/json\">{\"lightbox_close\": \"Close\",\"lightbox_next\": \"Next\",\"lightbox_previous\": \"Previous\",\"lightbox_error\": \"The requested content cannot be loaded. Please try again later.\",\"lightbox_start_slideshow\": \"Start slideshow\",\"lightbox_stop_slideshow\": \"Stop slideshow\",\"lightbox_full_screen\": \"Full screen\",\"lightbox_thumbnails\": \"Thumbnails\",\"lightbox_download\": \"Download\",\"lightbox_share\": \"Share\",\"lightbox_zoom\": \"Zoom\",\"lightbox_new_window\": \"New window\",\"lightbox_toggle_sidebar\": \"Toggle sidebar\"}</script><div class=\"bbImageWrapper  js-lbImage\" title=\"big_379272.jpg\"data-src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fimg1.russianfood.com%2Fdycontent%2Fimages_upl%2F380%2Fbig_379272.jpg&amp;hash=4d8dd3363da16b1b53828897d6357679\" data-lb-sidebar-href=\"\" data-lb-caption-extra-html=\"\" data-single-image=\"1\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fimg1.russianfood.com%2Fdycontent%2Fimages_upl%2F380%2Fbig_379272.jpg&amp;hash=4d8dd3363da16b1b53828897d6357679\"data-url=\"https://img1.russianfood.com/dycontent/images_upl/380/big_379272.jpg\"class=\"bbImage\"data-zoom-target=\"1\"style=\"\"alt=\"big_379272.jpg\"title=\"\"width=\"\" height=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" /></div><br /><div class=\"bbImageWrapper  js-lbImage\" title=\"4de18be415b34bf7860828a65c5950db.jpg\"data-src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fs1.eda.ru%2FStaticContent%2FPhotos%2F4