te":"2024-01-19T17:46:31+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 274\" data-quote=\"Niall\" data-source=\"post: 1156559\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156559\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156559\">Niall said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Promoting Covid hysteria in the first half of 2020 - <b>when it mattered</b> - IS tantamount to telling his followers to &quot;trust the govt. science,&quot; just like the MSM.<br /><br />Adams even got irate with them at one point - SIX WEEKS into the first lockdown, with mass demonstrations well underway at many state capitols - and told them they were <i>in denial</i>:<br /><br /><a href=\"https://www.naturalnews.com/2020-04-30-denial-the-five-stages-of-coronavirus-grief-mental-resistance.html\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Why are so many people still stuck in DENIAL? The “five stages of coronavirus grief” explains the mental resistance against our new reality - by Mike Adams, Natural News, 30 April 2020</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>All I remember was that at first, he wasn&#039;t sure about the kill rate nor the transmission mode, so it may look like he hyped the whole thing (better safe than sorry). But by July 2020, he had figured out the deception/Fraud, and he made a 180 turn regarding the whole thing.<br /><br />I didn&#039;t know SOTT at the time, and if it weren&#039;t for his site, I would not have learned how to protect myself with alternative/natural substances nor how much the injections were harmful.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":19399,"user":"Faca Fritz","date":"2024-02-12T10:16:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T07:57:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T22:44:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6460,"user":"Puma","date":"2024-01-22T13:51:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:22:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T02:42:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14181,"user":"Wandering Star","date":"2024-01-20T02:02:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2556,"user":"clerck de bonk","date":"2024-01-19T22:57:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4518,"user":"Adobe","date":"2024-01-19T21:56:49+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17583,"user":"ziutek","date":"2024-01-19T21:26:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-19T21:02:41+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-19T18:23:29+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":15488,"user":"N1mTzo","id":1156587,"date":"2024-01-19T17:54:55+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 4717\" data-quote=\"Jones\" data-source=\"post: 1156543\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156543\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156543\">Jones said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Now, Deb Dana would say that if it comes down to a battle between the autonomic nervous system (both vagals and sympathetic) and the brain, that the autonomic nervous system would win every time.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>This is interesting. Perhaps I didn’t quite understand, but what you describe is very similar to some autoimmune diseases (arthritis, psoriatic arthritis, ankylosing arthritis, etc.)<br />Many autoimmune diseases begin when a person experiences prolonged stress or shock (the death of a loved one, loss of a job, etc.) and this is the trigger for the onset of the disease.<br />Having studied autoimmune diseases for a long time, I came to the conclusion that these are largely diseases of the brain (and not joints or other organs - all this is a consequence and not a cause). Your brain is at war (sending signals to your body 24/7) with your immune system (including through your nervous system). Because of this, the immune (and nervous too) system is constantly in a hyperactive state and it begins to attack joints, skin, internal organs, eyes - seeing “enemies” everywhere (and destroying the entire body).<br />For example, with ankylosing arthritis (and psoriatic arthritis), the entire spine becomes ossified - this is very similar to when the body builds a kind of stone fortress, trying to literally fence itself off from the brain.<br />By the way, the most effective drugs for autoimmune diseases today are the so-called JAK inhibitors; they block the transmission of signals (nerve impulses) inside the cell. They are also used in the treatment of severe forms of Covid to relieve the “cytokine storm”.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-29T03:02:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-25T13:01:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T22:45:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6460,"user":"Puma","date":"2024-01-22T13:53:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:22:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T02:43:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15332,"user":"Matty F","date":"2024-01-21T17:48:16+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett"