":11007,"user":"Bluegazer","date":"2024-01-21T08:35:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":882,"user":"latulipenoire","date":"2024-01-21T01:40:38+0100","reaction":"Love"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-20T23:44:00+0100","reaction":"Love"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-20T20:35:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4180,"user":"Lilou","date":"2024-01-20T20:17:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":91,"user":"1984","date":"2024-01-20T20:10:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14800,"user":"Sergey","date":"2024-01-20T18:07:52+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":76,"user":"Lucius","date":"2024-01-20T17:42:40+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":4717,"user":"Jones","id":1156698,"date":"2024-01-20T00:46:06+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 15488\" data-quote=\"N1mTzo\" data-source=\"post: 1156587\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156587\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156587\">N1mTzo said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">This is interesting. Perhaps I didn’t quite understand, but what you describe is very similar to some autoimmune diseases (arthritis, psoriatic arthritis, ankylosing arthritis, etc.)<br />Many autoimmune diseases begin when a person experiences prolonged stress or shock (the death of a loved one, loss of a job, etc.) and this is the trigger for the onset of the disease.<br />Having studied autoimmune diseases for a long time, I came to the conclusion that these are largely diseases of the brain (and not joints or other organs - all this is a consequence and not a cause). Your brain is at war (sending signals to your body 24/7) with your immune system (including through your nervous system). Because of this, the immune (and nervous too) system is constantly in a hyperactive state and it begins to attack joints, skin, internal organs, eyes - seeing “enemies” everywhere (and destroying the entire body).<br />For example, with ankylosing arthritis (and psoriatic arthritis), the entire spine becomes ossified - this is very similar to when the body builds a kind of stone fortress, trying to literally fence itself off from the brain.<br />By the way, the most effective drugs for autoimmune diseases today are the so-called JAK inhibitors; they block the transmission of signals (nerve impulses) inside the cell. They are also used in the treatment of severe forms of Covid to relieve the “cytokine storm”.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />That&#039;s pretty much it from what I understand of PVT so far. The nervous system responds to a threat and promotes a sympathetic or dorsal vagal response and gets retuned - because apparently it is always learning. Then there are new triggers to those survival states, but the brain makes up stories to explain new triggers while the physiology has withdrawn resources from some bodily operations to focus on others to prepare the body to deal with threat. One of the functions that resources are withdrawn from are higher cognitive functions, so the stories that the brain makes up to try to explain the survival state are inaccurate. So a cycle with a negative feedback loop begins where the story reinforces the state and the state reinforces the story. There has been some work done with vagal stimulation in autoimmune diseases and inflammation that you might be interested in (see <a href=\"https://www.mdpi.com/2073-4409/11/24/4103\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a> and <a href=\"https://bioelecmed.biomedcentral.com/articles/10.1186/s42234-021-00069-5\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"noopener\">here</a> for example). Porges would say that a ventral vagal state is the best for good health outcomes because the body is in optimal homeostatic balance then and is distributing resources to all bodily systems accordingly.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":7512,"user":"Gwenllian","date":"2024-05-24T11:12:18+0200","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-02-08T21:34:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T08:03:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-25T13:14:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T22:55:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6460,"user":"Puma","date":"2024-01-22T14:05:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:34:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12994,"user":"isparnid","date":"2024-01-22T10:31:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T03:08:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15488,"user":"N1mTzo","date":"2024-01-21T20:50:10+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":17354,"user":"Liliea","date":"2024-01-21T19:07:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15332,"user":"Matty F","date":"2024-01-21T18:35:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":679,"user":"Mark7","date":"2024-01-21T15:58:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3761,"user":"Yas","date":"2024-01-21T15:44:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-21T11:13:17+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-20T20:38:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-01-20T20:07:41+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-20T16:55:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-20T07:36:17+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4619,"user":"jhonny","date":"2024-01-20T06:31:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":47,"user":"Ryan","date":"2024-01-20T04:36:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13103,"user":"Evan","date":"2024-01-20T03:11:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14181,"user":"Wandering Star","date":"2024-01-20T02:07:53+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4601,"user":"987baz","date":"2024-01-20T01:56:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-01-20T00:56:42+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":8877,"user":"Persej","id":1156699,"date":"2024-01-20T00:47:57+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 68\" data-quote=\"Gaby\" data-source=\"post: 1156687\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156687\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156687\">Gaby said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">It is speculated that ivermectin works very well because it increases interferons, your innate immune system defense against viruses and cancer.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />Interesting. It seems that Russians have another product that increases interferons:<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"\" data-quote=\"\" data-source=\"\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Amiksin<br /><br />Pharmacodynamics.<br /><br />Low molecular weight synthetic interferon inducer that stimulates the formation of all types of interferons in the body (alpha, beta, gamma and lambda). The main producers of interferon in response to the administration of tilorone are intestinal epithelial cells, hepatocytes, T-lymphocytes, neutrophils and granulocytes. After oral administration, the maximum production of interferon is determined in the sequence intestine - liver - blood after 4-24 hours. Amiksin® has an immunomodulatory and antiviral effect.<br /><br />According to experimental studies, after a single oral administration of the drug Amiksin® in a dose equivalent to the maximum daily dose for humans, the maximum concentration in the lung tissue of interferon lambda is determined after 24 hours, interferon alpha - after 48 hours. Induction of interferon lambda in lung tissue helps to increase antiviral protection of the respiratory tract during influenza and other respiratory viral infections.<br /><br />Induces the synthesis of interferon in human leukocytes. Stimulates bone marrow stem cells, depending on the dose, enhances antibody formation, reduces the degree of immunosuppression, restores the ratio of T-suppressors and T-helpers. Effective against various viral infections, including influenza viruses, other acute respiratory viral infections, hepatitis viruses and herpes viruses. The mechanism of antiviral action is associated with inhibition of the translation of virus-specific proteins in infected cells, as a result of which viral reproduction is suppressed.<br /><br />Pharmacokinetics.<br /><br />After oral administration, it is quickly absorbed from the gastrointestinal tract. Bioavailability - 60%. About 80% of the drug binds to plasma proteins. The drug is excreted almost unchanged through the intestines (70%) and through the kidneys (9%). The half-life (T1/2) is 48 hours. The drug does not undergo biotransformation and does not accumulate in the body.<br /><br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"192769\" data-url=\"https://amixin.ru/instrukcija-po-primeneniju/\" data-host=\"amixin.ru\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://amixin.ru/instrukcija-po-primeneniju/\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Амиксин инструкция по применению</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">Амиксин®  - современный противовирусный препарат, индуктор образования интерферонов. Усиливает выработку антител при ОРВИ. Максимум активности уже в первые 24 часа.</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Famixin.ru%2Ffavicon.ico&amp;hash=faf8db948d857a67331a6ab57296bb03&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"amixin.ru\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>amixin.ru</div></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />It was discovered a long time ago: <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tilorone\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Tilorone - Wikipedia</a><br /><br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"192770\" data-url=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC444270/\" data-host=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fcorehtml%2Fpmc%2Fpmcgifs%2Fpmc-card-share.jpg%3F_%3D0&amp;hash=7cac684a7abf4850b4f89c3e7b3e57b9&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC444270/\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Tilorone Hydrochloride: an Oral Interferon-Inducing Agent</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">Tilorone hydrochloride characteristically induces an unusually delayed and prolonged interferon response not commonly associated with other synthetic inducers. Maximum circulating interferon levels of 8,000 to 10,000 units/ml were detected 12 hr postinoculation ...</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fcoreutils%2Fnwds%2Fimg%2Ffavicons%2Ffavicon.png&amp;hash=eb8ac7f39d9da0327bd85a4f035f16b8&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov</div></div></div></div><br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"192771\" data-url=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5786809/\" data-host=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fcorehtml%2Fpmc%2Fpmcgifs%2Fpmc-card-share.jpg%3F_%3D0&amp;hash=7cac684a7abf4850b4f89c3e7b3e57b9&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5786809/\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Efficacy of Tilorone Dihydrochloride against Ebola Virus Infection</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">Tilorone dihydrochloride (tilorone) is a small-molecule, orally bioavailable drug that is used clinically as an antiviral outside the United States. A machine-learning model trained on anti-Ebola virus (EBOV) screening data previously identified tilorone ...</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fcoreutils%2Fnwds%2Fimg%2Ffavicons%2Ffavicon.png&amp;hash=eb8ac7f39d9da0327bd85a4f035f16b8&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov</div></div></div></div><br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"192772\" data-url=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7100484/\" data-host=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fcorehtml%2Fpmc%2Fpmcgifs%2Fpmc-card-share.jpg%3F_%3D0&amp;hash=7cac684a7abf4850b4f89c3e7b3e57b9&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC7100484/\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Tilorone: a Broad-Spectrum Antiviral Invented in the USA and Commercialized in Russia and beyond</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">For the last 50 years we have known of a broad-spectrum agent tilorone dihydrochloride (Tilorone). This is a small-molecule orally bioavailable drug that was originally discovered in the USA and is currently used clinically as an antiviral in ...</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fcoreutils%2Fnwds%2Fimg%2Ffavicons%2Ffavicon.png&amp;hash=eb8ac7f39d9da0327bd85a4f035f16b8&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov</div></div></div></div>","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":7512,"user":"Gwenllian","date":"2024-05-24T10:34:24+0200","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-02-08T21:35:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-30T18:45:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T08:05:09+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-25T13:16:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T22:56:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10595,"user":"Korzik18","date":"2024-01-23T18:22:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:34:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12994,"user":"isparnid","date":"2024-01-22T10:31:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T03:15:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17354,"user":"Liliea","date":"2024-01-21T19:07:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15332,"user":"Matty F","date":"2024-01-21T18:39:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-21T17:22:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":679,"user":"Mark7","date":"2024-01-21T15:58:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3761,"user":"Yas","date":"2024-01-21T15:44:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-21T11:13:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-20T23:49:16+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-01-20T20:08:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-20T17:02:28+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-01-20T16:28:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":27,"user":"Beau","date":"2024-01-20T15:54:51+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-20T11:52:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":68,"user":"Gaby","date":"2024-01-20T11:09:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13979,"user":"Kmicic","date":"2024-01-20T11:07:51+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4667,"user":"Tristan","date":"2024-01-20T09:39:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5384,"user":"Maya","date":"2024-01-20T09:39:02+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":2556,"user":"clerck de bonk","date":"2024-01-20T09:36:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-20T07:36:22+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4601,"user":"987baz","date":"2024-01-20T05:35:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":47,"user":"Ryan","date":"2024-01-20T04:38:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14181,"user":"Wandering Star","date":"2024-01-20T02:08:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14324,"user":"Candice","date":"2024-01-20T02:03:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-20T02:01:23+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":8398,"user":"jebediah","id":1156706,"date":"2024-01-20T01:41:52+0100","text":"Thank for sharing. Amazing data.<br /><br />A: As far as we can see, they have already been introduced, just the people are not paying attention.<br /><br />I post something years ago in the forum... but, of course, I&#039;n not sure if would be the point.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":18191,"user":"Uperios","date":"2024-02-08T21:35:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-30T18:46:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12829,"user":"ryu","date":"2024-01-22T21:32:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:34:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17354,"user":"Liliea","date":"2024-01-21T19:08:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-01-20T16:28:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-20T11:52:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-20T07:36:24+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":12697,"user":"youlik","id":1156711,"date":"2024-01-20T02:19:45+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12487\" data-quote=\"Akul\" data-source=\"post: 1156214\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156214\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156214\">Akul said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Mutual disputes and bad relations among the Slavs, and the <b>tyranny by the Soviet Russians</b>, only contributed to the Slavic nations being exploited by the Western elites.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>It&#039;s all beautifully and scientifically written, but one phrase turns it all into dust and points to the Western mainstream.<br />I am a Soviet Russian, I was 23 when the Soviet Union collapsed, I had already served in the Soviet Army and such definitions cut my ears. What kind of tyranny are you talking about if we, ordinary residents of Russia, in your interpretation the main tyrants of eastern Europe, envied ordinary residents of Poland, Hungary, Czechoslovakia, GDR, Yugoslavia, a little less Bulgaria and Romania, because in the ordinary everyday sense they all lived better than us? And even then it was clear that this is not because they are all smarter or better at work, but because all this is paid for by our resources. I fully agree that people in the West lived even better and these, in your interpretation of the tyrannized, did not have the opportunity to live the same way, i.e. there was some control. Yes, there was a leaky control, because if it were at least something worthwhile tyranny, then the events of 1956 and 1968 in Budapest and Prague simply could not have happened. Why did this control arise and was exist, or, in other words, how could it not arise, if we recall that all the countries of Eastern Europe, except Poland and Czechoslovakia occupied by the Germans, were allies of Nazi Germany during its attack on the USSR and participated in this attack.<br />I don&#039;t want to portray the USSR as the best human formation that existed, probably not, but seeing what was happening on the &quot;other side&quot;, I can&#039;t put it next to it. If you like to call the influence of the Soviet Union tyranny, your will, but then what do you call what nazi Germany did on the territory of Belarus you mentioned, and can these things be equated at least approximately?<br /><br /><div class=\"bbCodeSpoiler\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"bbCodeSpoiler-button button--longText button\" data-xf-click=\"toggle\" data-xf-init=\"tooltip\" title=\"Click to reveal or hide spoiler\"><span class=\"button-text\"><span>Spoiler: <span class=\"bbCodeSpoiler-button-title\">Russian spelling</span></span></span></button><div class=\"bbCodeSpoiler-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--spoiler\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\">Как все это красиво и наукообразно написано, однако одно словосочетание обращает все это в пыль и указывает на западный мейнстрим.<br /> Я советский русский, мне было 23, когда развалился Советский Союз, я уже успел послужить в Советской Армии и мне режет уши такие определения. О какой тирании вы говорите, если мы, обычные жители России, в вашей интерпретации основные тираны восточной европы, завидовали обычным жителям Польши, Венгрии, Чехословакии, ГДР, Югославии, чуть меньше Болгарии и Румынии, потому что в обычном бытовом смысле все они жили лучше, чем мы? И уже тогда было понятно, что это происходит не потому, что все они умнее или лучше работают, а потому что все это оплачивается нашими ресурсами. Я вполне соглашусь в том, что на западе люди жили еще лучше и у этих, в вашей интерпретации тиранизируемых, не было возможности жить так же, т.е. существовал некоторый контроль. Да, контроль существовал и то дырявый, потому что если бы это было хоть чего то стоящая тирания, то событий 1956 и 1968 в Будапеште и в Праге просто не могло бы произойти. Почему возник и существовал этот контроль или, по другому говоря, как он мог не возникнуть, если вспомнить, что все страны Восточной Европы, кроме оккупированных немцами Польши и Чехословакии, были союзниками фашистской Германии при ее нападении на СССР и участвовали в этом нападении.<br /> Я не хочу изображать СССР, как лучшую человеческую формацию из существовавших, наверное это не так, но видя, что происходило с &quot;другой стороны&quot;, я не могу поставить это рядом. Если вам нравится называть влияние Советского союза тиранией, воля ваша, но как тогда вы назовете то, что сделала фашистская Германия на территории упомянутой вами Белоруссии и можно ли эти вещи приравнять хотя бы приблизительно?</div></div></div></div>","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":19399,"user":"Faca Fritz","date":"2024-02-12T10:57:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-30T18:46:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2381,"user":"kinyash","date":"2024-01-28T08:01:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T08:06:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-25T13:19:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T22:58:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":1789,"user":"axj","date":"2024-01-23T18:41:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10595,"user":"Korzik18","date":"2024-01-23T18:23:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16911,"user":"AndrewMn","date":"2024-01-22T12:34:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:34:30+0100","reaction":"Sad"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T03:22:43+0100","reactio