&#039;s that sound?<br />Everybody look, what&#039;s going down?<br />You better stop<br />Children, what&#039;s that sound?<br />Everybody look, what&#039;s going down?","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":9854,"user":"oli 518","date":"2024-02-09T15:00:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-30T18:53:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12879,"user":"Harmony99","date":"2024-01-29T16:17:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3726,"user":"3DStudent","date":"2024-01-26T19:36:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T23:15:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17335,"user":"forest_light","date":"2024-01-23T23:59:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-23T20:37:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-23T09:34:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-22T22:07:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:36:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T05:14:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-01-21T21:17:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10829,"user":"Jtucker","date":"2024-01-21T18:11:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":679,"user":"Mark7","date":"2024-01-21T17:16:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7840,"user":"Stoneboss","date":"2024-01-21T15:38:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10543,"user":"Christine","date":"2024-01-21T11:39:57+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-21T11:28:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-21T10:49:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":882,"user":"latulipenoire","date":"2024-01-21T02:07:06+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-20T19:12:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15669,"user":"Henchman 21","date":"2024-01-20T18:49:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-20T18:07:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7642,"user":"echo","date":"2024-01-20T17:24:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5546,"user":"Thebull","date":"2024-01-20T16:49:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14181,"user":"Wandering Star","date":"2024-01-20T16:36:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-01-20T16:33:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6987,"user":"Two-tents","date":"2024-01-20T16:33:01+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":8018,"user":"luc","id":1156850,"date":"2024-01-20T15:55:23+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">A: As yet unknown organic structure throughout the body carrying a different fluid other than blood or lymph that is related to light. Your ancestors glowed and transmitted light and power.<br /><br />Q: (Joe) Was that related to the veins? They were talking about blue veins or the light coming from them... Wasn&#039;t there some session about it?<br /><br />(L) There was, there was something about it. I think we were talking about dancing once and they were talking about some kind of energy flow that came through the arms that allowed them to be able to levitate.<br /><br />(Joe) Yeah, that was the spear-handed Maruts and stuff like that.<br /><br />(L) Is that why, or the means by which, some odd people throughout history have been able to levitate because they had some genetic quirk that allowed this system to be operational?<br /><br />A: Yes.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 30\" data-quote=\"Joe\" data-source=\"post: 1156767\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156767\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156767\">Joe said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Here&#039;s the reference I was thinking of.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />This reminds me of what the &quot;Munich Cosmic Circle&quot; (around 1900) said about what they called &quot;Blutleuchte&quot; (&quot;blood light&quot; or &quot;blood beacon&quot;). Here&#039;s a bit about one of its members, Alfred Schuler,  from Wikipedia:<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"\" data-quote=\"\" data-source=\"\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">At the end of the nineteenth century the Munich <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Borough\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">borough</a> of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Schwabing\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Schwabing</a> became the center of certain anti-<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle-class\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">bourgeois</a> forces tending towards an interest in the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Occult\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">occult</a>, among which were found the secretive cult of the <i>Blutleuchte</i> (&quot;Blood Beacon&quot;). An <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Esotericism\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">occult circle</a> (<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Munich_Cosmic_Circle\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Munich Cosmic Circle</a>) gravitating around <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karl_Wolfskehl\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Karl Wolfskehl</a>, Alfred Schuler and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ludwig_Klages\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Ludwig Klages</a> developed a doctrine according to which the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Western_world\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Occident</a> was plagued by downfall and degeneration, caused by the rationalizing and demythologizing effects of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Christianity\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Christianity</a>, held to be responsible for the betrayal of life&#039;s primary forces. A way out of this desolate state could, according to the &quot;Cosmic&quot; view, only be found by a return to the pagan origins. No exact common ground did however exist, as to what this &quot;homecoming&quot; would entail.<br /><br />Alfred Schuler and Ludwig Klages came to know each other in 1893.<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alfred_Schuler#cite_note-2\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">[note 1]</a> They were, above all others, the leading personalities of the &quot;Blutleuchte&quot; and, with a few other &#039;initiates&#039; such as <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ludwig_Derleth\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Ludwig Derleth</a> and the poet <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karl_Wolfskehl\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">Karl Wolfskehl</a>, the founders of this &quot;occult circle&quot;. The first contact with Stefan George was established through Wolfskehl.<br /><br /><b>As clearly signalled by the name, &quot;Blutleuchte&quot;, &quot;Blood&quot; and &quot;Light&quot; were to play an important role. With the historical &quot;degeneration of the blood&quot;, held to be a sacred life elixir and a metaphysical substrate of souls, &quot;truthful&quot; life was seen as sinking into an ever more weakened state. And thus it was found to be necessary to lead this conception of the blood up to its former state of light and power, as it was thought to have been in heathen times thousands of years ago, and to some degree in antiquity. In the sign of the &quot;Blood Beacon&quot; and the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Swastika\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">swastika</a>, its <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incarnate\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">incarnate</a> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Emblem\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">emblem</a>, a healthy state of life were to be regained.<br /><br />From a chosen few, among which they imagined themselves to be and in which the &quot;untainted blood&quot; was supposed to be still working its healthy influence, a reversal was thought to be possible. By the work of these chosen few, the &quot;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incarnation\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">incarnation</a> of the undying spark of a distant past&quot; (L. Klages), the founding energies of the &quot;cosmic <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solstice\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">solstice</a>&quot; were to be rekindled. The occult practices of the <i>Blutleuchte</i> was supposed to be a symbiosis of heathendom and &quot;lordly leadership&quot; in the service of a wayward humanity in need of a fundamental <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palingenesis\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">rebirth</a>.</b></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />Now, these guys were a mixed bag, to say the least. But maybe they were unto something here. I haven&#039;t read the primary works (Ludwig Klages wrote extensively, for example), might check this out at some point.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":47,"user":"Ryan","date":"2024-03-24T05:15:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-30T18:54:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17281,"user":"Aylen","date":"2024-01-28T23:19:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-25T13:35:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T23:16:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17335,"user":"forest_light","date":"2024-01-24T01:47:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4601,"user":"987baz","date":"2024-01-24T01:22:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-22T22:09:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12829,"user":"ryu","date":"2024-01-22T21:28:55+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-01-22T19:47:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15102,"user":"Kari Baba","date":"2024-01-22T13:16:47+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:36:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16791,"user":"Benjamin","date":"2024-01-22T07:54:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T05:22:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11403,"user":"Sylvia","date":"2024-01-22T03:30:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-01-21T21:19:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":679,"user":"Mark7","date":"2024-01-21T17:19:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-21T11:29:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-21T10:50:49+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3693,"user":"JEEP","date":"2024-01-21T05:14:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":882,"user":"latulipenoire","date":"2024-01-21T03:49:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18714,"user":"Freya Stewart","date":"2024-01-21T02:01:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-20T22:42:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-20T20:47:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-01-20T20:12:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7776,"user":"Carl","date":"2024-01-20T19:38:22+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-20T19:13:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-20T18:17:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7687,"user":"A Jay","date":"2024-01-20T17:42:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3,"user":"Approaching Infinity","date":"2024-01-20T17:14:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12487,"user":"Akul","date":"2024-01-20T16:56:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5546,"user":"Thebull","date":"2024-01-20T16:49:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-01-20T15:58:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":27,"user":"Beau","date":"2024-01-20T15:58:24+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":12487,"user":"Akul","id":1156864,"date":"2024-01-20T17:06:26+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 8018\" data-quote=\"luc\" data-source=\"post: 1156850\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156850\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156850\">luc said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">This reminds me of what the &quot;Munich Cosmic Circle&quot; (around 1900) said about what they called &quot;Blutleuchte&quot; (&quot;blood light&quot; or &quot;blood beacon&quot;). Here&#039;s a bit about one of its members, Alfred Schuler,  from Wikipedia:<br /><br />At the end of the nineteenth century the Munich borough of Schwabing became the center of certain anti-bourgeois forces tending towards an interest in the occult, among which were found the secretive cult of the Blutleuchte (&quot;Blood Beacon&quot;). An occult circle (Munich Cosmic Circle) gravitating around Karl Wolfskehl, Alfred Schuler and Ludwig Klages developed a doctrine according to which the Occident was plagued by downfall and degeneration, caused by the rationalizing and demythologizing effects of Christianity, held to be responsible for the betrayal of life&#039;s primary forces. A way out of this desolate state could, according to the &quot;Cosmic&quot; view, only be found by a return to the pagan origins. No exact common ground did however exist, as to what this &quot;homecoming&quot; would entail.<br /><br />Alfred Schuler and Ludwig Klages came to know each other in 1893.[note 1] They were, above all others, the leading personalities of the &quot;Blutleuchte&quot; and, with a few other &#039;initiates&#039; such as Ludwig Derleth and the poet Karl Wolfskehl, the founders of this &quot;occult circle&quot;. The first contact with Stefan George was established through Wolfskehl.<br /><br />As clearly signalled by the name, &quot;Blutleuchte&quot;, &quot;Blood&quot; and &quot;Light&quot; were to play an important role. With the historical &quot;degeneration of the blood&quot;, held to be a sacred life elixir and a metaphysical substrate of souls, &quot;truthful&quot; life was seen as sinking into an ever more weakened state. And thus it was found to be necessary to lead this conception of the blood up to its former state of light and power, as it was thought to have been in heathen times thousands of years ago, and to some degree in antiquity. In the sign of the &quot;Blood Beacon&quot; and the swastika, its incarnate emblem, a healthy state of life were to be regained.<br /><br />From a chosen few, among which they imagined themselves to be and in which the &quot;untainted blood&quot; was supposed to be still working its healthy influence, a reversal was thought to be possible. By the work of these chosen few, the &quot;incarnation of the undying spark of a distant past&quot; (L. Klages), the founding energies of the &quot;cosmic solstice&quot; were to be rekindled. The occult practices of the Blutleuchte was supposed to be a symbiosis of heathendom and &quot;lordly leadership&quot; in the service of a wayward humanity in need of a fundamental rebirth.<br /><br />Now, these guys were a mixed bag, to say the least. But maybe they were unto something here. I haven&#039;t read the primary works (Ludwig Klages wrote extensively, for example), might check this out at some point.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Maybe am mistaken, and possibly some could feel offended, but could the ritual sacrifices of humans (and even cannibalism), and in Christanity&#039;s eucharist practice of &quot;eating the body of Christ&quot; and &quot;drinking the blood of Christ&quot; actually be, or at least echoes, some STS sinister necromancy degeneration?","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":9854,"user":"oli 518","date":"2024-02-09T15:03:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-30T18:54:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T08:20:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3726,"user":"3DStudent","date":"2024-01-26T19:41:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T23:16:28+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-23T20:38:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-01-22T19:47:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:36:49+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T05:24:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-01-21T21:19:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19656,"user":"JandI","date":"2024-01-21T20:04:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4518,"user":"Adobe","date":"2024-01-21T15:11:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-21T11:30:06+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5546,"user":"Thebull","date":"2024-01-20T23:50:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-20T22:42:49+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":12487,"user":"Akul","id":1156869,"date":"2024-01-20T17:32:21+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12487\" data-quote=\"Akul\" data-source=\"post: 1156864\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156864\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156864\">Akul said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Maybe am mistaken, and possibly some could feel offended, but could the ritual sacrifices of humans (and even cannibalism), and in Christanity&#039;s eucharist practice of &quot;eating the body of Christ&quot; and &quot;drinking the blood of Christ&quot; actually be, or at least echoes, some STS sinister necromancy degeneration?</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl is-pending is-recrawl  js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"194500\" data-url=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/julius-caesar-and-mithraism.52358/#post-1045912\" data-host=\"cassiopaea.org\" data-pending=\"true\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/img/FB_sky.jpg\" alt=\"cassiopaea.org\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/julius-caesar-and-mithraism.52358/#post-1045912\"class=\"link link--internal fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"\"rel=\"\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Julius Caesar and Mithraism</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">First, as the saying goes, let&#039;s render unto Caesar the things that are Caesar&#039;s. The following article taps into some key ideas shared by Laura.  Julius Caesar and Mithraism  Mithraism has been lionized by generations of historians. In particular, Belgian historian Franz Cumont[1] who dominated...</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/styles/cass/img/favicon.png\" alt=\"cassiopaea.org\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>cassiopaea.org</div></div></div></div><br />&quot;Thank you very much for sharing it. So if I understood it correctly, the cult of Mithraism is the cult of reenacting the assassination of Julius Caesar, which if he was the inspiration for Paul&#039;s Christ... it&#039;s the constant killing of the principles which Paul was attempting to convey to humanity, correct?&quot;<br /><br />&quot;Exactly! This reenactment / celebration is still going on today under other covers. Literally satanic. At a human level, a manifestation of the destructive nature of 4D STS.&quot;<br /><br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl is-pending is-recrawl  js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"194501\" data-url=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/julius-caesar-and-mithraism.52358/page-2#post-1045991\" data-host=\"cassiopaea.org\" data-pending=\"true\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/img/FB_sky.jpg\" alt=\"cassiopaea.org\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/julius-caesar-and-mithraism.52358/page-2#post-1045991\"class=\"link link--internal fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"\"rel=\"\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Julius Caesar and Mithraism</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">Pierre vous êtes passionnant, je reconnais votre intelligence supérieure et vous suis infiniment reconnaissante de la partager avec nous... Je me suis permis de faire un copier/coller de votre article en Français que je relierai avec plaisir, à loisir pour mieux m&#039;en imprégner...  UN GRAND MERCI...</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/styles/cass/img/favicon.png\" alt=\"cassiopaea.org\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>cassiopaea.org</div></div></div></div><br />&quot;In the Catholic tradition, we cannibalize the body of Christ. This act is called Eucharist and the origin is, supposedly, the last supper&quot;<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 2167\" data-quote=\"Alejo\" data-source=\"post: 1045999\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1045999\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1045999\">Alejo said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">And it’s interesting that the bull represents virility in several cultures, manliness and strength of will. Without a will to resist, we’re more than willing slaves.<br /><br />But also, this whole tendency to label everything as toxic masculinity, and feminizing society, kind of takes on a different meaning when viewed through the lens of Mithras.<br /><br />And it works it’s magic in society by hooking itself on the most compassionate and empathic aspects of that masculinity. By creating guilt with twisted logic.<br /><br />The other interesting aspect is that the bull in the ritual, much as it happened with Caesar, cannot be met head on, it had to be betrayed, lured in with false promises and then betrayed and murdered in cold blood.<br /><br />An abyss indeed.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />So the question is, could all this practices, more or less, actually be a reference to the STS &quot;cannibalization&quot; of the blood light (both materialistically and what it represents as an energy/virtue)?","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":19538,"user":"divusiulius","date":"2024-02-13T22:18:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11608,"user":"nidO","date":"2024-02-04T04:24:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-30T18:55:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15831,"user":"Sheeba","date":"2024-01-28T16:29:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T08:20:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3726,"user":"3DStudent","date":"2024-01-26T19:43:06+