entRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Flrc-cdn.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fassets%2F2021%2F02%2FLRC-share.jpg&amp;hash=9a8f978553366e878f1ee94ba667a9dd&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.lewrockwell.com\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://www.lewrockwell.com/2012/10/joseph-mercola/many-medications-remain-safe-and-effective-well-past-their-expiration-dates/\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Many Medications Remain Safe and Effective Well Past Their Expiration Dates - LewRockwell</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">Recently by Joseph Mercola: Antibiotic Alert: The Drug the Doctor Ordered Could Cause Deadly SideEffects       Story at-a-glance Prescription drugs typically have an expiration date of one to five years, but many “expired” drugs are just as potent as when they were originally made, even several...</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Flrc-cdn.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fassets%2F2017%2F09%2Fcropped-favicon-500x500-32x32.jpg&amp;hash=a3938930913a3714a283605cc021ec02&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"www.lewrockwell.com\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>www.lewrockwell.com</div></div></div></div><br /><br /><br />In short, the ivermectin will probably outlive us.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>That&#039;s why they are asking people to put out-of-date medicines back into the pharmacy. People think it&#039;s so they can throw them away in secure containers, but the real reason is that the medicines are being recycled. So it&#039;s a good reason not to &quot;give&quot; these medicines to the pharmacy, but to keep them for ourselves, because maybe one day we&#039;ll need them. Or for other people in need of them.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":8472,"user":"goyacobol","date":"2024-04-06T04:15:51+0200","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11608,"user":"nidO","date":"2024-02-06T06:20:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-30T19:36:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17281,"user":"Aylen","date":"2024-01-28T23:24:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15533,"user":"Deliverance","date":"2024-01-27T14:10:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T08:25:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7597,"user":"hiker","date":"2024-01-26T20:59:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-26T17:12:49+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12854,"user":"Tuulikki","date":"2024-01-25T09:30:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T23:29:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19148,"user":"Happy Poo","date":"2024-01-23T23:15:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-23T20:42:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10595,"user":"Korzik18","date":"2024-01-23T18:37:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-23T16:46:55+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11120,"user":"Mr.Cyan","date":"2024-01-23T15:25:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-22T22:14:57+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12829,"user":"ryu","date":"2024-01-22T21:23:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-22T20:42:55+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-22T18:43:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":360,"user":"mabar","date":"2024-01-22T18:13:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16911,"user":"AndrewMn","date":"2024-01-22T13:35:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3628,"user":"mantle","date":"2024-01-22T12:57:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:39:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16791,"user":"Benjamin","date":"2024-01-22T08:06:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T05:54:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11403,"user":"Sylvia","date":"2024-01-22T03:46:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-01-21T21:26:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15332,"user":"Matty F","date":"2024-01-21T19:29:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10829,"user":"Jtucker","date":"2024-01-21T18:20:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15669,"user":"Henchman 21","date":"2024-01-21T17:33:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12091,"user":"YoYa","date":"2024-01-21T16:30:28+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":8690,"user":"Corvus","date":"2024-01-21T16:21:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17361,"user":"seve","date":"2024-01-21T16:11:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7840,"user":"Stoneboss","date":"2024-01-21T15:48:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4518,"user":"Adobe","date":"2024-01-21T15:30:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12341,"user":"Laurentien2","date":"2024-01-21T13:49:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":297,"user":"Nienna","date":"2024-01-21T13:20:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2567,"user":"miguel angel","date":"2024-01-21T13:04:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11715,"user":"Ysus","date":"2024-01-21T12:44:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10543,"user":"Christine","date":"2024-01-21T12:04:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":68,"user":"Gaby","date":"2024-01-21T12:01:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-21T11:42:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":838,"user":"EricG","date":"2024-01-21T11:17:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-21T11:16:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-21T10:58:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-01-21T10:20:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4180,"user":"Lilou","date":"2024-01-21T05:14:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13103,"user":"Evan","date":"2024-01-21T04:24:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-01-21T03:15:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-21T01:33:44+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":12697,"user":"youlik","id":1156961,"date":"2024-01-21T03:15:42+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12487\" data-quote=\"Akul\" data-source=\"post: 1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156790\">Akul said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">No, you&#039;re completely extrapolating and misinterpreting context of my short statement. I did not refer to the &quot;ordinary residents&quot; neither their somekind of envy for international ordinary residents. All this is your words and viewpoint and it is really intriguing why are you having and bringing up such an idea.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>I did not touch on the context of your statement, I was only affected by an incorrect and unfair definition, which I tried to show. In this definition, I saw the &quot;protruding ears&quot; of the &quot;western mainstream&quot; and I will write about it below. You are right that my words about &quot;some kind of envy&quot; are my words and my point of view, but this is also my life and this idea did not &quot;arise&quot; as you write.<br />There was such a stamp in Soviet propaganda: the Western world is rotting. A joke based on this stamp was very well known among the people at that time. A dialogue between two Soviet citizens, one of whom has just returned from a trip to the West. They ask him: well, how are things there, are they rotting? He answers: of course they rot, but it smells so good.<br />A Russian proverb says that there is some truth in every joke, and in this sense, the above joke reflects the reason for the collapse of the Soviet system, I will write about this a little bit.<br />In general, your message is worth parsing for almost every sentence.<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12487\" data-quote=\"Akul\" data-source=\"post: 1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156790\">Akul said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">In the dictatorships the common people hardly have a major influence on the general inner and outer politics.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>This is not quite true. In any dictatorship, dictators monitor the condition of the masses, and those who do not end up quickly and badly. There are many examples of this from ancient times to the present day. From the modern one, we can recall Kampuchea from the time of the Khmer Rouge.<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12487\" data-quote=\"Akul\" data-source=\"post: 1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156790\">Akul said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Soviet Union was a political and military superpower, and Russia basically acted as the &quot;Slavic motherland&quot; for all the Eastern European countries.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>I would look a little wider here. A certain territory has undergone drastic, dramatic and catastrophic changes for many direct participants in a historically very short period of time, and at the same time, what you write about has not changed. The Russian Empire, the USSR and present-day Russia preserve this, and in this I see some &quot;supra-historical&quot;, if I may say so, objectivity. By the way, C&#039;s talked about the features of the genotype associated with geographical location.<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12487\" data-quote=\"Akul\" data-source=\"post: 1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156790\">Akul said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Dugin&#039;s fourth political theory and Russian&#039;s New World are basically the same, updated old ideologization - saying otherwise is pure naivety and ignorance.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>This is not for me at all. I am not familiar with Dugin&#039;s theories and know him only in the context of the tragedy that happened to his daughter.<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12487\" data-quote=\"Akul\" data-source=\"post: 1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156790\">Akul said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">The &quot;tyranny&quot; was not about controlling other countries because ordinary people lived there better than ordinary people in Russia but because of geopolitical interests and nothing much else.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Here you are turning it upside down. I didn&#039;t talk about tyranny BECAUSE some people lived better than others. I was talking about how it is somewhat strange to call tyranny a state where tyrants live worse than those who are tyrannized.<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12487\" data-quote=\"Akul\" data-source=\"post: 1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156790\">Akul said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">If the USSR &quot;rule&quot; - and in general the marxist-socialist ideological framework and structures of power in all the countries - would have been better then there wouldn&#039;t have happen such a big and sudden disintergration of the whole Eastern Bloc (including Yugoslavia). It practically fell apart by itself inside, with the downfall starting already in the late 70s or early 80s. It was simply faulty ideology, faulty measures to keep the power structures, common existential dread and needs, corruption, low conscientiousness and spirituality of collective generations.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>This is a completely false statement and again the notorious &quot;protruding ears of the Western mainstream&quot;, with the exception of just one word - corruption. The Soviet ideology, as a system of control and restriction, was no worse or better than any other. The Chinese won&#039;t let me lie. How can you not see? The collapse of the Soviet system did not happen for ideological reasons, but simply because the ruling elites were bribed. The Soviet Union was simply sold by its rulers and what rested on the influence of the Soviet Union immediately collapsed with it.<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12487\" data-quote=\"Akul\" data-source=\"post: 1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156790\">Akul said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Nazi Germany is out of question here. Why are you even bringing it up? It is really misleading and pointless excusing the harsh politics and humanitarian, social and economical distaters that happened during the USSR period by brining into the Nazi Germany or &quot;Western mainstream&quot;</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>No, dear interlocutor, this cannot be so. A little above, you said general words about &quot;forever&quot; or &quot;not forever&quot; and I will return the general words to you - everything is connected with everything.<br /> More specifically, the entire political structure of the modern world is based on the results of the Second World War or, as it is called in Russia, the Great Patriotic War or, in other words, the victory over Nazi Germany and its allies. Whether this is good or bad in this case is not important, it is important that this is so far the case. Here we come close to what this notorious &quot;Western mainstream&quot; is. The main goal of all this is to change the political structure of the world. To promote something they call a &quot;rules-based order,&quot; where the rule, in fact, should be one thing: as the world hegemon said, so it will be. In this sense, it is very important to reduce the importance of the outcome of this war as the cause of the modern political world order. This is done by all possible means (silencing, falsification, rewriting history) and, unfortunately, they are achieving some success.<br /> I recall the results of some surveys of young people in America. When asked who won the Second World War, almost everyone says that it is the United States and almost no one remembers the USSR. Similar polls in Japan (!) asking who used nuclear weapons in Hiroshima and Nagasaki are also shocking with their results. Young people either do not know, or say that the USSR did it and no one says what really happened.<br /> This is the result of the effort.<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12487\" data-quote=\"Akul\" data-source=\"post: 1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156790\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156790\">Akul said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Bringing up Nazi Germany or &quot;Western mainstream&quot; are only weasel words and strawman arguments to propagate USSR or &quot;Eastern mainstream&quot;.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>To what extent these are empty words and false arguments and in what place the propaganda of the USSR is present here, let people draw a conclusion, and here I can congratulate you on the &quot;eastern mainstream&quot;. I&#039;ve never heard of such a thing and, accordingly, you are the author. You can patent it.<br /><br /><div class=\"bbCodeSpoiler\"><button type=\"button\" class=\"bbCodeSpoiler-button button--longText button\" data-xf-click=\"toggle\" data-xf-init=\"tooltip\" title=\"Click to reveal or hide spoiler\"><span class=\"button-text\"><span>Spoiler: <span class=\"bbCodeSpoiler-button-title\">Russian spelling</span></span></span></button><div class=\"bbCodeSpoiler-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--spoiler\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\">Контекста вашего заявления я не касался, меня затронуло только неправильное и несправедливое определение, что я и пытался показать. В этом определении я увидел &quot;торчащие уши&quot; &quot;западного мейнстрима&quot;и чуть ниже я напишу об этом. Вы правы в том, что мои слова о &quot;некоей зависти&quot;, это мои слова и моя точка зрения, но это и моя жизнь и эта идея не &quot;возникла&quot;, как вы пишете.<br /> В советской пропаганде существовал такой штамп: западный мир загнивает. В народе в то время была очень известна шутка, основанная на этом штампе. Диалог двух советских граждан, один из которых только что вернулся из поездки на запад. Его спрашивают: ну и как там дела, загнивают? Он отвечает: конечно загнивают, но как приятно пахнет.<br /> Русская поговорка говорит о том, что в каждой шутке есть доля правды и в этом смысле в приведенной шутке отражена причина произошедшего развала советской системы, чуть я напишу и об этом.<br /> Вообще ваше сообщение достойно разбора почти по каждому предложению. <br />Это не совсем так. В любой диктатуре диктаторы следят за состоянием масс, а те кто этого не делает кончают быстро и плохо. Примеров тому очень много с древних времен и до наших дней. Из современного можно вспомнить Кампучию времен &quot;Красных Кхмеров&quot;.<br /> Здесь я посмотрел бы чуть шире. Определенная территория в исторически очень короткий срок претерпела кардинальные, драматические и катастрофические для многих непосредственных участников, изменения и при этом то, о чем вы пишете не изменилось. Российская Империя, СССР и нынешняя Россия сохраняют это и в этом я усматриваю некоторую &quot;надисторическую&quot;, если можно так сказать, объективность. Кстати, C&#039;s говорили об особенностях генотипа, связанных с географической локацией.<br /> Вот это вообще не ко мне. Я не знаком с теориями Дугина и знаю его только в контексте трагедии, произошедшей с его дочерью. <br />Здесь вы переворачиваете с ног на голову. Я не говорил о тирании ПОТОМУ ЧТО одни жили лучше других. Я говорил о том, несколько странно называть тиранией состояние, когда тираны живут хуже тех, кого тиранизируют.<br /> Это полностью ложное утверждение и опять пресловутые &quot; торчащие уши западного мейнстрима&quot;, за исключением всего одного слова- коррупция. Советская идеология, как система контроля и ограничения была ничем не хуже и не лучше любой другой. Китайцы не дадут мне соврать. Как вы не видите? Обрушение советской системы произошло не по идеологическим причинам, а банально из-за того, что удалось подкупить правящие элиты. Советский Союз просто продали его правители и то что держалось на влиянии Советского Союза немедленно рухнуло вместе с ним. <br /> Нет, уважаемый собеседник, это не может быть так. Чуть выше вы говорили общие слова про &quot;вечно&quot; или &quot;не вечно&quot; и я верну вам общие слова- все связано со всем. Если говорить конкретнее, то все политическое устройство современного мира основано на итогах Второй мировой войны или, как это называют у нас в России, Великая Отечественная Война или, другими словами, победы над фашистской Германией и ее союзниками. Плохо это или хорошо в данном случае не важно, важно что это пока так. Тут мы вплотную подходим к тому, что такое этот пресловутый &quot;западный мейнстрим&quot;. Основная цель всего этого изменить политическое устройство мира. Продвинуть нечто, что они называют &quot;порядок, основанный на правилах&quot;, где правило, по сути, должно быть одно: как сказал мировой гегемон, так и будет. В этом смысле очень важно снизить значение итогов этой войны, как причины современного политического мироустройства. Это делается всеми возможными средствами (замалчивания, фальсификации, переписывание истории) и, к сожалению, определенных успехов они добиваются. Я вспоминаю результаты некотрых опросов молодых людей в Америке. На вопрос кто победил во Второй мировой войне практически все говорят, что это США и почти никто не вспоминает об СССР. Подобные опросы в Японии(!) с вопросом кто применил ядерное оружие в Хиросиме и Нагасаки тоже шокируют своими результатами. Молодые люди или не знают, или говорят, что это сделал СССР и никто не говорит как было на самом деле. Вот это и есть результат усилий. <br />Насколько это пустые слова и ложные аргументы и в каком месте здесь присутствует пропаганда СССР, пусть люди делают вывод, а я здесь могу вас поздравить с &quot;восточным мейнстримом&quot;. Я никогда такого не слышал и, соответственно вы автор. Можете запатентовать.</div></div></div></div>","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":15533,"user":"Deliverance","date":"2024-01-27T14:16:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-26T17:21:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":1789,"user":"axj","date":"2024-01-23T21:46:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:39:15+0100","reaction":"Sad"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T06:10:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17354,"user":"Liliea","date":"2024-01-21T21:27:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19656,"user":"JandI","date":"2024-01-21T20:22:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-21T17:51:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19468,"user":"ImaPrototype","date":"2024-01-21T13:45:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-21T11:44:41+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-21T11:16:28+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13966,"user":"Tyomodachi","date":"2024-01-21T11:13:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12487,"user":"Akul","date":"2024-01-21T10:15:54+0100","reaction":"Sad"},{"user_id":9769,"user":"Altair","date":"2024-01-21T09:14:06+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4731,"user":"HiThere","date":"2024-01-21T09:01:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13103,"user":"Evan","date":"2024-01-21T04:29:39+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":11007,"user":"Bluegazer","id":1156984,"date":"2024-01-21T08:52:14+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 4717\" data-quote=\"Jones\" data-source=\"post: 1156821\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156821\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156821\">Jones said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">So, all liquids are fluids, but not all fluids are liquids. Don&#039;t know if the same applies in 4D, but the fluid that the C&#039;s are talking about could be a gas.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />Let&#039;s think about the electric current. In general, it is said to be a flow of charged particles. If we stick to the meaning of the words, where something has a flow, then it behaves like a fluid.<br /><br />I remember the C&#039;s said in a session something about dna and superconductivity.<br /><br />Where there is superconductivity, the flow of electrons occurs with almost no resistance....","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-30T19:38:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17281,"user":"Aylen","date":"2024-01-28T23:24:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T08:26:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-26T17:22:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12854,"user":"Tuulikki","date":"2024-01-25T09:30:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T23:30:06+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15962,"user":"Mililea","date":"2024-01-24T06:09:28+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4601,"user":"987baz","date":"2024-01-24T01:27:22+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-23T20:44:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-23T17:16:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-22T22:15:52+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-22T20:43:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-01-22T20:01:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-22T18:49:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18714,"user":"Freya Stewart","date":"2024-01-22T16:53:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:40:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16791,"user":"Benjamin","date":"2024-01-22T08:07:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T06:12:22+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11403,"user":"Sylvia","date":"2024-01-22T03:46:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5415,"user":"Skyalmian","date":"2024-01-21T22:15:17+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17354,"user":"Liliea","date":"2024-01-21T21:28:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-01-21T21:27:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15488,"user":"N1mTzo","date":"2024-01-21T21:23:06+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15332,"user":"Matty F","date":"2024-01-21T20:20:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10028,"user":"Cassandra94","date":"2024-01-21T19:18:41+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10829,"user":"Jtucker","date":"2024-01-21T18:20:22+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-21T17:52:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-21T17:08:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14324,"user":"Candice","date":"2024-01-21T16:17:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7840,"user":"Stoneboss","date":"2024-01-21T15:48:51+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-01-21T15:37:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12341,"user":"Laurentien2","date":"2024-01-21T14:12:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-21T11:44:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4717,"user":"Jones","date":"2024-01-21T11:24:52+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-21T11:16:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7850,"user":"Ðekel","date":"2024-01-21T11:16:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12779,"user":"Lukasz","date":"2024-01-21T10:59:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7642,"user":"echo","date":"2024-01-21T09:01:31+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":8018,"user":"luc","id":1156991,"date":"2024-01-21T09:31:32+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 7776\" data-quote=\"Carl\" data-source=\"post: 1156884\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156884\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156884\">Carl said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Good health-jitsu therefore should work on all levels. Lots of things can be effective, including all kinds of pills and powders, peptides and steroids, antibiotics, expensive technology such as HBOT, neurofeedback, zappers, some really whacky stuff, and much more.<br /><br />Many of us have benefited from such things and we continue to push and research this area for a good reason.<br /><br />That said, if you treat your physical body as *only* a 3d machine then I agree that you will certainly run into persistent un-fixable issues, and maybe even do more damage. A huge part of healing, protection and prevention work is mental/emotional, and a huge part also is &quot;spiritual&quot;.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />Yes, body and mind must go together, depend on each other, and interact with each other. Another reason why one size fits all approaches seldom exist: just as different physical conditions require different approaches, so too for different minds. Because of the interdependence of both, there are myriad variables.<br /><br />I&#039;m often amazed when I find out that something that was bothering me physically could be solved with changes in my mind. A trivial example is things like cortisol levels - if you constantly freak out because your mind constantly dwells on disaster, for instance, no supplements will help. You gotta change your mind.<br /><br />But I&#039;m ALSO often amazed when I find out stuff I thought were in my mind completely change or vanish because of physical treatment! It definitely goes both ways.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":47,"user":"Ryan","date":"2024-03-24T06:02:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9854,"user":"oli 518","date":"2024-02-19T22:13:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3248,"user":"Breton","date":"2024-02-13T21:44:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11608,"user":"nidO","date":"2024-02-06T06:22:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-30T19:38:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17281,"user":"Aylen","date":"2024-01-28T23:25:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17307,"user":"Asa","date":"2024-01-28T22:42:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15533,"user":"Deliverance","date":"2024-01-27T14:19:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T08:27:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-26T17:23:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17335,"user":"forest_light","date":"2024-01-25T10:06:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T23:31:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11262,"user":"Matai","date":"2024-01-24T08:14:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15962,"user":"Mililea","date":"2024-01-24T06:09:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4601,"user":"987baz","date":"2024-01-24T01:27:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":1789,"user":"axj","date":"2024-01-23T21:47:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-23T20:44:28+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-23T17:17:16+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11120,"user":"Mr.Cyan","date":"2024-01-23T15:26:22+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2451,"user":"Aiming","date":"2024-01-23T12:31:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-22T22:16:16+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12829,"user":"ryu","date":"2024-01-22T21:24:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-22T20:45:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-22T18:50:22+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:40:42+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16791,"user":"Benjamin","date":"2024-01-22T08:10:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11107,"user":"kaixin82","date":"2024-01-22T07:39:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T06:15:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11403,"user":"Sylvia","date":"2024-01-22T03:46:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":27,"user":"Beau","date":"2024-01-21T21:54:51+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17354,"user":"Liliea","date":"2024-01-21T21:28:49+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-01-21T21:28:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19656,"user":"JandI","date":"2024-01-21T20:23:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15332,"user":"Matty F","date":"2024-01-21T20:23:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10829,"user":"Jtucker","date":"2024-01-21T18:20:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-21T17:52:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-21T17:09:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":8690,"user":"Corvus","date":"2024-01-21T16:23:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17361,"user":"seve","date":"2024-01-21T16:11:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7840,"user":"Stoneboss","date":"2024-01-21T15:49:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-01-21T15:37:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":882,"user":"latulipenoire","date":"2024-01-21T14:18:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12341,"user":"Laurentien2","date":"2024-01-21T14:13:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":8877,"user":"Persej","date":"2024-01-21T13:57:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7687,"user":"A Jay","date":"2024-01-21T13:50:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":30,"user":"Joe","date":"2024-01-21T13:43:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":297,"user":"Nienna","date":"2024-01-21T13:21:52+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11868,"user":"Ursus Minor","date":"2024-01-21T12:35:16+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11007,"user":"Bluegazer","date":"2024-01-21T12:11:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-21T11:45:32+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":17563,"user":"cosmo_alex","id":1156996,"date":"2024-01-21T09:53:23+0100","text":"Great story.<br /><br />One of the topics that I am currently interested in is the way of life of ancient man. That&#039;s why I study the Indians of North America. They seemed to have the least contact with the “gods.” And one gets the feeling that their thinking, way of life - everything is very close to what a person should be.  Not absolutely, but I see something important in them.  So here it is.<br /><br />Can anybody tell me more about how the agricultural way of life influenced people&#039;s thinking and development?  Maybe there was a transcript.  Or someone will share their observations.<br /><br />After all, it is interesting that hunting and gathering do not provide guarantees of surviving the winter, and agriculture and raising livestock quickly led to the creation of money, states and gave rise to the vices of civilization and thinking.  I really want to understand what Cassiopeia and nearby sources say about this.<br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 9px\">(My + Google translate)<br />Отличная запись. Одна из тем, которой я сейчас интересуюсь, это образ жизни древнего человека. Поэтому изучаю индейцев северной Америки. Они как будто меньше всего соприкасались с &quot;богами&quot;. И создаётся ощущение, что их мышление, образ жизни - всё очень близко к тому, каким должен быть человек. Не абсолютно, но что-то важное в них вижу.<br />Так вот. Можете больше подсказать, как аграрный образ жизни повлиял на мышление и развитие людей? Может, была стенограмма. Или кто-то поделится своими наблюдениями. Ведь это интересно, что охота и собирательство не дают гарантий пережить зиму, а сельское хозяйство и выращивание скота быстро привело к созданию денег, государств и породило пороки цивилизации и мышления. Очень хочется понять, что об этом говорят Кассиопея и ближайшие источники</span>.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-30T19:38:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15533,"user":"Deliverance","date":"2024-01-27T14:20:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3726,"user":"3DStudent","date":"2024-01-26T19:56:06+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T23:32:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12829,"user":"ryu","date":"2024-01-22T21:25:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-22T18:51:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-22T10:41:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-22T06:17:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-01-21T21:28:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7642,"user":"echo","date":"2024-01-21T11:19:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-21T11:17:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6269,"user":"loreta","date":"2024-01-21T10:27:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14181,"user":"Wandering Star","date":"2024-01-21T10:20:26+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":12487,"user":"Akul","id":1156999,"date":"2024-01-21T10:10:02+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12697\" data-quote=\"youlik\" data-source=\"post: 1156961\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156961\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156961\">youlik said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">I did not touch on the context of your statement, I was only affected by an incorrect and unfair definition, which I tried to show.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Why are you going beyond a mere correction of some definition, writing a whole narrative defending a STS psychopathic system?<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12697\" data-quote=\"youlik\" data-source=\"post: 1156961\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156961\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156961\">youlik said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">I didn&#039;t talk about tyranny BECAUSE some people lived better than others. I was talking about how it is somewhat strange to call tyranny a state where tyrants live worse than those who are tyrannized.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>To not have been a tyranny in which tens of millions have died, existed gulags and various forms of opression till this day...<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12697\" data-quote=\"youlik\" data-source=\"post: 1156961\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156961\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156961\">youlik said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \"><b>This is a completely false statement and again the notorious &quot;protruding ears of the Western mainstream&quot;, with the exception of just one word - corruption. The Soviet ideology, as a system of control and restriction, was no worse or better than any other. The Chinese won&#039;t let me lie. How can you not see? The collapse of the Soviet system did not happen for ideological reasons, but simply because the ruling elites were bribed.</b> <b>The Soviet Union was simply sold by its rulers and what rested on the influence of the Soviet Union immediately collapsed with it.<br /><br />Here we come close to what this notorious &quot;Western mainstream&quot; is. The main goal of all this is to change the political structure of the world. To promote something they call a &quot;rules-based order,&quot; where the rule, in fact, should be one thing: as the world hegemon said, so it will be. In this sense, it is very important to reduce the importance of the outcome of this war as the cause of the modern political world order. This is done by all possible means (silencing, falsification, rewriting history) and, unfortunately, they are achieving some success.</b></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>...putting the blame to the fall of the psychopathic system to a small group and an elite and specifically their corruption and not on the corrupt system and ideology itself. So typical.<br /><br />...that the Soviet ideology as a system was no worse or better than any other - by comparing it to the worst of the worst likes of Nazi Germany and Mao&#039;s China where died and which caused deaths and else in similar and greater number of <i>tens of millions of people</i>. We are not even touching to issue of lack of freedom, censorship, political and ideological oppression and other silencing, falsfication and historical revisionism, poverty and many other issues in USSR.<br /><br />Such a friendly and exemplary companionship to give USSR an impression of being a system of such integrity and idealism to the point you say in the same sentence &quot;<a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/session-13-january-2024.54173/page-17#post-1156711\" class=\"link link--internal\">I don&#039;t want to portray the USSR as the best human formation that existed, probably not, but seeing what was happening on the &quot;other side&quot;, I can&#039;t put it next to it</a>&quot; - as if there&#039;s <i>any</i> chance it could have been &quot;the best human formation that existed&quot;. It is ridiculous even having in the same sentence &quot;best&quot; and &quot;USSR&quot;. Do you even know how much is common to hear in the West such illusionary statements about the &quot;ideal&quot; communist countries? How the joke goes:<br /><br /><script class=\"js-extraPhrases\" type=\"application/json\">{\"lightbox_close\": \"Close\",\"lightbox_next\": \"Next\",\"lightbox_previous\": \"Previous\",\"lightbox_error\": \"The requested content cannot be loaded. Please try again later.\",\"lightbox_start_slideshow\": \"Start slideshow\",\"lightbox_stop_slideshow\": \"Stop slideshow\",\"lightbox_full_screen\": \"Full screen\",\"lightbox_thumbnails\": \"Thumbnails\",\"lightbox_download\": \"Download\",\"lightbox_share\": \"Share\",\"lightbox_zoom\": \"Zoom\",\"lightbox_new_window\": \"New window\",\"lightbox_toggle_sidebar\": \"Toggle sidebar\"}</script><div class=\"bbImageWrapper  js-lbImage\" title=\"main-qimg-bd98dc6d22635451f554dec9a9672da8-lq\"data-src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fqph.cf2.quoracdn.net%2Fmain-qimg-bd98dc6d22635451f554dec9a9672da8-lq&amp;hash=1b53c38a12c6691adfabac4588335ba8\" data-lb-sidebar-href=\"\" data-lb-caption-extra-html=\"\" data-single-image=\"1\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fqph.cf2.quoracdn.net%2Fmain-qimg-bd98dc6d22635451f554dec9a9672da8-lq&amp;hash=1b53c38a12c6691adfabac4588335ba8\"data-url=\"https://qph.cf2.quoracdn.net/main-qimg-bd98dc6d22635451f554dec9a9672da8-lq\"class=\"bbImage\"data-zoom-target=\"1\"style=\"width: 227px\"alt=\"main-qimg-bd98dc6d22635451f554dec9a9672da8-lq\"title=\"\"width=\"\" height=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" /></div><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12697\" data-quote=\"youlik\" data-source=\"post: 1156961\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156961\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156961\">youlik said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">To what extent these are empty words and false arguments and in what place the propaganda of the USSR is present here, let people draw a conclusion,</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Look at your wording.<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 12697\" data-quote=\"youlik\" data-source=\"post: 1156961\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156961\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156961\">youlik said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">and here I can congratulate you on the &quot;eastern mainstream&quot;. I&#039;ve never heard of such a thing and, accordingly, you are the author. You can patent it.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Thanks, but I am not interested in playing dichotomy games with &quot;Western mainstream&quot; ignoring the existence of its counterpart(s), as if there wasn&#039;t already division of the world order after the World War II and didn&#039;t happen the Cold War. If you wish to promote and propagate STS Eastern mainstream viewpoints capitalizing on the anti-Western mainstream rationalization and sentiments of others - good luck.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-22T18:53:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":19656,"user":"JandI","date":"2024-01-21T20:26:04+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":54,"user":"Timótheos","id":1157023,"date":"2024-01-21T11:27:05+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 6269\" data-quote=\"loreta\" data-source=\"post: 1156950\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156950\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156950\">loreta said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">That&#039;s why they are asking people to put out-of-date medicines back into the pharmacy. People think it&#039;s so they can throw them away in secure containers, but the real reason is that the medicines are being recycled. So it&#039;s a good reason not to &quot;give&quot; these medicines to the pharmacy, but to keep them for ourselves, because maybe one day we&#039;ll need them. Or for other people in need of them.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Not sure about the laws for pharmacies in other countries, but in Canada this is definitely not true.  People are asked to bring in their expired prescriptions, which are taken by the pharmacist and put into a big 5 gallon medical waste bucket, and when full, is picked up to be incinerated.  It is illegal for pharmacists in Canada to dispense, reuse or sell any expired medicine.<br /><br />That being said, the way I understand it, an expiry date on a medicine refers to the approximate date when that drug has lost more than 5% of its potency, which renders it below the minimum efficacious threshold in medical terms.  The drug doesn&#039;t suddenly become ineffective or turn poisonous, and can still be up to 95% effective or less, gradually decreasing over time, which means they can be safely used for years after the printed expiry date.<br /><br />So, with that in mind, it&#039;s best to save all your medicines regardless of the expiry date, as they will likely work well enough and may prove to be quite valuable in the future when more and more shortages start to appear.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":47,"user":"Ryan","date":"2024-03-24T06:03:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9854,"user":"oli 518","date":"2024-02-19T22:19:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3248,"user":"Breton","date":"2024-02-13T21:45:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11608,"user":"nidO","date":"2024-02-06T06:23:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-30T19:38:55+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15533,"user":"Deliverance","date":"2024-01-27T14:23:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T08:28:52+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7597,"user":"hiker","date":"2024-01-27T06:31:52+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3726,"user":"3DStudent","date":"2024-01-26T19:58:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-26T17:27:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17335,"user":"forest_light","date":"2024-01-25T10:07:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12854,"user":"Tuulikki","date":"2024-01-25T09:35:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T23:33:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11262,"user":"Matai","date":"2024-01-24T08:15:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15962,"user":"Mililea","date":"2024-01-24T06:11:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17310,"user":"Anya112003","date":"2024-01-23T20:46:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-23T17:19:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11120,"user":"Mr.Cyan","date":"2024-01-23T15:26:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5,"user":"herondancer","date":"2024-01-23T07:31:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-22T22:17:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-01-22T20:47:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo