5,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-21T18:44:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12341,"user":"Laurentien2","date":"2024-01-21T18:36:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-21T18:02:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15669,"user":"Henchman 21","date":"2024-01-21T17:37:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-21T17:20:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6460,"user":"Puma","date":"2024-01-21T17:17:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-01-21T17:03:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3770,"user":"sid","date":"2024-01-21T16:36:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4383,"user":"Maat","date":"2024-01-21T16:32:06+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14181,"user":"Wandering Star","date":"2024-01-21T16:22:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":8690,"user":"Corvus","date":"2024-01-21T16:17:49+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":8877,"user":"Persej","id":1157105,"date":"2024-01-21T16:29:37+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17563\" data-quote=\"cosmo_alex\" data-source=\"post: 1156996\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1156996\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1156996\">cosmo_alex said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Can anybody tell me more about how the agricultural way of life influenced people&#039;s thinking and development? Maybe there was a transcript. Or someone will share their observations.<br /><br />After all, it is interesting that hunting and gathering do not provide guarantees of surviving the winter, and agriculture and raising livestock quickly led to the creation of money, states and gave rise to the vices of civilization and thinking. I really want to understand what Cassiopeia and nearby sources say about this.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />I think I know what the C&#039;s have meant when they said, &quot;The mindset of the purpose of the agrarian diet is related.&quot;<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">(gottathink) Dentist Weston Price has documented the drastic change in jaw structure following the introduction of agrarian diets to groups of peoples. Is this one of the causes of the DNA damage causing truncated fluid flow?<br /><br />(L) Well, that&#039;s based on the question which we&#039;ve already rejected. So I guess in a sense that question is unaskable as it&#039;s written... But the question is still valid: Does the introduction of agrarian diets help perpetuate this condition or this truncation, this genetic deficiency or lack of upregulation of the genes that allow for this?<br /><br />A: Yes<br /><br />Q: (L) So agrarian diets are wholly responsible?<br /><br />A: No<br /><br />Q: (L) Partly responsible?<br /><br />A: Yes.<b> The mindset of the purpose of the agrarian diet is related.</b></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />The purpose of the agrarian diet is about preserving the food for winter, because you cannot hunt and gather all year round in the current climate on this planet. So, what Weston Price has documented in his book is not actually the drastic change in jaw structure following the introduction of agrarian diets to groups of peoples, but he documented that drastic change in bone structure came as a consequence of introduction of food that came from the central states to its colonies. And the only way that food can be brought by long travel to the colonies unspoiled is by refining them. And in order to do that, you have to strip away that food from many nutrients. Wheat flour is stripped away from bran and germ, cows are fed certain food that makes the butter hard at room temperature, sugar is heavily used in canned food as a preservative, and so on...<br /><br />And that is what Weston Price claimed that made people sick, the process of preserving the food, not agrarian diets per se.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":47,"user":"Ryan","date":"2024-03-24T06:06:55+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3443,"user":"Turgon","date":"2024-03-02T02:22:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11608,"user":"nidO","date":"2024-02-06T06:36:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-01-31T20:30:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17284,"user":"ELT","date":"2024-01-30T15:27:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15831,"user":"Sheeba","date":"2024-01-28T16:40:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T08:33:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7597,"user":"hiker","date":"2024-01-27T06:38:47+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12854,"user":"Tuulikki","date":"2024-01-25T09:42:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-24T23:41:27+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-23T17:28:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5809,"user":"Breo","date":"2024-01-23T17:17:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17361,"user":"seve","date":"2024-01-23T10:30:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-01-22T22:19:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,