2024<br /><br /><br />(Ryan) And is the astral plane related to these?<br /><br />A: Not so much. Astral involves &quot;emotions.&quot;</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Thank you for the session.<br />This maybe is the reason that many times people are seeing all these monsters near military bases or battle fields; all human negative thoughts, fears, hate or just emotions general are energy that can be seen as alive beings or forces on astral plane. And of course there is beings above these that eat these emotions, just like we eat chicken <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/smiley.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":-)\" title=\"Smile    :-)\" data-shortname=\":-)\" /><br /><br />If being (who or what ever) is evolved enough on his/her path the these forces then can be controlled and be used in good or bad. This Banana Guy from wave came in to my mind where he made somekind of spell to books writer and after that she had health issues and pool water changed to ”peasoup”. Eventually problem thankfully solved, but makes me wonder what the forces truly were.<br /><br />Many of you have read Castanedas books and ie in The Second Ring of Power there Carlos meets ”ally” many times in different forms. These forms are maybe elementals that he sees in different animal forms and in general if person doesnt have enough love/knowledge/will to control these forces, these forces can walk over that person.<br /><br />Think someone would be thrown to astral plane and could not control his thoughts or emotions at all, these own thoughts would eat this newcomer alive. So yes we all should strive up and purify ourselves.<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Q: (Joe) Is there any particular specific precaution we could take for this particular possible virus that&#039;s upcoming? Other than what we are already doing?<br /><br />A: No.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />I had on issue when found out what they are doing to us with COVID. First trying to understand that they really are doing this, after that thinking surviving, peoples suffering, what stuff to buy before everything goes down. But why? Yes, food, basic health supplies, toilet paper and tobacco for some, but anything too much extra will act like magnet that asks for trouble. And I have seen that Nature tries always give you what you want, but it rarely is in the form you thought it would be. For PTB also. So like one of my ex-boss use to say; who prepares for everything is not prepared for anything.<br /><br />Still reading comments, just couple thoughts from the session.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":13215,"user":"ApotheosisMMC.","date":"2024-03-29T05:16:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9854,"user":"oli 518","date":"2024-02-22T01:56:26+0100","reaction":"Love"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-02-02T17:49:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3726,"user":"3DStudent","date":"2024-01-31T19:03:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17361,"user":"seve","date":"2024-01-28T18:17:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-01-27T09:36:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":86,"user":"Ca.","date":"2024-01-27T05:08:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11403,"user":"Sylvia","date":"2024-01-25T23:08:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":882,"user":"latulipenoire","date":"2024-01-25T14:00:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17335,"user":"forest_light","date":"2024-01-25T11:15:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-01-25T05:38:49+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7840,"user":"Stoneboss","date":"2024-01-25T04:08:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":679,"user":"Mark7","date":"2024-01-25T02:27:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-01-25T02:27:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-25T01:25:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16791,"user":"Benjamin","date":"2024-01-25T01:13:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-25T00:33:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5393,"user":"sbeaudry","date":"2024-01-24T21:13:15+0100","reaction":"Love"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-01-24T19:45:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-24T18:13:49+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13630,"user":"Stella Marys","date":"2024-01-24T17:48:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7505,"user":"MK Scarlett","date":"2024-01-24T17:23:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-24T16:55:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-24T16:17:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17354,"user":"Liliea","date":"2024-01-24T16:03:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-01-24T14:21:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15332,"user":"Matty F","date":"2024-01-24T11:24:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15344,"user":"Cassis","date":"2024-01-24T11:13:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-24T10:53:55+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7642,"user":"echo","date":"2024-01-24T10:33:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-24T09:30:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-24T08:10:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":1533,"user":"Debra","date":"2024-01-24T07:42:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6269,"user":"loreta","date":"2024-01-24T07:33:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6460,"user":"Puma","date":"2024-01-24T07:33:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11120,"user":"Mr.Cyan","date":"2024-01-24T07:02:06+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5546,"user":"Thebull","date":"2024-01-24T06:47:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-01-24T06:25:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14181,"user":"Wandering Star","date":"2024-01-24T05:58:36+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":8800,"user":"SMM","id":1157712,"date":"2024-01-24T07:26:15+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"\" data-quote=\"\" data-source=\"\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">The subconscious and collective unconscious might be another way to describe our perceptions of a thing&#039;s essence.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />I mean this in the sense of looking within, as it states in the article, as per the maxim - &quot;As above, so below. As within, so without.&quot;<br /><br />For example, in The Wave, when Laura fought the spiders.<br /><br />So, we see from our collective unconsciousness&#039; perspective - through a 3D lens.<br /><br />It is worth adding this part from the article about Medusa (Jellyfish):<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"\" data-quote=\"\" data-source=\"\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \"><b>Jellyfish (medusa)</b> also gracefully move with the currents, not actively pursuing prey, but rather creating a gentle pulsating current to draw plankton into their “mouths”.  Although not engaged in active confrontation, both anemone and jellyfish employ electrochemical means for survival and defense.  Medusa and anemone are essentially unstructured, and share symptoms of hypersensitivity alternating with numbness, as well as many characteristics of the better-known sepia. There’s a desire for movement, along with sensitivity to their environment and a desire to “escape” from family and friends. But where sepia is usually shut down, medusa is “alive”, even if “alive” means restless and irritable! Medusa is also known for distress at times of major transition.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>","attachments":[],"reactions":[]},{"user_id":17563,"user":"cosmo_alex","id":1157799,"date":"2024-01-24T15:18:47+0100","text":"I studied the basic answers about agricultural nutrition and agriculture.<br />Thanks everyone, it was informative!<br /><br />It seems that the problem has many levels: agriculture and cattle breeding change the social way of life, affect health, lead to the emergence of surpluses, the need to protect them, and become the basis for the division of people into subordinates and elites.Everything also becomes standardized, money easily appears and the temptation to use it to accumulate wealth. The state, in our understanding, is ideal for such conditions: money, control, population growth.<br />And I discuss this within the framework of classical history. If we take into account that certain “gods” taught or forced people to do this, that agriculture appeared in different regions almost simultaneously, everything becomes even clearer. Grain and vineyards ideally fit into this picture, which make it possible to make beer and wine - light alcohol, which is necessary for the “gods”.<br />Those who were not directly given this knowledge received it from their neighbors. Something seemed “prestigious”, something promised benefits in trade, military operations, and simply in the idea of power.<br /><br /><b>P.S. 1</b>. Many North American Indians grew vegetables, roots, berries, and herbs; except for some nomadic tribes. It&#039;s similar to the agrarian type of life, but it seemed more natural. As a result, people lived in communities, without large cities. It is not surprising that the Europeans tried to force farming on the Indians - and many resisted this for a long time. “Our civilization” very accurately noticed the difference in lifestyle and tried to impose itself.<br /><b>P.S. 2</b>. Maybe I&#039;m wrong, but it seemed to me that there were many beneficial aspects to the agricultural lifestyle. Probably it’s a matter of ordinary dualism, when everything has pros and cons. But in the case of humanity, the problem is that the elite have the advantages, and the subordinates have the disadvantages.Stocking up is great. But when they can be taken away, when you are forced to make supplies for others, this is bad. Reducing aggression is also not a problem. The tribes lived in close groups, in their circle people valued each other; They showed aggression towards strangers. The world on Earth will be beautiful if we also perceive strangers well. But in our case, we are subordinated to a faceless system, there are no tribal relations, everyone is for himself, there is no sense of security, and we simply do not have time to think about who rules us.<br /><br />Thanks again everyone!<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"\" data-quote=\"\" data-source=\"\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \"><span style=\"font-size: 9px\">Google Translate:</span><br /><span style=\"font-family: 'arial'\"><span style=\"font-size: 9px\">Изучил основные ответы про аграрное питание и сельское хозяйство. Всем спасибо, было познавательно!<br />Похоже, проблема имеет много уровней: земледелие и скотоводство меняют социальный образ жизни, влияют на здоровье, приводят к появлению излишков, необходимости их защищать, становятся основой разделения людей на подчинённых и элиту. Всё также становится стандартизованным, легко появляются деньги и соблазн их использовать для накопления богатств. Государство в нашем понимании идеально подходит для таких условий: деньги, контроль, рост популяции.<br />И это я рассуждаю в рамках классической истории. Если же учесть, что некие «боги» обучили или принудили людей к этому, что сельское хозяйство появилось в разных регионах почти одномоментно, всё становится ещё понятней. В эту картину идеально попадают зерновые и виноградники, которые позволяют делать пиво и вино – лёгкий алкоголь, который необходим «богам».<br />Кому прямо не передали этих знаний, те получили их от соседей. Что-то показалось «престижным», что-то сулило выгоды в торговле, военных действиях, да и просто в идее власти.<br />P.S.<br />Многие индейцы Северной Америки выращивали овощи, корнеплоды, ягоды и травы; кроме некоторых кочевых племён. Это похоже на аграрный тип жизни, но он был словно более естественный. В итоге люди жили общинами, без крупных городов. Неудивительно, что европейцы пытались навязать индейцам фермерство – и многие этому долгое время противились. «Наша цивилизация» очень точно подметила разницу в образе жизни и пыталась навязать именно самое себя.<br />P.S. 2.<br />Может, я не прав, но мне показалось, что у аграрного образа жизни много полезных сторон. Наверное, дело в обычном дуализме, когда у всего есть плюсы и минусы. Но в случае человечества проблема в том, плюсы у элиты, а минусы у подчинённых. Делать запасы – это здорово. Но когда их могут отнять, когда тебя заставляют делать запасы для других, - это плохо. Понижение агрессии – тоже не проблема. Племена жили тесными группами, в своем кругу люди дорожили друг другом; агрессию они проявляли к чужакам. Мир на Земле будет красивым, если чужака мы будем воспринимать тоже хорошо. Но в нашем случае мы подчинены безликой системе, родоплеменных отношений нет, каждый сам за себя, нет чувства безопасности, и у нас просто нет времени задуматься над тем, кто нами правит.<br />Ещё раз всем спасибо!</span></span></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":9854,"user":"oli 518","date":"2024-02-22T02:03:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-02-02T17:51:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17281,"user":"Aylen","date":"2024-01-30T22:11:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":118,"user":"annp","date":"2024-01-27T02:15:52+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":8800,"user":"SMM","date":"2024-01-26T07:44:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2292,"user":"Aeneas","date":"2024-01-25T19:51:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2556,"user":"clerck de bonk","date":"2024-01-25T15:00:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18380,"user":"Alix","date":"2024-01-25T13:39:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11429,"user":"trytofly","date":"2024-01-25T12:14:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":91,"user":"1984","date":"2024-01-25T11:51:11+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-01-25T05:44:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-01-25T02:29:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":27,"user":"Beau","date":"2024-01-25T01:59:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17316,"user":"KaWaiAwaAwa","date":"2024-01-25T01:55:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18632,"user":"Bernardo GA","date":"2024-01-25T01:31:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16791,"user":"Benjamin","date":"2024-01-25T01:19:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-01-25T00:34:16+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4717,"user":"Jones","date":"2024-01-24T23:37:07+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5393,"user":"sbeaudry","date":"2024-01-24T23:22:33+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11382,"user":"Odin","date":"2024-01-24T23:21:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-01-24T19:47:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-24T18:59:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-01-24T18:16:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13630,"user":"Stella Marys","date":"2024-01-24T17:52:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-01-24T17:30:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3140,"user":"Bluefyre","date":"2024-01-24T16:56:49+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-01-24T16:25:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-24T16:18:53+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17354,"user":"Liliea","date":"2024-01-24T16:02:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-01-24T15:27:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-01-24T15:20:51+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","id":1157808,"date":"2024-01-24T15:52:20+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17563\" data-quote=\"cosmo_alex\" data-source=\"post: 1157799\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1157799\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1157799\">cosmo_alex said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \"><b>P.S. 2</b>. Maybe I&#039;m wrong, but it seemed to me that there were many beneficial aspects to the agricultural lifestyle. Probably it’s a matter of ordinary dualism, when everything has pros and cons. But in the case of humanity, the problem is that the elite have the advantages, and the subordinates have the disadvantages.Stocking up is great. But when they can be taken away, when you are forced to make supplies for others, this is bad. Reducing aggression is also not a problem. <b>The tribes lived in close groups, in their circle people valued each other; They showed aggression towards strangers.</b> The world on Earth will be beautiful if we also perceive strangers well. But in our case, we are subordinated to a faceless system, there are no tribal relations, everyone is for himself, there is no sense of security, and we simply do not have time to think about who rules us.<br /><br />Thanks again everyone!</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />This isn&#039;t always the case in Native cultures. Although there are widespread accounts of slavery, cannibalism, head-hunting and brutal tortures directed towards other tribes, there is also evidence of the ever-present problem of evil at play within tribes themselves. There looks to be plenty of evidence of &#039;secret societies&#039; or cults within Native tribes that terrorized their own people. <br /><br />There are a series of posts discussing this in detail, featuring a great synopsis of Hayden&#039;s book <i>The Power of Ritual in Prehistory: Secret Societies and Origins of Social Complexity, </i>starting here:<br /><br /><i><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"196658\" data-url=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/the-once-and-future-sky-god-from-goebekli-tepe-to-the-zodiac-and-beyond.52093/post-1049718\" data-host=\"cassiopaea.org\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/img/FB_sky.jpg\" alt=\"cassiopaea.org\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/the-once-and-future-sky-god-from-goebekli-tepe-to-the-zodiac-and-beyond.52093/post-1049718\"class=\"link link--internal fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"\"rel=\"\"data-proxy-href=\"\">THE ONCE AND FUTURE SKY GOD? – From Göbekli Tepe to The Zodiac – and Beyond…</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">This is a truly amazing and detailed series. So much research combined with your ability to bring it across so eloquently and precise is a gift that I thank you for giving me. Each post that you bring to the thread is eagerly awaited and makes so much sense. :-):flowers:</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/styles/cass/img/favicon.png\" alt=\"cassiopaea.org\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>cassiopaea.org</div></div></div></div></i><br />For some people there is a sort of pervasive &#039;longing for the village&#039; or &#039;longing for the tribe&#039; that accompanies the alienation, individualism and nihilism of the West&#039;s post-modern culture. I&#039;ve felt it myself. This was based on my somewhat naive idealization of the past, and Native people, also assumptions of what I thought authentic village life might be like. While there are some great values and good stories from Native cultures, I&#039;ve been learning that the past is far more complex and mysterious than I had originally thought, and that village life was no paradise.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":19148,"user":"Happy Poo","date":"2024-02-16T09:01:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-02-02T17:52:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7597,"user":"hiker","date":"2024-01-31T20:31:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17284,"user":"ELT","date":"2024-0