er":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-28T17:19:09+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":6263,"user":"DreamGod","id":1158796,"date":"2024-01-28T21:24:18+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Q: (L) So the reason they&#039;re concerned or interested is because nukes can break dimensional barriers?<br /><br />A: Yes<br /><br />Q: (L) And those barriers can be not just between horizontal dimensions, but between densities?<br /><br />A: Yes<br /><br />Q: (L) And also is it true that that energy can go into those other densities or dimensions and cause damage there?<br /><br />A: Yes</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Great Session, Thanks!<br /><br />When a nuke explode, it creates a &quot;mini sun&quot; like ball of energy (not fire); C&#039;s said that all stars are portals and planets are windows, something like that, so the point is: When a nuke explodes maybe it opens a portal for a time, like a &quot;mini sun&quot;, and that mess with other realms and let things enter in ours.<br /><br />Just a thought.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":3936,"user":"Andrian","date":"2024-02-07T18:09:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":203,"user":"thorbiorn","date":"2024-02-06T12:17:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16791,"user":"Benjamin","date":"2024-02-04T20:43:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":12854,"user":"Tuulikki","date":"2024-02-04T10:21:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-02-03T2