,"reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-01-29T19:10:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-01-29T18:32:15+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6164,"user":"Jefferson","date":"2024-01-29T18:22:57+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":15488,"user":"N1mTzo","id":1159024,"date":"2024-01-29T20:36:35+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 3193\" data-quote=\"seek10\" data-source=\"post: 1158933\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1158933\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1158933\">seek10 said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">The timing of Barabar caves are attributed to Mauryan emperor Ashoka&#039;s period (261 BC) because of some inscriptions of his time. This appropriation of the old monuments by the emperors is nothing new. But unfortunately it is<a href=\"https://www.historicmysteries.com/barabar-caves/\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"> hard to prove the dates</a>.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Most likely, the “official dating” is nonsense and these caves are hundreds (if not thousands) older than Buddhism/Hinduism.<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 3193\" data-quote=\"seek10\" data-source=\"post: 1158933\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1158933\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1158933\">seek10 said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">If Barabar caves are done by 4D STS what about Lot complex structures at Ajanta and Ellora caves which contains monuments of Buddhists and Hindus?.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Recycling/reuse of these ancient sites by Buddhists/Hindus. Please note that nowhere on these structures are there any inscriptions from the original builders. But there are crooked scribbles of Hindus on perfect blocks of granite (or other types of stone). This is found everywhere in Antiquity (Greece/Turkey/Lebanon (Baalbek), etc.) - on ideal stone megaliths there are crooked Hellenic/Roman inscriptions, they could hardly draw a few crooked symbols on the ancient buildings of the gods!<br />By the way, note that the Ajanta caves are located along a river called Waghora (sounds similar to Angkor Wat - in Cambodia - a place of worship of reptilian 4D STS). Waghora River/Water of Angkor<br /><br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 3193\" data-quote=\"seek10\" data-source=\"post: 1158933\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1158933\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1158933\">seek10 said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">That is (4098BCE to 1071 BCE). The end of it coincides with 1100 BCE comet impact (End of Bronze age) that became for the inspiration of Mahabharat and Illiad and the creators obviously used elements of very old stories for posterity. Probably these Troy stories are carried to Greece by these &quot;Sea people&quot;</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Most likely, there have been several such cometary “passages” since the time of Akhenaten (as the starting point for the emergence of monotheism), not only 1100 BC (and later there were also comets/tsunamis/volcanoes, etc.!). There were migrations/transfers of peoples to other regions and complete devastation of some places (which were repopulated after a long time without people). In Greece/Turkey (Tunisia, Egypt, Cambodia) many megalithic temples are buried 10 meters deep in clay. Some temples were partially excavated during Hellenic/Roman times and reused by these peoples.<br /><br />PS Regarding the secondary “population” of temples, there is a good photo from Cambodia (Angkor):<br /><a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/attachments/2024-01-29_222415-jpg.90876/\"target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/data/attachments/74/74039-e1bfb58876c585182637590962aaa385.jpg\"class=\"bbImage \"style=\"\"alt=\"2024-01-29_222415.JPG\"title=\"2024-01-29_222415.JPG\"width=\"179\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" /></a><br /><br />A warehouse of “Buddha” and Naga statues (a small building), covered with clay to the very top and dug up by restorers in the 21st century.<br />There are also “warehouses” of lingas (Hindu) in Ankor.<br />When new religions came, they simply removed the old idols and built (rebuilt) their temples on the site of ancient megalithic structures.<br />So you had Walmart, but a new owner came in, changed the sign, and now you have Costco/Target.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-02-07T17:38:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2556,"user":"clerck de bonk","date":"2024-02-06T12:26:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5393,"user":"sbeaudry","date":"2024-02-05T18:41:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16791,"user":"Benjamin","date":"2024-02-04T21:07:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3863,"user":"findit","date":"2024-02-03T21:25:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3628,"user":"mantle","date":"2024-02-02T12:43:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":45