d:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">I think having specifics places would be the wrong approach, since we wouldn&#039;t know about Iraq or Iran if they didn&#039;t ask specifically, perhaps Russia is where most of the people genetically speaking carry the Semite gen, but there could be lots of countries where there are people who are Semites, Maybe the clue relies on countries where the US has been in perpetual conflict with perhaps? Or there has been cruel wars in the past where lost of the population of a specific country suffered/died.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>My question is based few assumptions. first assumption is  Palestinians in Middle East are Semites, so they have wipeout program and There are many Semites all over the world though individual basis all over the world.   <br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Q: (seek10) C&#039;s mentioned 4D STS aim is to eliminate &#039;True Semites&#039; before the transition. Is the current and recent past Palestinian resistance to Israel the result of &quot;True Semitic&quot; gene type?<br /><br />A: Partly in so far as any of them carry it.<br /><br />Q: (L) Are you saying that Palestinians may not be Semitic, or only partly Semitic?<br /><br />A: Yes<br /><br />Q: (L) I think we once established that the Semites were something quite different from what we call them today, so that we can&#039;t necessarily say that Palestinians are Semitic, or even that the Jews are Semitic.<br /><br />(Joe) Is there a <b>significant concentration </b>of people anywhere in the world that carries that Semitic gene that they&#039;re talking about?<br /><br />A: Yes.<br /><br />(Gaby) Where?<br /><br />(Niall) Or who?<br /><br />A: Russia.<br /><br />Q: (Joe) Not your average &quot;Semites&quot;...</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>But it looks few in Palestinians are really Semite. And In fact very few across the world are Semites (considering the small population of  Iraq, Iran and Russia with significant concentration. I suspect  that small groups in this small population may be semite).  The second question is logical extension to the first question.<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">(seek10) The current War seems to be focused in Middle East. Do they have other plans for &quot;True Semites&quot; in other regions like in West or East other than vaccine framework?<br /><br />A: <b>Review knowledge</b> and <b>re-ask </b>in different form.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>At this point, I don&#039;t what knowledge to review, but It looks I need to re-ask. So As usual, we will find out what that is in future.  I have few books in my pipeline (for a year) to read about culture of few Islamic countries (including Iran) and wondered it may be