ll popular in South East Asia continent, it is this 50KYA migration of Parathas. <br /><a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/attachments/1707710724978-png.91530/\"target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/data/attachments/74/74693-0b97c1204e99e21606775c3f5e581189.jpg\"class=\"bbImage \"style=\"\"alt=\"1707710724978.png\"title=\"1707710724978.png\"width=\"100\" height=\"207\" loading=\"lazy\" /></a><br /><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genetics_and_archaeogenetics_of_South_Asia#\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"><b>Genetics and archaeogenetics of South Asia</b></a><br /><a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/attachments/migraciones_humanas_en_haplogrupos_de_adn-y-png.91531/\"target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/data/attachments/74/74694-d610b251831705be2e124438b6d22b8c.jpg\"class=\"bbImage \"style=\"\"alt=\"Migraciones_humanas_en_haplogrupos_de_ADN-Y.png\"title=\"Migraciones_humanas_en_haplogrupos_de_ADN-Y.png\"width=\"195\" height=\"100\" loading=\"lazy\" /></a>","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-02-28T21:36:28+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17284,"user":"ELT","date":"2024-02-13T10:38:16+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-02-13T01:31:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16791,"user":"Benjamin","date":"2024-02-12T23:45:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-02-12T23:07:06+0100","reaction":"Love"},{"user_id":11382,"user":"Odin","date":"2024-02-12T21:32:28+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15488,"user":"N1mTzo","date":"2024-02-12T19:28:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10829,"user":"Jtucker","date":"2024-02-12T17:12:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10595,"user":"Korzik18","date":"2024-02-12T15:42:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15533,"user":"Deliverance","date":"2024-02-12T13:56:38+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-02-12T12:50:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7509,"user":"candasiri","date":"2024-02-12T11:55:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-02-12T11:24:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-02-12T10:17:42+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4163,"user":"Eboard10","date":"2024-02-12T08:44:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15484,"user":"Olivierlejardinier","date":"2024-02-12T07:57:28+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-02-12T06:25:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14324,"user":"Candice","date":"2024-02-12T06:19:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-02-12T05:24:32+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":13515,"user":"KJS","id":1161582,"date":"2024-02-12T13:53:05+0100","text":"It sounds very Disease X-ish; someone should call Dr. Drosten:<br /><div class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--unfurl    js-unfurl fauxBlockLink\"data-unfurl=\"true\" data-result-id=\"198212\" data-url=\"https://news.yahoo.com/man-dies-lufthansa-flight-coughing-094328380.html\" data-host=\"news.yahoo.com\" data-pending=\"false\"><div class=\"contentRow\"><div class=\"contentRow-figure contentRow-figure--fixedSmall js-unfurl-figure\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.zenfs.com%2Fen%2Fthe_independent_635%2Ff423df39481992d27ac6037abf41e3a4&amp;hash=b542dc717dd32dd3eabb28eafc8d9b65&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"news.yahoo.com\" data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></div><div class=\"contentRow-main\"><h3 class=\"contentRow-header js-unfurl-title\"><a href=\"https://news.yahoo.com/man-dies-lufthansa-flight-coughing-094328380.html\"class=\"link link--external fauxBlockLink-blockLink\"target=\"_blank\"rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\"data-proxy-href=\"\">Man dies on Lufthansa flight after coughing up ‘litres of blood’ from mouth and nose</a></h3><div class=\"contentRow-snippet js-unfurl-desc\">Fellow passenger described ‘absolute horror’ of mid-air incident</div><div class=\"contentRow-minor contentRow-minor--hideLinks\"><span class=\"js-unfurl-favicon\"><img src=\"/forum/proxy.php?image=https%3A%2F%2Fs.yimg.com%2Frz%2Fl%2Ffavicon.ico&amp;hash=9a4055d89869f4195f05195f164e81a1&amp;return_error=1\" alt=\"news.yahoo.com\" class=\"bbCodeBlockUnfurl-icon\"data-onerror=\"hide-parent\"/></span>news.yahoo.com</div></div></div></div><blockquote data-attributes=\"\" data-quote=\"\" data-source=\"\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \"><h3>Man dies on Lufthansa flight after coughing up ‘litres of blood’ from mouth and nose&#8203;</h3>A 63-year-old man has died after coughing up “litres of blood” on a Lufthansa flight from Bangkok to Munich.<br /><br />Flight LH773 was scheduled to depart Bangkok for the Bavarian capital at 11.40pm on Thursday 8 February.<br /><br />After 90 minutes in the air, however, the plane was forced to turn around after a German national was pronounced dead onboard.<br /><br />According to a fellow passenger, the man lost litres of blood through his mouth and nose. “It was absolute horror, everyone was screaming,” said Karin Missfelder, who was situated in the row diagonally behind the passenger.<br /><br />Ms Missfelder, a nursing specialist at University Hospital in Zurich immediately noticed her fellow passenger’s poor health upon boarding.<br /><br />“He had cold sweats, was breathing much too quickly, and was already apathetic,” she told Swiss news outlet Blick.<br /><br />The man’s Filipina wife explained that the pair had run to the plane very quickly, which is why he wasn’t feeling well.<br /><br />At this stage, the nurse intervened and said that the passenger needed medical attention, prompting the captain to call for a doctor over the loudspeaker.<br /><br />“A young, around 30-year-old man from Poland with poor English looked at the German,” she said, but only felt his pulse and asked how he was feeling.<br /><br />“They then gave him a little chamomile tea, but he [had] already spit blood into the bag that his wife held out to him,” she said.<br /><br />Despite the escalating situation, the decision was made by airport officials to depart.<br /><br />As the plane became airborne, the man’s condition worsened dramatically and blood began gushing out of his mouth and nose. “The man lost litres of blood,” she said.<br /><br />Flight stewards immediately began resuscitation, to no avail, and the man was carried into the galley and a decision was made to return to Bangkok.<br /><br />The captain announced over the loudspeaker that the passenger had sadly died.<br /><br />Despite the ordeal that passengers had witnessed, Ms Missfelder’s husband, Martin, described the situation back at Bangkok Airport as chaotic. “Nobody looked after us, we waited two hours. There was no care team there, nobody,” he said.<br /><br />He said the worst thing was that the wife of the deceased passenger then had to proceed through customs alone. “She stood there all alone and apathetic and had to endure all the formalities.”<br /><br />“The fact that Lufthansa has no measures in his case, that no one cares about around 30 traumatised passengers around, is unacceptable.”<br /><br />In a statement to The Independent, a Lufthansa representative confirmed that “a medical emergency” had occurred on the flight. “Although immediate and comprehensive first aid measures were taken by the crew and a doctor on board, the passenger died during the flight.<br /><br />“After 1.5 hours of flight time, the crew decided to turn back to Bangkok, where the aircraft landed normally and safely. There, the instructions of the medical emergency services and the Thai authorities were followed.<br /><br />“The passengers on the cancelled flight have since been rebooked on other flights. Our thoughts are with the relatives of the deceased passenger. We also regret the inconvenience caused to the passengers of this flight.”<br /><br />Lufthansa did not respond when pressed on the decision to depart Bangkok in spite of the man’s failing health.<br /><br />The news comes as service has resumed after the German flag carrier cancelled hundreds of flights from the country’s major airports following a 27-hour strike by ground staff.<br /><br />Members of the Ver.di union walked out at five major German airports on Wednesday 7 February in a dispute over pay.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />Edit:<br />Sorry, I overlooked the previous mention of this. It&#039;s all over the news now.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-02-28T21:39:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-02-24T22:32:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16791,"user":"Benjamin","date":"2024-02-12T23:47:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-02-12T23:10:30+0100","reaction":"Sad"},{"user_id":17354,"user":"Liliea","date":"2024-02-12T22:25:41+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11382,"user":"Odin","date":"2024-02-12T21:32:54+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-02-12T20:13:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10829,"user":"Jtucker","date":"2024-02-12T17:13:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-02-12T15:54:52+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10595,"user":"Korzik18","date":"2024-02-12T15:42:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-02-12T15:18:22+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7850,"user":"Ðekel","date":"2024-02-12T14:59:41+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-02-12T14:48:47+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-02-12T14:48:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2556,"user":"clerck de bonk","date":"2024-02-12T14:33:25+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":3193,"user":"seek10","id":1161613,"date":"2024-02-12T16:25:49+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 3193\" data-quote=\"seek10\" data-source=\"post: 1161467\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1161467\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1161467\">seek10 said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Cayce description as mentioned <a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/atlantis.14160/post-1150230\" class=\"link link--internal\">here</a> seems to focus in Atlantic ocean( As he responding to the query of a specific person&#039;s incarnation in <span style=\"color: rgb(184, 49, 47)\">pacific ocean</span>). It is quite possible, war happened in different fronts with Northern Kantekaneans and India happens to be one area where nuclear weapons were used.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>I mean to say &#039;Atlantics Ocean&#039; not pacific ocean. sorry for that.<br /><br />Any way, there are some more factors validate this 50 KYA parantha extinction event and its relation to Rama. C&#039;s Already said Rama is after the War.<br />- The migration path towards South East Asia where Ramayan is widely popular( but not Mahabharat) including Angkhor Wat. It is considered Indian colonies of first millennium in South East Asia responsible for the spread of Hinduism. This migration path from India to South East Asia and to Australia makes it a fertile ground for the spread of so called &quot;Hinduism&quot; (with Ramayan) in the early first millennium. This line of thought makes 50KYA, not 2KYA<br /><br />Some more thoughts on some previous C&#039;s comments:<br />s-1994-10-16<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"\" data-quote=\"\" data-source=\"\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Q: (L) What is the origin of the<b> books of Enoch</b>?<br /><br />A:<b> Sanskritian society in area now referred to as India.</b><br /><br />Q: (L) What evaluation can we give the books of Enoch as far as level of truth?<br /><br />A: 50% of area was destroyed in nuclear conflagration in between<br /><br />Q: (L) In between what?<br /><br />A: Then and now in the expanded present.<br /><br /><b>Q: (L) What is the &quot;expanded&quot; present?<br /><br />A: The real measure of time.</b></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>I wondered how to interpret this &quot;expanded&quot; present.  This Sanskrit society in India is before 50KYA Nuclear War. How far back this <i>Book of Enoch</i> was written? Is it before entry of Kantek folks or after? Any further approximation I can narrow down to?<br /><br /> - Why do an &quot;expanded&quot; Present needs to exist if every thing is in linear timelines.  4D STS has time travel capabilities and C&#039;s mentioned that they are being playing with timelines since 80KYA. They are changing timelines since then. So For the intelligences (above 3D) they see multiple timelines. Though our linear mind go crazy with multi timelines, for 4D and above they must have certain methods ( algorithms and approximations) to represent multiple timelines in a specific graph that 3D humans can understand it by labeling &quot;Expanded&quot; Present. The reality with timelines should be ridiculously LOT more complex than this. <br /><div style=\"margin-left: 20px\"><ul><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">To make simplistic guess( w.r.t timeline changes),  there is a timeline changes after Kantek destruction 80 KYA before 50KYA( that&#039;s why C&#039;s mentioned the date of 80KYA).  That makes timeline of Sanskrit Society that wrote Book of Enoch before 80KYA. </li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">But, that comes with a BIG caveat.  Indian plate is not even at the current location 70KYA back.  It is floating some where in the Indian Ocean ( or part of Pangea) between 70KYA ( simplistic guess) at the time of <i> Book of Enoch </i>writing (before 80KYA).<ul><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">C&#039;s say planet went in to 4D around 70KYA (temporarily) where lithosphere is malleable that makes it easy breaking of it and forming the new continental plates and breaking. <ul><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">But when something goes into  4D and comes back to 3D,  will it come back exactly same orientation?  Related to missing 411 people cases, coming back from other densities/dimensions, orientations can get flipped.  But  here we are talking about large scale planets, will that happen? Probably not.  The entire <a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/atlantis.14160/post-1151564\" class=\"link link--internal\">continental drift theory</a> is based on patterns of fossils across different plates before separation.  So Indian plate was floating around pacific ocean or as a part of Pangea before 70KYA and some Sanskrit society living in it, who wrote &#039;<i>Book of Enoch</i>&#039;. that leads to few more question.<ul><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">I am not still convinced that pangea is one continent before 70KYA. It is too odd given the billion years history of life on the planet. Some other mechanism must have been there, which we don&#039;t know yet. But, I will go with the line of thought that there is a once continent called Pangea before 70KYA.</li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">Did Parantha&#039;s live on the land before 80KYA?<ul><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">If Paranthas lived on Indian plate before 80KYA, Did they use Sanskrit? It has to be as C&#039;s used the word &#039;Sanskritian Society&#039;</li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">But, the current Dravidian and Australasian languages  are very different from Sanskrit, though there are many mixing of words.<ul><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">Did the language change happened after 50KYA nuclear War? It was mentioned in the recent C&#039;s sessions, language can change hands(or mouths) and we can&#039;t trace it back races based on the language. </li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></li></ul></div><b>Why is it necessary to know about it now?</b><br /><br />In the modern Indian politics of  so-called &quot;left&quot; vs &quot;right&quot;, there is a battle of historical interpretation going on.  Though Modi&#039;s &quot;Right&quot; seems to have won the battle of economic  rejuvenation through reforming/motivating the bureaucracy (that stuck to &quot;entitled&quot; East India Company/British Days mindset, which Nehru-Gandhi failed to correct it)  and sanctified that with building of Rama temple (promoting it as &quot;new era&quot; and some even dub it as &quot;Rama Rajya&quot;) and all stage is set for Modi 3.0 <br /><br />Every new thing needs an new identity that is different from old to delineate it for electoral purposes. People are selfish by nature, pick it up according to their temperaments and Truth tends to be the first victim.  <br /><br />Indian &quot;Right&quot; try to use the term it &quot;Sanatana Dharma&quot;. Sanatana means &quot;eternal&quot;.  How old is old? What does it even mean by eternal?  Does the world or people&#039;s need doesn&#039;t change for ever?<br /><br />The answers to these questions tend to fall flat. They talk about same old 1500 BCE Rigveda, Aryans ( aka &quot;noble&quot;), Aryavartha (land of Aryas), BharataVarsha (land of  tribal chief Bharat in the current day Afghanistan and so on) and &quot;manusmriti&quot; (nutcase social hierarchy created by same Aryan Brahmins in the battle against Buddhists) . They make things up as they go.<br /><br />The assumption, as per British Indology (that started as a necessary furniture of Empire), Veda&#039;s are written in old Sanskrit by Aryan tribes invading India and they created so-called &quot;Hinduism&quot; where Rama plays important role. There is no data related to whoever exist there (aka current south Indian/Dravidian/Descendants of Paranthas) are inconsequential.  C&#039;s seems to be saying the complete opposite.<br /><div style=\"margin-left: 20px\"><ul><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">Vedas are written by &quot;descendants&quot; of Paranthas.  i.e. those who survived destruction of 50% of India ( aka North India destroyed 50KYA) where F haplogroup spread out happened to other areas.  It is South India as C&#039;s already mentioned these descendants  who wrote Vedas.</li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">It was written in Sanskrit. That doesn&#039;t mean it was there in India in Sanskrit.</li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">Aryans ( aka Kantekaneans) are &quot;outsiders&quot; came 4  times in different advanced weapons of the time .<ul><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">50KYA with Nuclear weapons</li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">8KYA with agriculture</li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">3.5 KYA with horses (supposed Rigvedic gang). All the appropriation</li><li data-xf-list-type=\"ul\">250 Years ago with &quot;Naval Power&quot;.</li></ul></li></ul></div>All this looks like a &quot;time loop&quot; or Atlantean reincarnation dance. <br /><br />Crux of the problem is  the &quot;Sanatana Dharma&quot; gang ( or Right wing or nationalist) who talk about <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indigenous_Aryanism\" target=\"_blank\" class=\"link link--external\" rel=\"nofollow ugc noopener\">&quot;Indigenous Aryanism&quot; </a>(Aka Out of India theory), can&#039;t even get that they themselves are outsiders. This is what &quot;Left&quot; trying to say (though their theories can&#039;t go beyond 3.6 KYA), but has to shut up due to their economic failures of the past.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-02-29T17:32:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-02-28T21:40:21+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-02-25T01:55:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13936,"user":"Cristal","date":"2024-02-15T16:39:43+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-02-13T06:53:45+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":9839,"user":"Jo Bugman","date":"2024-02-13T01:37:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-02-12T23:17:42+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":17354,"user":"Liliea","date":"2024-02-12T22:34:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15488,"user":"N1mTzo","date":"2024-02-12T19:36:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-02-12T18:58:51+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16915,"user":"Jebra","date":"2024-02-12T18:54:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-02-12T18:08:32+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13515,"user":"KJS","date":"2024-02-12T17:45:13+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10829,"user":"Jtucker","date":"2024-02-12T17:32:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13701,"user":"Gruchaa","date":"2024-02-12T16:59:59+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7509,"user":"candasiri","date":"2024-02-12T16:41:27+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":679,"user":"Mark7","id":1161667,"date":"2024-02-12T19:53:48+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 14284\" data-quote=\"iamthatis\" data-source=\"post: 1160397\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1160397\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1160397\">iamthatis said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">So maybe heavy water is a mediator of hyperdimensional phenomena in our bodies.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>You can drink it. It makes the body heavier and can be lethal in large amounts. A little bit is enough for psychic stuff I imagine.<br /><div class=\"bbMediaWrapper\" data-media-site-id=\"youtube\" data-media-key=\"VTLhKTi6_G0\"><div class=\"bbMediaWrapper-inner\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/VTLhKTi6_G0?wmode=opaque\"width=\"560\" height=\"315\"frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe></div></div>","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-02-28T21:40:52+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-02-13T06:54:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18714,"user":"Freya Stewart","date":"2024-02-13T05:49:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4527,"user":"Talas","date":"2024-02-12T23:57:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-02-12T23:19:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-02-12T22:29:17+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11382,"user":"Odin","date":"2024-02-12T21:34:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10595,"user":"Korzik18","date":"2024-02-12T20:58:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-02-12T20:46:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-02-12T20:13:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":4518,"user":"Adobe","date":"2024-02-12T20:06:51+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":11868,"user":"Ursus Minor","id":1161697,"date":"2024-02-12T22:19:55+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 14284\" data-quote=\"iamthatis\" data-source=\"post: 1161414\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1161414\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1161414\">iamthatis said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Apparently getting kinzhal&#039;d in the nether regions is taking its toll again. He was taken to hospital for &#039;an emergent bladder issue&#039;.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />You&#039;ve got to hand it to Lloyd Austin, while other war ministers tend to hide at home he went where the action is. He met the Russians and lived to tell...  <img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"🦽\" title=\"Manual wheelchair    :manual_wheelchair:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f9bd.png\" data-shortname=\":manual_wheelchair:\" />","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-02-28T21:44:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-02-13T06:54:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10595,"user":"Korzik18","date":"2024-02-13T05:49:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-02-13T00:33:09+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-02-12T23:19:47+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-02-12T22:29:25+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":15021,"user":"Chrístofir","id":1162180,"date":"2024-02-15T15:51:24+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 19137\" data-quote=\"lindrie\" data-source=\"post: 1160908\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1160908\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1160908\">lindrie said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">I though too much fiber of the wrong kind actually caused intestinal blockage? the body actually can&#039;t process fibers, that&#039;s where the gut flora is supposed comes in but it can only eat so much, I&#039;m sure. I&#039;m still reading through some of the older threads so maybe my info is still out of date? <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/nuts.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":nuts:\" title=\"Nutzoid    :nuts:\" data-shortname=\":nuts:\" /> If anything, one of the things I wanted to try is eat more cucumbers to allow the GI soak up its moisture, I can&#039;t seem to stay hydrated enough with water (liquids) alone. I can&#039;t quite tell if its working because I get full way too quickly!</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Thanks for your input! In the case of zeolite, from that experience I shared earlier in this thread,<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 15021\" data-quote=\"Chrístofir\" data-source=\"post: 1160756\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1160756\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1160756\">Chrístofir said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">It was eight years ago, and I remember following instructions which came with the zeolite. Don&#039;t have the instructions anylonger. But I do know where I went wrong hehe<br /><br />If I remember correctly it was supposed to be a five-day-cure, but I only got to Day 3... About the amount of water - plenty! The zeolite needs to be flushed properly. It has an excellent ability to absorb whatever is in the intestines, but it&#039;s not supposed to be staying there. So don&#039;t be stingy on the water!<br /><br />If I was to do another cure today, I&#039;d start out with a tiny amount of zeolite, and lots of water through-out the day. All in all, follow the advice of iyan above.<br /><br />I did a <a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/search/531538/?q=zeolite&amp;o=date\" class=\"link link--internal\">search for &quot;zeolite&quot;</a> in the forum and there seems to be bits of info here and there, so do try to see if you can find more info that might come in handy. <img src=\"/forum/styles/cass/smilies/thumbup.gif\"  class=\"smilie\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\":thup:\" title=\"Thumbs up    :thup:\" data-shortname=\":thup:\" /></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />I&#039;d defnitely discourage from using too much of fibers while on a zeolite regime. The zeolite needs all help it can get to be &quot;flushed&quot; through the intestines, and not to be encouraged to get stuck in (as in my case) intestinal pockets, thus causing constipation. <img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"☺️\" title=\"Smiling face    :relaxed:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/263a.png\" data-shortname=\":relaxed:\" /> Also I believe one should make sure not to engage in too much of sedentary activities during the zeolite regime. Instead try to be more physically active in order to proactively encourage bowel movements.<br /><br />Thank You! <img class=\"smilie smilie--emoji\" loading=\"lazy\" alt=\"🙏\" title=\"Folded hands    :pray:\" src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/joypixels/assets/8.0/png/unicode/64/1f64f.png\" data-shortname=\":pray:\" />","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-02-29T17:51:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-02-28T21:45:58+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-02-25T04:37:14+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-02-24T18:43:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":1533,"user":"Debra","date":"2024-02-24T18:09:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":2877,"user":"Mayb","date":"2024-02-16T22:46:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18714,"user":"Freya Stewart","date":"2024-02-16T02:03:28+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-02-15T20:01:56+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10595,"user":"Korzik18","date":"2024-02-15T17:57:29+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-02-15T17:02:26+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-02-15T16:04:06+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":17664,"user":"Pluchi","id":1162214,"date":"2024-02-15T18:36:04+0100","text":"What a wonderful, illuminating session!<br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17\" data-quote=\"Laura\" data-source=\"post: 1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1155572\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1155572\">Laura said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">Q: (Joe) Exactly. You have to know that it&#039;s happening to resist it.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>Thank you, Joe, for these words. I will borrow them, as they clearly show the importance of awareness.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":17406,"user":"Pat","date":"2024-04-24T20:29:57+0200","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":18193,"user":"wilfried","date":"2024-02-29T17:51:36+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-02-28T21:46:19+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":546,"user":"GRiM","date":"2024-02-28T04:25:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-02-25T04:37:21+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-02-24T18:11:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-02-16T07:25:39+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11403,"user":"Sylvia","date":"2024-02-16T04:37:00+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17281,"user":"Aylen","date":"2024-02-15T23:00:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6164,"user":"Jefferson","date":"2024-02-15T22:10:02+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11382,"user":"Odin","date":"2024-02-15T19:19:50+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-02-15T19:02:30+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-02-15T18:55:56+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":882,"user":"latulipenoire","id":1162216,"date":"2024-02-15T18:37:31+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 17664\" data-quote=\"Pluchi\" data-source=\"post: 1162214\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1162214\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1162214\">Pluchi said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">What a wonderful, illuminating session!<br /><br />Thank you, Joe, for these words. I will borrow them, as they clearly show the importance of awareness.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote><br />Ditto to that! Thank you again for everything!","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":17406,"user":"Pat","date":"2024-04-24T20:30:06+0200","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-02-28T21:46:25+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-02-25T04:37:24+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-02-24T18:11:48+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-02-16T07:25:44+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17281,"user":"Aylen","date":"2024-02-15T23:00:08+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":6164,"user":"Jefferson","date":"2024-02-15T22:10:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11382,"user":"Odin","date":"2024-02-15T19:19:53+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11699,"user":"Kay Kim","date":"2024-02-15T19:02:46+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7284,"user":"Don Cesar","date":"2024-02-15T18:56:01+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_id":3193,"user":"seek10","id":1163813,"date":"2024-02-24T18:01:33+0100","text":"<blockquote data-attributes=\"member: 3\" data-quote=\"Approaching Infinity\" data-source=\"post: 1158017\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-title\"><a href=\"/forum/goto/post?id=1158017\"class=\"bbCodeBlock-sourceJump\"rel=\"nofollow\"data-xf-click=\"attribution\"data-content-selector=\"#post-1158017\">Approaching Infinity said:</a></div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">I believe it was in interviews, maybe also in his <i>America Before</i> book. But one of the arguments I&#039;m pretty sure he&#039;s made is that civilizations tend to always congregate by coastlines and major sources of water. And there is so much land that is now underwater that if they were occupied, it&#039;s understandable that there aren&#039;t that many available remains on land today.</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>There are some text in Cayce&#039;s writings seems to suggest there is a technological necessity for Atlantean as a coastline society. From <br />ATLANTIS Vol. 1 (page 13) mentioned <a href=\"https://cassiopaea.org/forum/threads/atlantis.14160/post-1158085\" class=\"link link--internal\">here</a>. <br /><blockquote data-attributes=\"\" data-quote=\"\" data-source=\"\"class=\"bbCodeBlock bbCodeBlock--expandable bbCodeBlock--quote js-expandWatch\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-content\"><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandContent js-expandContent \">“. . . in the Atlantean land when there were the preparations of those things that  had pertained to the ability for the application of appliances to the various elements known as electrical forces in the present day; as to the manners and ways in which the <b>various crafts carried individuals from place to place, and what may be known in the present as the photographing from a distance, or the fields of activity that showed the ability for reading inscriptions through walls - even at distances, or for the preparations of the elevations in the various activities where there was the overcoming of the forces of nature, of gravity itself</b> ; and the preparations through the crystal, the mighty, the terrible crystal that made for the active principles in these, were a portion of the activity of the entity in that experience. Much of it brought destruction. . . .” (No. 519-1)<br /><br />“As indicated, the entity was associated with those that dealt with the mechanical appliances and their application during the experience. And, as we find, it was a period when there was much that has not even been thought of as yet in the present experience.<br /><br />“About the firestone that was in the experience did the activities of the entity then  make those applications that dealt with both the constructive and destructive forces in the period.<br /><br />“It would be well that there be given something of a description of this, that it  may be better understood by the entity in the present, as to how both constructive and destructive forces were generated by the activity of this stone.<br /><br />“It was in the center of a building, that today would be said to have been lined with non-conductive stone - something akin to asbestos - with the combined forces of bakelite or other non-conductors that are now being manufactured in England under a name that is known well to many of those that deal in such things.<br /><br />“<b>The building above the stone was oval, a dome which could be folded back, so that the activity of the stone was received from the sun&#039;s rays, or from the stars; the concentrating of the energies that emanate from bodies that are on fire themselves . . . <br />with the elements that are found and that are not found in the earth&#039;s atmosphere. The concentration, through the prisms or glass, as would be called in the present, was in such a manner that it acted upon the instruments that were connected with the various modes <br />of travel,<span style=\"color: rgb(209, 72, 65)\"> through induction methods</span> . . </b>. that made much the character of control, as the remote control through radio vibrations as would be in the present day; though the manner of force that was impelled from the stone acted upon the motivating forces in the crafts themselves.<br /><br />“There was the preparation so that when the dome was rolled back them might be little or no hindrance in the application<b> direct to the various crafts that were to be impelled through space, whether<span style=\"color: rgb(209, 72, 65)\"> in the radius of the visioning of the one eye</span>, as it might be called, or whether directed under water.</b> .</div><div class=\"bbCodeBlock-expandLink js-expandLink\"><a role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\">Click to expand...</a></div></div></blockquote>It does looks like their crystal technology needs &quot;line of sight&quot; for propelling the vehicles and that may involve lot of energy transfer from source (crystal) to target (ships). Probably that needs less obstructions in the sky and sea is natural choice for it.  i.e.  The current  geographical national boundaries  as location may not be appropriate way to describe the Atlantean  national boundaries. The hunter gatherer societies lived else where- i.e.  inland.","attachments":[],"reactions":[{"user_id":17406,"user":"Pat","date":"2024-04-24T20:33:29+0200","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":5223,"user":"happyliza","date":"2024-02-28T21:50:05+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10829,"user":"Jtucker","date":"2024-02-28T17:10:01+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11382,"user":"Odin","date":"2024-02-28T16:24:47+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14181,"user":"Wandering Star","date":"2024-02-26T15:56:12+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17945,"user":"Claus","date":"2024-02-26T07:28:34+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11403,"user":"Sylvia","date":"2024-02-26T04:54:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":3,"user":"Approaching Infinity","date":"2024-02-25T17:07:23+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":10482,"user":"Hindsight Man","date":"2024-02-25T07:20:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":118,"user":"annp","date":"2024-02-25T05:43:03+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":16918,"user":"XPan","date":"2024-02-25T05:02:53+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":17865,"user":"Anizta","date":"2024-02-25T04:38:40+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":635,"user":"flashgordonv","date":"2024-02-24T21:31:10+0100","reaction":"Wow"},{"user_id":10595,"user":"Korzik18","date":"2024-02-24T19:45:31+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":13966,"user":"Tyomodachi","date":"2024-02-24T19:28:04+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7850,"user":"Ðekel","date":"2024-02-24T19:27:10+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":14284,"user":"iamthatis","date":"2024-02-24T19:19:37+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11705,"user":"Tuatha de Danaan","date":"2024-02-24T18:47:20+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":15488,"user":"N1mTzo","date":"2024-02-24T18:39:18+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":11897,"user":"PERLOU","date":"2024-02-24T18:12:35+0100","reaction":"Like"},{"user_id":7948,"user":"irjO","date":"2024-02-24T18:12:20+0100","reaction":"Like"}]},{"user_